23(* This basic interpreter implements the following functions and *)
24(* statements ( ** means recognized but not implemented): *)
25(* *)
26(* ABS, ASC, ATN, **BEEP, BLOAD, **CALL, CASE, CDBL, CHAIN, CHR$, *)
27(* CINT, **CIRCLE, CLEAR, CLNG, CLOSE, CLS, **COLOR, **COMMON, *)
28(* CONST, COS, CSNG, CSRLIN, CVD, CVDMBF, CVI, CVL, CVS, CVSMBF, *)
29(* DATA, DATE$, **DECLARE, DECR, DEF FN, **DEF SEG, DEFDBL, *)
30(* DEFINT, DEFLNG, DEFSNG, DEFSTR, DELAY, DIM, DISPLAY, DO, *)
31(* DO UNTIL, DO WHILE, **DRAW, ELSE, ELSEIF, END, ENDIF, EOF, *)
32(* **ERASE, ERR, ERROR, EXIT DO, EXIT FOR, EXP, FIELD, FIX, *)
33(* **FLASH, FOR, FRE, FREEFILE, **FUNCTION, GET, GET#, GOSUB, *)
34(* GOSUB OF, GOTO, GOTO OF, GR, HEX$, HGR, HOME, HPLOT, HTAB, *)
35(* IF THEN, IF GOSUB, IF GOTO, INCR, INKEY$, **INP, INPUT, INPUT#, *)
36(* INPUT$, INSTR, INT, **INVERSE, **KEY, LBOUND, LCASE$, LEFT$, *)
37(* LEN, LET, LINE INPUT, LINE INPUT#, LINPUT, LINPUT# LOCATE, LOF, *)
38(* LOG, LOOP, LOOP UNTIL, LOOP WHILE, LSET, LTRIM$, MID$, MKD$, *)
39(* MKDMBF$, MKI$, MKL$, MKS$, MKSMBF$, NEXT, **NORMAL, OCT$, *)
40(* ON ERROR, ON GOSUB, ON GOTO, **ON KEY, **ON TIMER, OPEN, *)
41(* OPTION BASE, **OUT, **PAINT, **PALETTE, **PEEK, **PLAY, PLOT, *)
42(* **POINT, **POKE, POS, PRESET, PRINT, PRINT#, PRINT USING, *)
43(* **PR#, PSET, PUT, PUT#, RANDOMIZE, READ, REDIM, REM, RESET, *)
44(* RESTORE, RESUME, RETURN, RIGHT$, RND, RPT$, RSET, RTRIM$, *)
45(* **RUN, SCREEN, SEEK#, SEG$, SELECT, SGN, SIN, SLEEP, **SOUND, *)
46(* SPACE$, SPC, SQR, STOP, STR$, **STRIG, STRING$, **SUB, SWAP, *)
47(* SYSTEM, TAB, TAN, TEXT, TIME$, TIMER, **TYPE, UBOUND, UCASE$, *)
48(* VAL, VTAB, WEND, WHILE, WRITE, WRITE# *)

279const proc: sleep (in integer: secs) is func
280 local
281 var time: start_time is time.value;
282 begin
283 start_time := time(NOW);
284 await(start_time + secs . SECONDS);
285 end func;
286
287
288const proc: delay (in float: secs) is func
289 local
290 var time: start_time is time.value;
291 var integer: seconds is 0;
292 var integer: micro_seconds is 0;
293 begin
294 start_time := time(NOW);
295 seconds := trunc(secs);
296 micro_seconds := round((secs - flt(seconds)) * 1000000.0);
297 await(start_time + seconds . SECONDS + micro_seconds . MICRO_SECONDS);
298 end func;
299
300
301const proc: listProg (inout file: listFile, in integer: fromLine, in integer: toLine) is func
302 local
303 var integer: number is 0;
304 var boolean: doList is FALSE;
305 begin
306 doList := fromLine = 0;
307 for number range 1 to length(prg) do
308 if prg[number].linenum <> "" then
309 doList := integer(prg[number].linenum) >= fromLine and
310 integer(prg[number].linenum) <= toLine;
311 end if;
312 if doList and (prg[number].line <> "" or prg[number].linenum <> "" or
313 prg[number].label <> "") then
314 # write(listFile, ("(" <& number <& ")") lpad 5 <& " ");
315 if prg[number].linenum <> "" then
316 write(listFile, prg[number].linenum <& " ");
317 end if;
318 if prg[number].label <> "" then
319 write(listFile, prg[number].label <& ": ");
320 end if;
321 writeln(listFile, prg[number].line);
322 end if;
323 if prg[number].linenum <> "" then
324 doList := integer(prg[number].linenum) >= fromLine and
325 integer(prg[number].linenum) < toLine;
326 end if;
327 end for;
328 end func;

331(**
332 * Reads a BASIC symbol from a 'string'.
333 * When the function is called it is assumed that 'line' is empty or
334 * line[1] contains the first character to be handled. When the
335 * function is left 'line' is empty or line[1] contains the character
336 * after the BASIC symbol. A BASIC symbol can be:
337 * - A name: A letter followed by letters, digits or '.'.
338 * Optionally a '$', '%', '!', '#' or '&' can be added.
339 * - An integer number: A sequence of digits.
340 * - A float number: A sequence of digits which contains one
341 * decimal point. An optional exponent may follow. If
342 * an exponent is present the decimal point may be
343 * omitted. The exponent is introduced with 'E' or 'e'
344 * followed by an optional sign ('+' or '-') and a
345 * sequence of digits. If the float number does start
346 * with '.' a '0' is added in front of the returned
347 * symbol.
348 * - A hex literal: It starts with '&H' or '&h' followed by hex
349 * digits. A hex literal is converted to decimal and the
350 * decimal literal is returned.
351 * - An octal literal: It starts with '&O' or '&o' followed by
352 * octal digits. An octal literal is converted to decimal
353 * and the decimal literal is returned.
354 * - A string literal: A sequence of characters enclosed in double
355 * quotation marks. A string literal is returned with the
356 * introducing " but without the ending " .
357 * - A special symbol: The symbols '<>', '<=' and '>=' are special
358 * symbols consisting of two characters. There can be a
359 * spaces and tabs between the two characters. Such
360 * spaces and tabs are removed from the symbol.
361 * It is even possible that the two characters of a
362 * special symbol are interchanged. In this case the
363 * symbol is returned in the standardized form.
364 * - A one character symbol: If no other symbols can be
365 * recognized a symbol consisting of one character is
366 * created. E.g.: '=', '+', '-'.
367 * @return the BASIC symbol or "" at the end of the line.
368 *)
369const func string: get_symbol (inout string: line) is func
370 result
371 var string: symbol is "";
372 local
373 var integer: leng is 0;
374 var integer: start is 0;
375 var integer: index is 0;
376 var char: ch is ' ';
377 begin
378 leng := length(line);
379 if leng > 0 then
380 repeat
381 incr(start);
382 if start <= leng then
383 ch := line[start];
384 else
385 ch := '\0;';
386 end if;
387 until ch <> ' ' and ch <> '\t';
388 index := start;
389 case ch of
390 when letter_char:
391 repeat
392 incr(index);
393 if index <= leng then
394 ch := line[index];
395 else
396 ch := ' ';
397 end if;
398 until ch not in basic_name_char;
399 if ch = '$' or ch = '%' or ch = '!' or ch = '#' or ch = '&' then
400 incr(index);
401 end if;
402 symbol := upper(line[start .. pred(index)]);
403 line := line[index .. ];
404 when digit_char:
405 repeat
406 incr(index);
407 if index <= leng then
408 ch := line[index];
409 else
410 ch := ' ';
411 end if;
412 until ch not in digit_char;
413 if ch = '.' then
414 incr(index);
415 if index <= leng and line[index] in digit_char then
416 repeat
417 incr(index);
418 if index <= leng then
419 ch := line[index];
420 else
421 ch := ' ';
422 end if;
423 until ch not in digit_char;
424 end if;
425 end if;
426 if ch = 'E' or ch = 'e' then
427 incr(index);
428 if index <= leng then
429 ch := line[index];
430 else
431 ch := ' ';
432 end if;
433 if ch in digit_char or ch = '+' or ch = '-' then
434 if ch = '+' or ch = '-' then
435 incr(index);
436 if index <= leng then
437 ch := line[index];
438 else
439 ch := ' ';
440 end if;
441 end if;
442 while ch in digit_char do
443 incr(index);
444 if index <= leng then
445 ch := line[index];
446 else
447 ch := ' ';
448 end if;
449 end while;
450 else
451 decr(index);
452 end if;
453 end if;
454 if ch in number_suffix then
455 incr(index);
456 end if;
457 symbol := line[start .. pred(index)];
458 line := line[index .. ];
459 when {'.'}:
460 incr(index);
461 if index <= leng and line[index] in digit_char then
462 repeat
463 incr(index);
464 if index <= leng then
465 ch := line[index];
466 else
467 ch := ' ';
468 end if;
469 until ch not in digit_char;
470 if ch = 'E' or ch = 'e' then
471 incr(index);
472 if index <= leng then
473 ch := line[index];
474 else
475 ch := ' ';
476 end if;
477 if ch in digit_char or ch = '+' or ch = '-' then
478 if ch = '+' or ch = '-' then
479 incr(index);
480 if index <= leng then
481 ch := line[index];
482 else
483 ch := ' ';
484 end if;
485 end if;
486 while ch in digit_char do
487 incr(index);
488 if index <= leng then
489 ch := line[index];
490 else
491 ch := ' ';
492 end if;
493 end while;
494 else
495 decr(index);
496 end if;
497 end if;
498 if ch in number_suffix then
499 incr(index);
500 end if;
501 symbol := "0" & line[start .. pred(index)];
502 line := line[index .. ];
503 else
504 symbol := ".";
505 line := line[index .. ];
506 end if;
507 when {'&'}:
508 incr(index);
509 if index <= leng then
510 ch := line[index];
511 if ch = 'H' or ch = 'h' then
512 incr(index);
513 start := index;
514 while index <= leng and line[index] in hexdigit_char do
515 incr(index);
516 end while;
517 if index > start then
518 symbol := str(integer(line[start .. pred(index)], 16));
519 if index <= leng and line[index] in number_suffix then
520 symbol &:= line[index len 1];
521 incr(index);
522 end if;
523 else
524 symbol := "&H";
525 end if;
526 elsif ch = 'O' or ch = 'o' then
527 incr(index);
528 start := index;
529 while index <= leng and line[index] in octdigit_char do
530 incr(index);
531 end while;
532 if index > start then
533 symbol := str(integer(line[start .. pred(index)], 8));
534 if index <= leng and line[index] in number_suffix then
535 symbol &:= line[index len 1];
536 incr(index);
537 end if;
538 else
539 symbol := "&O";
540 end if;
541 else
542 symbol := "&";
543 end if;
544 else
545 symbol := "&";
546 end if;
547 line := line[index .. ];
548 when {'"'}:
549 repeat
550 incr(index);
551 until index > leng or line[index] = '"';
552 symbol := line[start .. pred(index)];
553 line := line[succ(index) .. ];
554 when {'<'}:
555 # Sometimes <> or <= are written as < > or < =
556 repeat
557 incr(index);
558 if index <= leng then
559 ch := line[index];
560 else
561 ch := '\0;';
562 end if;
563 until ch <> ' ' and ch <> '\t';
564 if ch = '>' then
565 incr(index);
566 symbol := "<>";
567 elsif ch = '=' then
568 incr(index);
569 symbol := "<=";
570 else
571 symbol := "<";
572 end if;
573 line := line[index .. ];
574 when {'>'}:
575 # Sometimes >= is written as > =
576 repeat
577 incr(index);
578 if index <= leng then
579 ch := line[index];
580 else
581 ch := '\0;';
582 end if;
583 until ch <> ' ' and ch <> '\t';
584 if ch = '=' then
585 incr(index);
586 symbol := ">=";
587 elsif ch = '<' then
588 # Sometimes <> is written as >< or > <
589 incr(index);
590 symbol := "<>";
591 else
592 symbol := ">";
593 end if;
594 line := line[index .. ];
595 when {'='}:
596 repeat
597 incr(index);
598 if index <= leng then
599 ch := line[index];
600 else
601 ch := '\0;';
602 end if;
603 until ch <> ' ' and ch <> '\t';
604 if ch = '<' then
605 # Sometimes <= is written as =< or = <
606 incr(index);
607 symbol := "<=";
608 elsif ch = '>' then
609 # Sometimes >= is written as => or = >
610 incr(index);
611 symbol := ">=";
612 else
613 symbol := "=";
614 end if;
615 line := line[index .. ];
616 when {'\r'}:
617 symbol := "";
618 line := line[succ(index) .. ];
619 otherwise:
620 symbol := line[index len 1];
621 line := line[succ(index) .. ];
622 end case;
623 end if;
624 # writeln(log, "SY=" <& literal(symbol));
625 end func;
626
627
628const func boolean: endOfStatement (in string: symbol) is
629 return symbol = ":" or symbol = "" or symbol = "'" or symbol = "REM" or symbol = "ELSE";
630
631
632const func boolean: ignoreRestOfLine (in string: symbol) is
633 return symbol = "'" or symbol = "REM" or symbol = "DATA" or symbol = "DATA&";
634
635
636const func boolean: isStringExpr (in string: symbol) is
637 return symbol in string_var_name or
638 symbol <> "" and
639 (symbol[length(symbol)] = '$' or symbol[1] = '\"' or symbol[1] in defstr_var and
640 not symbol[length(symbol)] in numeric_var_suffix);
641
642
643const func boolean: isStringVar (in string: symbol) is
644 return symbol in string_var_name or
645 symbol <> "" and
646 (symbol[length(symbol)] = '$' or symbol[1] in defstr_var and
647 not symbol[length(symbol)] in numeric_var_suffix);
648
649
650const func boolean: isNumericVar (in string: symbol) is
651 return symbol not in string_var_name or
652 symbol <> "" and
653 (symbol[1] in letter_char - defstr_var or
654 symbol[length(symbol)] in numeric_var_suffix);
655
656
657const func float: getNumericVar (in string: varName) is func
658 result
659 var float: numericValue is 0.0;
660 begin
661 if varName in numeric_var then
662 numericValue := numeric_var[varName];
663 end if;
664 end func;
665
666
667const proc: setNumericVar (in string: varName, in float: number) is func
668 begin
669 numeric_var @:= [varName] number;
670 end func;
671
672
673const func string: getStringVar (in string: varName) is func
674 result
675 var string: stringValue is "";
676 begin
677 if varName in string_var then
678 stringValue := string_var[varName];
679 end if;
680 end func;
681
682
683const proc: setStringVar (in string: varName, in string: stri) is func
684 begin
685 string_var @:= [varName] stri;
686 end func;
687
688
689const func integer: varptr (in string: variable_name) is func
690 result
691 var integer: address is 0;
692 begin
693 if variable_name not in varptr_value then
694 varptr_value @:= [variable_name] succ(length(varptr_value));
695 end if;
696 address := varptr_value[variable_name];
697 varname_value @:= [address] variable_name;
698 end func;

700
701const func string: varptrStri (in string: variable_name) is func
702 result
703 var string: addrStri is "";
704 local
705 var integer: address is 0;
706 begin
707 address := varptr(variable_name);
708 addrStri := "\3;" & bytes(address, UNSIGNED, LE);
709 end func;

715 begin
716 if address in varname_value then
717 variable_name := varname_value[address];

719 end func;

749const proc: addDoLoopHeader (in integer: tailLine, in integer: tailColumn,
750 in integer: headLine, in integer: headColumn) is func
751 begin
752 if tailLine in doLoopHeaders then
753 if tailColumn not in doLoopHeaders[tailLine] then
754 doLoopHeaders[tailLine] @:= [tailColumn] doLoopDescrType.value;
755 end if;
756 else
757 doLoopHeaders @:= [tailLine] doLoopHeaderInColumn.value;
758 doLoopHeaders[tailLine] @:= [tailColumn] doLoopDescrType.value;
759 end if;
760 doLoopHeaders[tailLine][tailColumn].headLine := headLine;
761 doLoopHeaders[tailLine][tailColumn].headColumn := headColumn;
762 end func;
763
764
765const func boolean: doLoopHeaderPresent (in integer: tailLine, in integer: tailColumn,
766 inout integer: headLine, inout integer: headColumn) is func
767 result
768 var boolean: headerIsPresent is FALSE;
769 begin
770 if tailLine in doLoopHeaders then
771 if tailColumn in doLoopHeaders[tailLine] then
772 headerIsPresent := TRUE;
773 headLine := doLoopHeaders[tailLine][tailColumn].headLine;
774 headColumn := doLoopHeaders[tailLine][tailColumn].headColumn;
775 end if;
776 end if;
777 end func;

780const proc: line_marker is func
781 begin
782 if statement_label <> "" then
783 write(log, statement_label <& " ");
784 elsif file_line_number >= 1 and file_line_number <= length(prg) then
785 if prg[file_line_number].fileName <> prg[1].fileName then
786 write(log, prg[file_line_number].fileName);
787 end if;
788 write(log, "(" <& prg[file_line_number].fileLine <& ") ");
789 else
790 write(log, "##### " <& file_line_number <& " ##### ");
791 end if;
792 end func;
793
794
795const proc: line_marker (in integer: line_number) is func
796 begin
797 if line_number >= 1 and line_number <= length(prg) then
798 if prg[line_number].label <> "" then
799 write(log, prg[line_number].label);
800 elsif prg[line_number].linenum <> "" then
801 write(log, prg[line_number].linenum);
802 else
803 if prg[line_number].fileName <> prg[1].fileName then
804 write(log, prg[line_number].fileName);
805 end if;
806 write(log, "(" <& prg[line_number].fileLine <& ")");
807 end if;
808 else
809 write(log, "##### " <& line_number <& " ##### ");
810 end if;
811 end func;
812
813
814const proc: error_marker is func
815 begin
816 write(err, " ***** ");
817 if statement_label <> "" then
818 write(err, "[" <& statement_label <& "] ");
819 elsif file_line_number >= 1 and file_line_number <= length(prg) then
820 if prg[file_line_number].fileName <> prg[1].fileName then
821 write(err, prg[file_line_number].fileName);
822 end if;
823 write(err, "(" <& prg[file_line_number].fileLine <& ") ");
824 end if;
825 end func;

828const proc: error_marker (in string: label) is func
829 begin
830 write(err, " ***** (" <& label <& ") ");
831 end func;

834const proc: error_expect (in string: expected_symbol, in string: symbol) is func
835 begin
836 error_marker;
837 writeln(err, literal(expected_symbol) <&
838 " EXPECTED - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
839 end func;

842const proc: error_expect2 (in string: expected_symbol1, in string: expected_symbol2, in string: symbol) is func
843 begin
844 error_marker;
845 writeln(err, literal(expected_symbol1) <& " OR " <& literal(expected_symbol2) <&
846 " EXPECTED - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
847 end func;

849
850const proc: error_expect3 (in string: expected_symbol1, in string: expected_symbol2,
851 in string: expected_symbol3, in string: symbol) is func
852 begin
853 error_marker;
854 writeln(err, literal(expected_symbol1) <& ", " <& literal(expected_symbol2) <& " OR " <&
855 literal(expected_symbol3) <& " EXPECTED - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
856 end func;

858
859const proc: expect (in string: expected_symbol, inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
860 begin
861 if symbol = expected_symbol then
862 symbol := get_symbol(line);
863 else
864 error_expect(expected_symbol, symbol);
865 end if;
866 end func;

869const func boolean: label_or_linenum (in string: symbol) is
870 return symbol in label or (symbol <> "" and symbol[1] in digit_char);
871
872
873const proc: goto_label_or_linenum (in string: new_label) is func
874 local
875 var integer: number is 0;
876 var integer: searched_linenum is 0;
877 var integer: matched_linenum is MAX_LINENUM;
878 var integer: linenum is 0;
879 begin
880 if new_label in label then
881 statement_label := new_label;
882 file_line_number := pred(label[statement_label]);
883 elsif new_label <> "" and new_label[1] in digit_char then
884 searched_linenum := integer(new_label);
885 for number range 1 to length(prg) do
886 if prg[number].linenum <> "" then
887 linenum := integer(prg[number].linenum);
888 if linenum >= searched_linenum and
889 linenum < matched_linenum then
890 matched_linenum := linenum;
891 end if;
892 end if;
893 end for;
894 if matched_linenum <> MAX_LINENUM and
895 str(matched_linenum) in label then
896 error_marker;
897 writeln(err, "LABEL " <& new_label <&
898 " DOES NOT EXIST - USE " <& matched_linenum <& " INSTEAD");
899 statement_label := str(matched_linenum);
900 file_line_number := pred(label[statement_label]);
901 else
902 error_marker;
903 writeln(err, "LABEL " <& new_label <& " DOES NOT EXIST");
904 end if;
905 else
906 error_marker;
907 writeln(err, "LABEL " <& new_label <& " DOES NOT EXIST");
908 end if;
909 end func;
910
911
912const proc: set_return_position (in string: line) is func
913 local
914 var integer: column is 0;
915 begin
916 column := length(prg[file_line_number].line) - length(line) + 1;
917 gosubReturn := [] (gosubReturnDescrType.value) & gosubReturn;
918 gosubReturn[1].returnLine := file_line_number;
919 gosubReturn[1].returnColumn := column;
920 gosubReturn[1].forLoopStackDepth := length(forLoop);
921 gosubReturn[1].whileLoopStackDepth := length(whileLoop);
922 gosubReturn[1].doLoopStackDepth := length(doLoop);
923 end func;
924
925
926const proc: set_sub_entry_position is func
927 begin
928 gosubReturn[1].subEntryLine := succ(file_line_number);
929 end func;
930
931
932const proc: check_loop_stacks_before_return (in string: returnStatementName) is func
933 begin
934 if length(forLoop) > gosubReturn[1].forLoopStackDepth then
935 error_marker;
936 writeln(err, returnStatementName <& " - SOME FOR LOOPS WERE NOT LEFT");
937 repeat
938 line_marker;
939 write(log, "LEAVE THE \"FOR " <& forLoop[1].varName <&
940 "\" LOOP AT LINE ");
941 line_marker(forLoop[1].bodyLine);
942 writeln(log);
943 forLoop := forLoop[2 .. ];
944 until length(forLoop) <= gosubReturn[1].forLoopStackDepth;
945 end if;
946 if length(whileLoop) > gosubReturn[1].whileLoopStackDepth then
947 error_marker;
948 writeln(err, returnStatementName <& " - SOME WHILE LOOPS WERE NOT LEFT");
949 repeat
950 line_marker;
951 write(log, "LEAVE THE \"WHILE\" LOOP AT LINE ");
952 line_marker(whileLoop[1].condLine);
953 writeln(log);
954 whileLoop := whileLoop[2 .. ];
955 until length(whileLoop) <= gosubReturn[1].whileLoopStackDepth;
956 end if;
957 if length(doLoop) > gosubReturn[1].doLoopStackDepth then
958 error_marker;
959 writeln(err, returnStatementName <& " - SOME DO LOOPS WERE NOT LEFT");
960 repeat
961 line_marker;
962 write(log, "LEAVE THE \"DO\" LOOP AT LINE ");
963 line_marker(doLoop[1].headLine);
964 writeln(log);
965 doLoop := doLoop[2 .. ];
966 until length(doLoop) <= gosubReturn[1].doLoopStackDepth;
967 end if;
968 end func;
969
970
971const proc: do_return (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
972 begin
973 file_line_number := gosubReturn[1].returnLine;
974 statement_label := prg[file_line_number].linenum;
975 line := prg[file_line_number].line[gosubReturn[1].returnColumn .. ];
976 symbol := get_symbol(line);
977 gosubReturn := gosubReturn[2 .. ];
978 end func;

981const proc: goto_on_error (in string: on_error_label, in string: line) is func
982 begin
983 error_linenum := prg[file_line_number].linenum;
984 resume_next_line := file_line_number;
985 resume_next_column :=
986 length(prg[file_line_number].line) - length(line) + 1;
987 in_error_handler := TRUE;
988 goto_label_or_linenum(on_error_label);
989 end func;
990
991
992const proc: do_resume_next (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
993 begin
994 if resume_next_line <> 0 then
995 file_line_number := resume_next_line;
996 statement_label := prg[file_line_number].linenum;
997 line := prg[file_line_number].line[resume_next_column .. ];
998 symbol := get_symbol(line);
999 in_error_handler := FALSE;
1000 resume_next_line := 0;
1001 else
1002 error_marker;
1003 writeln(err, "CANNOT RESUME NEXT");
1004 end if;
1005 end func;
1006
1007
1008const proc: do_resume_same (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
1009 begin
1010 if resume_same_line <> 0 then
1011 file_line_number := resume_same_line;
1012 statement_label := prg[file_line_number].linenum;
1013 line := prg[file_line_number].line[resume_same_column .. ];
1014 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1015 in_error_handler := FALSE;
1016 resume_same_line := 0;
1017 else
1018 error_marker;
1019 writeln(err, "CANNOT RESUME 0");
1020 end if;
1021 end func;

1024const func color: color_num (in integer: col_num) is func
1025 result
1026 var color: col is black;
1027 begin
1028 case col_num of
1029 when {0}: col := black;
1030 when {1}: col := dark_blue;
1031 when {2}: col := dark_green;
1032 when {3}: col := dark_cyan;
1033 when {4}: col := dark_red;
1034 when {5}: col := dark_magenta;
1035 when {6}: col := brown;
1036 when {7}: col := light_gray;
1037 when {8}: col := dark_gray;
1038 when {9}: col := light_blue;
1039 when {10}: col := light_green;
1040 when {11}: col := light_cyan;
1041 when {12}: col := light_red;
1042 when {13}: col := light_magenta;
1043 when {14}: col := yellow;
1044 when {15}: col := white;
1045 end case;
1046 end func;

1049const func string: get_data_line (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
1050 result
1051 var string: data_line is "";
1052 local
1053 var boolean: searching is TRUE;
1054 var string: data_symbol is "";
1055 begin
1056 while searching do
1057 incr(data_line_number);
1058 if data_line_number > length(prg) then
1059 if on_error_label <> "" then
1060 error_code := 4; # Out of data
1061 line_marker;
1062 writeln(log, error_code <& " OUT OF DATA" <&
1063 " - ON ERROR GOTO " <& on_error_label);
1064 goto_on_error(on_error_label, line);
1065 symbol := "";
1066 line := "";
1067 else
1068 error_marker;
1069 writeln(err, "OUT OF DATA");
1070 end if;
1071 data_line := ",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,";
1072 searching := FALSE;
1073 elsif prg[data_line_number].line <> "" then
1074 data_line := prg[data_line_number].line;
1075 (* writeln(data_line_number lpad 5 <& " " <&
1076 prg[data_line_number].line); *)
1077 repeat
1078 data_symbol := get_symbol(data_line);
1079 until data_symbol = "" or
1080 data_symbol = "DATA" or data_symbol = "DATA&" or
1081 data_symbol = "'" or data_symbol = "REM";
1082 if data_symbol = "DATA&" then
1083 data_symbol := "DATA";
1084 data_line := "&" & data_line;
1085 line_marker;
1086 writeln(log, "DATA STATEMENT CORRECTED FROM " <&
1087 literal(prg[data_line_number].line) <&
1088 " TO " <& literal("DATA " & data_line));
1089 end if;
1090 if data_symbol = "DATA" then
1091 searching := FALSE;
1092 end if;
1093 end if;
1094 end while;
1095 end func;
1096
1097
1098const proc: data_statement_in_line is func
1099 local
1100 var string: data_symbol is "";
1101 begin
1102 data_symbol := get_symbol(data_line);
1103 if data_symbol = "DATA&" then
1104 data_symbol := "DATA";
1105 data_line := "&" & data_line;
1106 line_marker;
1107 writeln(log, "DATA STATEMENT CORRECTED FROM " <&
1108 literal(prg[data_line_number].line) <&
1109 " TO " <& literal("DATA " & data_line));
1110 end if;
1111 if data_symbol = "'" or data_symbol = "REM" then
1112 data_line := "";
1113 elsif data_symbol <> "" and data_symbol <> "DATA" then
1114 error_expect3("DATA", "REM", "'", data_symbol);
1115 end if;
1116 end func;
1117
1118
1119const func string: get_data_field (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
1120 result
1121 var string: data_field is "";
1122 local
1123 var integer: comma_pos is 0;
1124 var integer: quote_pos is 0;
1125 var integer: colon_pos is 0;
1126 var string: data_symbol is "";
1127 begin
1128 if data_line = "" then
1129 data_line := get_data_line(symbol, line);
1130 end if;
1131 if not in_error_handler then
1132 while data_line <> "" and data_line[1] = ' ' do
1133 data_line := data_line[2 .. ];
1134 end while;
1135 if data_line <> "" and data_line[1] = '"' then
1136 data_field := "";
1137 data_line := data_line[2 .. ];
1138 quote_pos := pos(data_line, "\"");
1139 while quote_pos <> 0 do
1140 if succ(quote_pos) <= length(data_line) and
1141 data_line[succ(quote_pos)] = '"' then
1142 data_field &:= data_line[ .. quote_pos];
1143 data_line := data_line[quote_pos + 2 .. ];
1144 quote_pos := pos(data_line, "\"");
1145 else
1146 data_field &:= data_line[ .. pred(quote_pos)];
1147 data_line := data_line[succ(quote_pos) .. ];
1148 quote_pos := 0;
1149 end if;
1150 end while;
1151 while data_line <> "" and data_line[1] = ' ' do
1152 data_line := data_line[2 .. ];
1153 end while;
1154 if data_line <> "" then
1155 if data_line[1] = ':' then
1156 data_line := data_line[2 .. ];
1157 data_statement_in_line;
1158 elsif data_line[1] = ',' then
1159 data_line := data_line[2 .. ];
1160 else
1161 data_symbol := get_symbol(data_line);
1162 if data_symbol = "'" or data_symbol = "REM" then
1163 data_line := "";
1164 else
1165 error_expect2(",", ":", data_symbol);
1166 end if;
1167 end if;
1168 end if;
1169 else
1170 comma_pos := pos(data_line, ",");
1171 colon_pos := pos(data_line, ":");
1172 if colon_pos <> 0 then
1173 if comma_pos = 0 or colon_pos < comma_pos then
1174 data_field := data_line[ .. pred(colon_pos)];
1175 data_line := data_line[succ(colon_pos) .. ];
1176 data_statement_in_line;
1177 else
1178 data_field := data_line[ .. pred(comma_pos)];
1179 data_line := data_line[succ(comma_pos) .. ];
1180 if data_line = "" then
1181 (* A comma at the end of a DATA line is READ as an *)
1182 (* empty string with the next call of get_data_field. *)
1183 data_line := " ";
1184 end if;
1185 end if;
1186 else
1187 if comma_pos <> 0 then
1188 data_field := data_line[ .. pred(comma_pos)];
1189 data_line := data_line[succ(comma_pos) .. ];
1190 if data_line = "" then
1191 (* A comma at the end of a DATA line is READ as an *)
1192 (* empty string with the next call of get_data_field. *)
1193 data_line := " ";
1194 end if;
1195 else
1196 data_field := data_line;
1197 data_line := "";
1198 end if;
1199 end if;
1200 end if;
1201 end if;
1202 end func;
1203
1204
1205const proc: skip_space_cr_lf (inout file: inFile) is func
1206 local
1207 var char: ch is ' ';
1208 begin
1209 ch := inFile.bufferChar;
1210 while ch = ' ' or ch = '\r' or ch = '\n' do
1211 ch := getc(inFile);
1212 end while;
1213 inFile.bufferChar := ch;
1214 end func;
1215
1216
1217const func string: read_input_string (inout file: inFile) is func
1218 result
1219 var string: stri is "";
1220 local
1221 var char: ch is ' ';
1222 begin
1223 ch := inFile.bufferChar;
1224 if ch = '"' then
1225 ch := getc(inFile);
1226 while ch <> '"' and ch <> '\r' and ch <> '\n' and ch <> EOF do
1227 stri &:= str(ch);
1228 ch := getc(inFile);
1229 end while;
1230 ch := getc(inFile);
1231 else
1232 while ch <> ',' and ch <> '\r' and ch <> '\n' and ch <> EOF do
1233 stri &:= str(ch);
1234 ch := getc(inFile);
1235 end while;
1236 end if;
1237 inFile.bufferChar := ch;
1238 end func;
1239
1240
1241const func string: read_input_number (inout file: inFile) is func
1242 result
1243 var string: number is "";
1244 local
1245 var char: ch is ' ';
1246 begin
1247 ch := inFile.bufferChar;
1248 if ch = '"' then
1249 ch := getc(inFile);
1250 while ch <> '"' and ch <> '\r' and ch <> '\n' and ch <> EOF do
1251 number &:= str(ch);
1252 ch := getc(inFile);
1253 end while;
1254 ch := getc(inFile);
1255 else
1256 while ch <> ',' and ch <> ' ' and ch <> '\r' and ch <> '\n' and ch <> EOF do
1257 number &:= str(ch);
1258 ch := getc(inFile);
1259 end while;
1260 end if;
1261 inFile.bufferChar := ch;
1262 end func;

1291const proc: set_function (in string: name, in string: params, in string: expression) is func
1292 local
1293 var defFnType: newDefFn is defFnType.value;
1294 begin
1295 if name not in def_fn_list then
1296 newDefFn.name := name;
1297 newDefFn.params := params;
1298 newDefFn.expression := expression;
1299 def_fn_list @:= [name] (newDefFn);
1300 end if;
1301 end func;

1303
1304const proc: define_function (in var string: variable_name,
1305 inout string: symbol, inout string: line, in boolean: doLog) is func
1306 local
1307 var string: param1 is "";
1308 var string: param2 is "";
1309 var integer: func_end_pos is 0;
1310 begin
1311 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1312 if variable_name = "FN" and symbol <> "" and
1313 symbol[1] >= 'A' and symbol[1] <= 'Z' then
1314 variable_name &:= symbol;
1315 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1316 end if;
1317 param1 := "";
1318 if symbol = "(" then
1319 repeat
1320 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1321 if symbol <> "" and symbol[1] >= 'A' and symbol[1] <= 'Z' then
1322 param1 &:= symbol & " ";
1323 end if;
1324 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1325 until symbol <> ",";
1326 expect(")", symbol, line);
1327 if length(param1) >= 1 then
1328 param1 := param1[.. pred(length(param1))];
1329 end if;
1330 end if;
1331 if symbol = "=" then
1332 param2 := line;
1333 repeat
1334 func_end_pos := length(line);
1335 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1336 until endOfStatement(symbol);
1337 param2 := param2[ .. length(param2) - func_end_pos];
1338 set_function(variable_name, param1, param2);
1339 if doLog then
1340 line_marker;
1341 writeln(log, "DEF " <& variable_name <& "(" <& param1 <& ")=" <& param2);
1342 end if;
1343 else
1344 expect("=", symbol, line);
1345 end if;
1346 end func;
1347
1348
1349const proc: getBoundsFromIndexPart (in var string: indexPart, in integer: dimension,
1350 inout boolean: first, inout integer: lbound, inout integer: ubound) is func
1351 local
1352 var integer: indexDimension is 0;
1353 var integer: anIndex is 0;
1354 begin
1355 if indexPart <> "" and (indexPart[1] = '[' or indexPart[1] = '(') then
1356 repeat
1357 indexPart := indexPart[2 ..];
1358 anIndex := integer(getDigits(indexPart));
1359 incr(indexDimension);
1360 until indexDimension = dimension;
1361 if first then
1362 lbound := anIndex;
1363 ubound := anIndex;
1364 first := FALSE;
1365 else
1366 if anIndex < lbound then
1367 lbound := anIndex;
1368 end if;
1369 if anIndex > ubound then
1370 ubound := anIndex;
1371 end if;
1372 end if;
1373 end if;
1374 end func;
1375
1376
1377const proc: getBounds (in string: array_name, in integer: dimension,
1378 inout integer: lbound, inout integer: ubound) is func
1379 local
1380 var string: varName is "";
1381 var boolean: first is TRUE;
1382 begin
1383 for key varName range numeric_var do
1384 if startsWith(varName, array_name) then
1385 getBoundsFromIndexPart(varName[succ(length(array_name)) ..],
1386 dimension, first, lbound, ubound);
1387 end if;
1388 end for;
1389 for key varName range string_var do
1390 if startsWith(varName, array_name) then
1391 getBoundsFromIndexPart(varName[succ(length(array_name)) ..],
1392 dimension, first, ubound, ubound);
1393 end if;
1394 end for;
1395 end func;
1396

1399 result
1400 var integer: lbound is 0;
1401 local
1402 var integer: ubound is 0;
1403 begin
1404 getBounds(array_name, dimension, lbound, ubound);

1418const func integer: getFirstIndex (in string: array_name,
1419 inout string: name_start, inout string: name_end) is func
1420 result
1421 var integer: lbound is 0;
1422 local
1423 var integer: parenPos is 0;
1424 var integer: commaPos is 0;
1425 var integer: paren2Pos is 0;
1426 var string: indexString is "";
1427 begin
1428 parenPos := pos(array_name, "(");
1429 if parenPos = 0 then
1430 parenPos := pos(array_name, "[");
1431 end if;
1432 if parenPos <> 0 then
1433 name_start := array_name[.. parenPos];
1434 commaPos := pos(array_name, ",", succ(parenPos));
1435 if commaPos <> 0 then
1436 name_end := array_name[commaPos ..];
1437 indexString := array_name[succ(parenPos) .. pred(commaPos)];
1438 else
1439 paren2Pos := pos(array_name, ")", succ(parenPos));
1440 if paren2Pos = 0 then
1441 paren2Pos := pos(array_name, "]", succ(parenPos));
1442 end if;
1443 if paren2Pos <> 0 then
1444 name_end := array_name[paren2Pos ..];
1445 indexString := array_name[succ(parenPos) .. pred(paren2Pos)];
1446 end if;
1447 end if;
1448 lbound := integer(indexString);
1449 end if;
1450 end func;

1453const func float: exec_expr (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is forward;
1454
1455
1456const proc: append_index (inout string: name, inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
1457 local
1458 var float: num is 0.0;
1459 begin
1460 if symbol = "(" or symbol = "[" then
1461 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1462 num := exec_expr(symbol, line);
1463 name &:= "(" & str(round(num));
1464 while symbol = "," do
1465 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1466 num := exec_expr(symbol, line);
1467 name &:= "," & str(round(num));
1468 end while;
1469 if symbol <> ")" and symbol <> "]" then
1470 error_expect2(")", "]", symbol);
1471 else
1472 name &:= ")";
1473 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1474 end if;
1475 end if;
1476 if symbol = "." then
1477 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1478 name &:= "." & symbol;
1479 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1480 end if;
1481 end func;
1482

1484const func string: get_name (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
1485 result
1486 var string: name is "";
1487 begin
1488 name := symbol;
1489 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1490 append_index(name, symbol, line);
1491 end func;

1493
1494const proc: skip_parenthesized_stri (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
1495 local
1496 var string: close_symbol is "";
1497 begin
1498 if symbol = "(" then
1499 close_symbol := ")";
1500 elsif symbol = "[" then
1501 close_symbol := "]";
1502 end if;
1503 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1504 while symbol <> close_symbol and symbol <> "" do
1505 if symbol = "(" or symbol = "[" then
1506 skip_parenthesized_stri(symbol, line);
1507 else
1508 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1509 end if;
1510 end while;
1511 if symbol <> close_symbol then
1512 error_expect(close_symbol, symbol);
1513 else
1514 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1515 end if;
1516 end func;
1517
1518
1519const func boolean: is_let_statement (in string: line) is func
1520 result
1521 var boolean: is_let_statement is FALSE;
1522 local
1523 var string: symbol is "";
1524 var string: help_line is "";
1525 begin
1526 help_line := line;
1527 symbol := get_symbol(help_line);
1528 if symbol = "(" or symbol = "[" then
1529 skip_parenthesized_stri(symbol, help_line);
1530 end if;
1531 if symbol = "." then
1532 symbol := get_symbol(help_line);
1533 symbol := get_symbol(help_line);
1534 end if;
1535 is_let_statement := symbol = "=";
1536 end func;

1539const func string: exec_str_expr (
1540 inout string: symbol,
1541 inout string: line,
1542 inout string: variable_name) is forward;

1544
1545const func string: exec_str_function (in defFnType: defFn, inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
1546 result
1547 var string: exprResult is "";
1548 local
1549 var string: func_expr is "";
1550 var string: func_symbol is "";
1551 var string: formal_params is "";
1552 var string: formal_param is "";
1553 var string: unused_name is "";
1554 var array string: str_value_backup is 0 times "";
1555 var array float: num_value_backup is 0 times 0.0;
1556 begin
1557 write(log, "function " <& defFn.name);
1558 formal_params := defFn.params;
1559 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1560 if symbol = "(" then
1561 write(log, "(");
1562 repeat
1563 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1564 formal_param := get_symbol(formal_params);
1565 if formal_param[length(formal_param)] = '$' then
1566 if formal_param in string_var then
1567 str_value_backup &:= [] (string_var[formal_param]);
1568 else
1569 str_value_backup &:= [] ("");
1570 end if;
1571 string_var @:= [formal_param] exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
1572 write(log, string_var[formal_param]);
1573 else
1574 if formal_param in numeric_var then
1575 num_value_backup &:= [] (numeric_var[formal_param]);
1576 else
1577 num_value_backup &:= [] (0.0);
1578 end if;
1579 numeric_var @:= [formal_param] exec_expr(symbol, line);
1580 write(log, numeric_var[formal_param]);
1581 end if;
1582 write(log, symbol);
1583 until symbol <> ",";
1584 expect(")", symbol, line);
1585 end if;
1586 func_expr := defFn.expression;
1587 writeln(log, " = " <& func_expr);
1588 func_symbol := get_symbol(func_expr);
1589 exprResult := exec_str_expr(func_symbol, func_expr, unused_name);
1590 formal_params := defFn.params;
1591 formal_param := get_symbol(formal_params);
1592 while formal_param <> "" do
1593 if formal_param[length(formal_param)] = '$' then
1594 string_var @:= [formal_param] str_value_backup[1];
1595 str_value_backup := str_value_backup[2 ..];
1596 else
1597 numeric_var @:= [formal_param] num_value_backup[1];
1598 num_value_backup := num_value_backup[2 ..];
1599 end if;
1600 formal_param := get_symbol(formal_params);
1601 end while;
1602 end func;
1603

1709const func integer: keyboardScanCode (in char: current_key) is func
1710 result
1711 var integer: scanCode is 0;
1712 begin
1713 case current_key of
1714 when {KEY_ESC}: scanCode := 16#01;
1715 when {'!' (* At keypad: '1' *) }: scanCode := 16#02;
1716 when {'@' (* At keypad: '2' *) }: scanCode := 16#03;
1717 when {'#' (* At keypad: '3' *) }: scanCode := 16#04;
1718 when {'$' (* At keypad: '4' *) }: scanCode := 16#05;
1719 when {'%' (* At keypad: '5' *) }: scanCode := 16#06;
1720 when {'^' (* At keypad: '6' *) }: scanCode := 16#07;
1721 when {'&' (* At keypad: '7' *) }: scanCode := 16#08;
1722 when {'*' (* At keypad: '8' *) }: scanCode := 16#09;
1723 when {'(' (* At keypad: '9' *) }: scanCode := 16#0a;
1724 when {')' (* At keypad: '0' *) }: scanCode := 16#0b;
1725 when {'_', '-'}: scanCode := 16#0c;
1726 when {'+', '='}: scanCode := 16#0d;
1727 when {KEY_BS}: scanCode := 16#0e;
1728 when {KEY_TAB}: scanCode := 16#0f;
1729 when {'Q', 'q', KEY_ALT_Q, KEY_CTL_Q}: scanCode := 16#10;
1730 when {'W', 'w', KEY_ALT_W, KEY_CTL_W}: scanCode := 16#11;
1731 when {'E', 'e', KEY_ALT_E, KEY_CTL_E}: scanCode := 16#12;
1732 when {'R', 'r', KEY_ALT_R, KEY_CTL_R}: scanCode := 16#13;
1733 when {'T', 't', KEY_ALT_T, KEY_CTL_T}: scanCode := 16#14;
1734 when {'Y', 'y', KEY_ALT_Y, KEY_CTL_Y}: scanCode := 16#15;
1735 when {'U', 'u', KEY_ALT_U, KEY_CTL_U}: scanCode := 16#16;
1736 when {'I', 'i', KEY_ALT_I (* KEY_TAB=KEY_CTL_I *) }: scanCode := 16#17;
1737 when {'O', 'o', KEY_ALT_O, KEY_CTL_O}: scanCode := 16#18;
1738 when {'P', 'p', KEY_ALT_P, KEY_CTL_P}: scanCode := 16#19;
1739 when {'{', '['}: scanCode := 16#1a;
1740 when {'}', ']'}: scanCode := 16#1b;
1741 when {KEY_NL}: scanCode := 16#1c;
1742 # Not mapped: CTRL scanCode := 16#1d;
1743 when {'A', 'a', KEY_ALT_A, KEY_CTL_A}: scanCode := 16#1e;
1744 when {'S', 's', KEY_ALT_S, KEY_CTL_S}: scanCode := 16#1f;
1745 when {'D', 'd', KEY_ALT_D, KEY_CTL_D}: scanCode := 16#20;
1746 when {'F', 'f', KEY_ALT_F, KEY_CTL_F}: scanCode := 16#21;
1747 when {'G', 'g', KEY_ALT_G, KEY_CTL_G}: scanCode := 16#22;
1748 when {'H', 'h', KEY_ALT_H (* KEY_BS=KEY_CTL_H *) }: scanCode := 16#23;
1749 when {'J', 'j', KEY_ALT_J (* KEY_NL=KEY_CTL_J *) }: scanCode := 16#24;
1750 when {'K', 'k', KEY_ALT_K, KEY_CTL_K}: scanCode := 16#25;
1751 when {'L', 'l', KEY_ALT_L, KEY_CTL_L}: scanCode := 16#26;
1752 when {':', ';'}: scanCode := 16#27;
1753 when {'"', '\''}: scanCode := 16#28;
1754 when {'~', '`'}: scanCode := 16#29;
1755 # Not mapped: LEFT SHIFT scanCode := 16#2a;
1756 when {'|', '\\'}: scanCode := 16#2b;
1757 when {'Z', 'z', KEY_ALT_Z, KEY_CTL_Z}: scanCode := 16#2c;
1758 when {'X', 'x', KEY_ALT_X, KEY_CTL_X}: scanCode := 16#2d;
1759 when {'C', 'c', KEY_ALT_C, KEY_CTL_C}: scanCode := 16#2e;
1760 when {'V', 'v', KEY_ALT_V, KEY_CTL_V}: scanCode := 16#2f;
1761 when {'B', 'b', KEY_ALT_B, KEY_CTL_B}: scanCode := 16#30;
1762 when {'N', 'n', KEY_ALT_N, KEY_CTL_N}: scanCode := 16#31;
1763 when {'M', 'm', KEY_ALT_M, KEY_CTL_M}: scanCode := 16#32;
1764 when {'<', ','}: scanCode := 16#33;
1765 when {'>', '.'}: scanCode := 16#34;
1766 when {'?', '/'}: scanCode := 16#35;
1767 # Not mapped: RIGHT SHIFT scanCode := 16#36;
1768 # Not mapped: PRTSC or * scanCode := 16#37;
1769 # Not mapped: ALT scanCode := 16#38;
1770 when {' '}: scanCode := 16#39;
1771 # Not mapped: CAPSLOCK scanCode := 16#3a;
1772 when {KEY_F1, KEY_SFT_F1, KEY_CTL_F1, KEY_ALT_F1}: scanCode := 16#3b;
1773 when {KEY_F2, KEY_SFT_F2, KEY_CTL_F2, KEY_ALT_F2}: scanCode := 16#3c;
1774 when {KEY_F3, KEY_SFT_F3, KEY_CTL_F3, KEY_ALT_F3}: scanCode := 16#3d;
1775 when {KEY_F4, KEY_SFT_F4, KEY_CTL_F4, KEY_ALT_F4}: scanCode := 16#3e;
1776 when {KEY_F5, KEY_SFT_F5, KEY_CTL_F5, KEY_ALT_F5}: scanCode := 16#3f;
1777 when {KEY_F6, KEY_SFT_F6, KEY_CTL_F6, KEY_ALT_F6}: scanCode := 16#40;
1778 when {KEY_F7, KEY_SFT_F7, KEY_CTL_F7, KEY_ALT_F7}: scanCode := 16#41;
1779 when {KEY_F8, KEY_SFT_F8, KEY_CTL_F8, KEY_ALT_F8}: scanCode := 16#42;
1780 when {KEY_F9, KEY_SFT_F9, KEY_CTL_F9, KEY_ALT_F9}: scanCode := 16#43;
1781 when {KEY_F10, KEY_SFT_F10, KEY_CTL_F10, KEY_ALT_F10}: scanCode := 16#44;
1782 # Not mapped: NUMLOCK scanCode := 16#45;
1783 # Not mapped: SCROLL LOCK scanCode := 16#46;
1784 when {KEY_HOME, KEY_CTL_HOME, '7'}: scanCode := 16#47;
1785 when {KEY_UP, KEY_CTL_UP, '8'}: scanCode := 16#48;
1786 when {KEY_PGUP, KEY_CTL_PGUP, '9'}: scanCode := 16#49;
1787 # Already mapped: '-' scanCode := 16#4a;
1788 when {KEY_LEFT, KEY_CTL_LEFT, '4'}: scanCode := 16#4b;
1789 when {KEY_PAD_CENTER, '5'}: scanCode := 16#4c;
1790 when {KEY_RIGHT, KEY_CTL_RIGHT, '6'}: scanCode := 16#4d;
1791 # Already mapped: '+' scanCode := 16#4e;
1792 when {KEY_END, KEY_CTL_END, '1'}: scanCode := 16#4f;
1793 when {KEY_DOWN, KEY_CTL_DOWN, '2'}: scanCode := 16#50;
1794 when {KEY_PGDN, KEY_CTL_PGDN, '3'}: scanCode := 16#51;
1795 when {KEY_INS, KEY_CTL_INS, '0'}: scanCode := 16#52;
1796 when {KEY_DEL, KEY_CTL_DEL (* '.' *) }: scanCode := 16#53;
1797 otherwise: scanCode := 0;
1798 end case;
1799 end func;

1802const proc: execLines is forward;
1803
1804
1805const func string: exec_str_primary (inout string: symbol, inout string: line,
1806 inout string: variable_name) is func
1807 result
1808 var string: exprResult is "";
1809 local
1810 var string: unused_name is "";
1811 var string: stri1 is "";
1812 var string: stri2 is "";
1813 var float: num1 is 0.0;
1814 var float: num2 is 0.0;
1815 var integer: index1 is 0;
1816 var integer: index2 is 0;
1817 var file: aFile is STD_NULL;
1818 var char: current_key is ' ';
1819 var string: func_name is "";
1820 begin
1821 variable_name := "";
1822 case symbol of
1823 when {""}:
1824 error_marker;
1825 writeln(err, "EXPRESSION EXPECTED - FOUND END OF LINE.");
1826 when {"CHR$"}:
1827 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1828 expect("(", symbol, line);
1829 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
1830 expect(")", symbol, line);
1831 exprResult := str(chr(round(num1)));
1832 writeln(log, "CHR$(" <& num1 <& ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
1833 when {"COMMAND$"}:
1834 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1835 exprResult := command_line;
1836 writeln(log, "COMMAND$ -> " <& literal(exprResult));
1837 when {"DATE$"}:
1838 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1839 exprResult := str_mm_dd_yyyy(time(NOW), "-");
1840 writeln(log, "DATE$ -> " <& literal(exprResult));
1841 when {"HEX$"}:
1842 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1843 expect("(", symbol, line);
1844 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
1845 expect(")", symbol, line);
1846 exprResult := round(num1) RADIX 16;
1847 writeln(log, "HEX$(" <& num1 <& ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
1848 when {"INKEY$"}:
1849 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1850 write(log, "INKEY$ ");
1851 flush(log);
1852 flush(win);
1853 if inputReady(KEYBOARD) then
1854 current_key := getc(KEYBOARD);
1855 exprResult := extendedKeyCode(current_key);
1856 else
1857 exprResult := "";
1858 end if;
1859 write(log, "-> " <& literal(exprResult));
1860 if exprResult <> "" and current_key in keyDescription then
1861 write(log, " (" <& keyDescription[current_key] <& ")");
1862 end if;
1863 writeln(log);
1864 when {"INPUT$"}:
1865 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1866 expect("(", symbol, line);
1867 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
1868 if index1 >= 0 then
1869 if symbol = "," then
1870 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1871 if symbol = "#" then
1872 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1873 end if;
1874 index2 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
1875 expect(")", symbol, line);
1876 aFile := getFileValue(index2);
1877 if aFile <> STD_NULL then
1878 write(log, "INPUT$(" <& index1 <& ", #" <& index2 <& ") ");
1879 flush(log);
1880 exprResult := gets(aFile, index1);
1881 writeln(log, "-> " <& literal(exprResult));
1882 else
1883 error_marker;
1884 writeln(err, "FILE #" <& index2 <& " NOT OPEN IN INPUT$.");
1885 end if;
1886 else
1887 expect(")", symbol, line);
1888 write(log, "INPUT$(" <& index1 <& ") ");
1889 flush(log);
1890 flush(win);
1891 exprResult := gets(KEYBOARD, index1);
1892 writeln(log, "-> " <& literal(exprResult));
1893 end if;
1894 else
1895 error_marker;
1896 writeln(err, "INPUT$ WITH NEGATIVE NUMBER " <& index1 <& ".");
1897 while symbol <> ")" do
1898 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1899 end while;
1900 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1901 end if;
1902 when {"LCASE$"}:
1903 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1904 expect("(", symbol, line);
1905 stri1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
1906 expect(")", symbol, line);
1907 exprResult := lower(stri1);
1908 writeln(log, "LCASE$(" <& literal(stri1) <& ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
1909 when {"LEFT$"}:
1910 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1911 expect("(", symbol, line);
1912 stri1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
1913 expect(",", symbol, line);
1914 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
1915 expect(")", symbol, line);
1916 exprResult := stri1[ .. round(num1)];
1917 writeln(log, "LEFT$(" <& literal(stri1) <& ", " <& num1 <&
1918 ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
1919 when {"LTRIM$"}:
1920 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1921 expect("(", symbol, line);
1922 stri1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
1923 expect(")", symbol, line);
1924 index1 := 1;
1925 while index1 <= length(stri1) and stri1[index1] = ' ' do
1926 incr(index1);
1927 end while;
1928 exprResult := stri1[index1 ..];
1929 writeln(log, "LTRIM$(" <& literal(stri1) <& ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
1930 when {"MID$"}:
1931 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1932 expect("(", symbol, line);
1933 stri1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
1934 expect(",", symbol, line);
1935 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
1936 if symbol = "," then
1937 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1938 num2 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
1939 expect(")", symbol, line);
1940 exprResult := stri1[round(num1) .. round(num1) + round(num2) - 1];
1941 write(log, "MID$(" <& literal(stri1) <& ", " <& num1 <& ", " <& num2);
1942 else
1943 expect(")", symbol, line);
1944 exprResult := stri1[round(num1) .. ];
1945 write(log, "MID$(" <& literal(stri1) <& ", " <& num1);
1946 end if;
1947 writeln(log, ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
1948 when {"MKD$"}:
1949 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1950 expect("(", symbol, line);
1951 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
1952 expect(")", symbol, line);
1953 exprResult := bytes(bin64(num1), LE, 8);
1954 writeln(log, "MKD$(" <& num1 <& ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
1955 when {"MKDMBF$"}:
1956 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1957 expect("(", symbol, line);
1958 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
1959 expect(")", symbol, line);
1960 block
1961 exprResult := bytes(float2MbfBits(num1, DOUBLE), LE, 8);
1962 writeln(log, "MKDMBF$(" <& num1 <& ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
1963 exception
1964 catch RANGE_ERROR:
1965 error_marker;
1966 writeln(err, "MKDMBF$(" <& num1 <& ") FAILED");
1967 end block
1968 when {"MKI$"}:
1969 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1970 expect("(", symbol, line);
1971 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
1972 expect(")", symbol, line);
1973 exprResult := str(chr(index1 mod 256)) &
1974 str(chr(index1 mdiv 256 mod 256));
1975 writeln(log, "MKI$(" <& index1 <& ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
1976 when {"MKL$"}:
1977 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1978 expect("(", symbol, line);
1979 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
1980 expect(")", symbol, line);
1981 exprResult := str(chr(index1 mod 256)) &
1982 str(chr(index1 mdiv 256 mod 256)) &
1983 str(chr(index1 mdiv 65536 mod 256)) &
1984 str(chr(index1 mdiv 16777216 mod 256));
1985 writeln(log, "MKL$(" <& index1 <& ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
1986 when {"MKS$"}:
1987 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1988 expect("(", symbol, line);
1989 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
1990 expect(")", symbol, line);
1991 exprResult := bytes(bin32(num1), LE, 4);
1992 writeln(log, "MKS$(" <& num1 <& ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
1993 when {"MKSMBF$"}:
1994 symbol := get_symbol(line);
1995 expect("(", symbol, line);
1996 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
1997 expect(")", symbol, line);
1998 block
1999 exprResult := bytes(float2MbfBits(num1, SINGLE), LE, 4);
2000 writeln(log, "MKSMBF$(" <& num1 <& ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
2001 exception
2002 catch RANGE_ERROR:
2003 error_marker;
2004 writeln(err, "MKSMBF$(" <& num1 <& ") FAILED");
2005 end block
2006 when {"OCT$"}:
2007 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2008 expect("(", symbol, line);
2009 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2010 expect(")", symbol, line);
2011 exprResult := round(num1) RADIX 8;
2012 writeln(log, "OCT$(" <& num1 <& ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
2013 when {"RIGHT$"}:
2014 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2015 expect("(", symbol, line);
2016 stri1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
2017 expect(",", symbol, line);
2018 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2019 expect(")", symbol, line);
2020 exprResult := stri1[length(stri1) - round(num1) + 1 .. ];
2021 writeln(log, "RIGHT$(" <& literal(stri1) <& ", " <& num1 <&
2022 ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
2023 when {"RPT$"}:
2024 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2025 expect("(", symbol, line);
2026 stri1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
2027 expect(",", symbol, line);
2028 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2029 expect(")", symbol, line);
2030 index1 := round(num1);
2031 if index1 >= 0 then
2032 exprResult := stri1 mult index1;
2033 writeln(log, "RPT$(" <& literal(stri1) <& ", " <& num1 <&
2034 ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
2035 else
2036 error_marker;
2037 writeln(err, "RPT$(" <& literal(stri1) <& ", " <& num1 <&
2038 ") - REPEAT COUNT NEGATIVE");
2039 end if;
2040 when {"RTRIM$"}:
2041 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2042 expect("(", symbol, line);
2043 stri1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
2044 expect(")", symbol, line);
2045 index1 := length(stri1);
2046 while index1 >= 1 and stri1[index1] = ' ' do
2047 decr(index1);
2048 end while;
2049 exprResult := stri1[.. index1];
2050 writeln(log, "RTRIM$(" <& literal(stri1) <& ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
2051 when {"SEG$"}:
2052 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2053 expect("(", symbol, line);
2054 stri1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
2055 expect(",", symbol, line);
2056 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2057 expect(",", symbol, line);
2058 num2 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2059 expect(")", symbol, line);
2060 exprResult := stri1[round(num1) len round(num2)];
2061 write(log, "SEG$(" <& literal(stri1) <& ", " <& num1 <& ", " <& num2);
2062 writeln(log, ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
2063 when {"SPACE$"}:
2064 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2065 expect("(", symbol, line);
2066 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2067 expect(")", symbol, line);
2068 index1 := round(num1);
2069 if index1 >= 0 then
2070 exprResult := " " mult index1;
2071 writeln(log, "SPACE$(" <& num1 <& ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
2072 else
2073 error_marker;
2074 writeln(err, "REPEAT COUNT " <& num1 <& " NEGATIVE IN SPACE$.");
2075 end if;
2076 when {"STR$"}:
2077 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2078 expect("(", symbol, line);
2079 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2080 expect(")", symbol, line);
2081 exprResult := str(round(num1));
2082 if exprResult[1] <> '-' then
2083 exprResult := " " & exprResult;
2084 end if;
2085 if exprResult[length(exprResult) - 1 .. ] = ".0" then
2086 exprResult := exprResult[ .. length(exprResult) - 2];
2087 end if;
2088 writeln(log, "STR$(" <& num1 <& ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
2089 when {"STRING$"}:
2090 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2091 expect("(", symbol, line);
2092 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2093 expect(",", symbol, line);
2094 index1 := round(num1);
2095 if index1 >= 0 then
2096 if isStringExpr(symbol) then
2097 stri1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
2098 exprResult := stri1 mult index1;
2099 writeln(log, "STRING$(" <& num1 <& ", " <& literal(stri1) <&
2100 ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
2101 else
2102 num2 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2103 exprResult := str(chr(round(num2))) mult index1;
2104 writeln(log, "STRING$(" <& num1 <& ", " <& num2 <&
2105 ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
2106 end if;
2107 expect(")", symbol, line);
2108 else
2109 error_marker;
2110 writeln(err, "REPEAT COUNT " <& num1 <& " NEGATIVE IN STRING$.");
2111 while symbol <> ")" do
2112 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2113 end while;
2114 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2115 end if;
2116 when {"TIME$"}:
2117 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2118 exprResult := strTime(truncToSecond(time(NOW)));
2119 writeln(log, "TIME$ -> " <& literal(exprResult));
2120 when {"UCASE$"}:
2121 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2122 expect("(", symbol, line);
2123 stri1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
2124 expect(")", symbol, line);
2125 exprResult := upper(stri1);
2126 writeln(log, "UCASE$(" <& literal(stri1) <& ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
2127 when {"VARPTR$"}:
2128 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2129 expect("(", symbol, line);
2130 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
2131 expect(")", symbol, line);
2132 exprResult := varptrStri(variable_name);
2133 writeln(log, "VARPTR$(" <& variable_name <& ") -> " <& literal(exprResult));
2134 otherwise:
2135 if symbol[1] = '"' then
2136 exprResult := symbol[2 .. ];
2137 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2138 elsif symbol[1] >= 'A' and symbol[1] <= 'Z' then
2139 if symbol in def_fn_list then
2140 func_name := symbol;
2141 exprResult := exec_str_function(def_fn_list[func_name], symbol, line);
2142 writeln(log, "function " <& func_name <& " is " <& literal(exprResult));
2143 elsif symbol in subfunction then
2144 func_name := symbol;
2145 line_marker;
2146 writeln(log, "**CALL FUNCTION " <& symbol);
2147 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2148 if symbol = "(" then
2149 repeat
2150 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2151 until symbol = ")";
2152 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2153 end if;
2154 set_return_position(line);
2155 gosubReturn[1].subName := func_name;
2156 file_line_number := subfunction[func_name];
2157 line_marker;
2158 writeln(log, "EXECUTE FUNCTION " <& func_name);
2159 incr(file_line_number);
2160 execLines;
2161 file_line_number := gosubReturn[1].returnLine;
2162 gosubReturn := gosubReturn[2 .. ];
2163 exprResult := getStringVar(func_name);
2164 line_marker;
2165 writeln(log, "RETURN FROM FUNCTION " <& func_name <& " -> " <& literal(exprResult));
2166 else
2167 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
2168 exprResult := getStringVar(variable_name);
2169 writeln(log, variable_name <& " is " <& literal(exprResult));
2170 end if;
2171 else
2172 error_marker;
2173 writeln(err, "UNEXPECTED SYMBOL " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
2174 end if;
2175 end case;
2176 end func;

2179const func string: exec_str_mult (inout string: symbol, inout string: line,
2180 inout string: variable_name) is func
2181 result
2182 var string: exprResult is "";
2183 local
2184 var float: num1 is 0.0;
2185 var integer: factor is 0;
2186 begin
2187 exprResult := exec_str_primary(symbol, line, variable_name);
2188 while symbol = "*" do
2189 variable_name := "";
2190 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2191 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2192 factor := round(num1);
2193 if factor >= 0 then
2194 exprResult := exprResult mult factor;
2195 else
2196 error_marker;
2197 writeln(err, "REPEAT COUNT " <& num1 <&
2198 " NEGATIVE IN STRING MULTIPLICATION.");
2199 end if;
2200 end while;
2201 end func;

2204const func string: exec_str_expr (inout string: symbol, inout string: line,
2205 inout string: variable_name) is func
2206 result
2207 var string: exprResult is "";
2208 local
2209 var string: unused_name is "";
2210 var string: stri is "";
2211 begin
2212 exprResult := exec_str_mult(symbol, line, variable_name);
2213 while symbol = "+" or symbol = "&" do
2214 variable_name := "";
2215 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2216 stri := exec_str_mult(symbol, line, unused_name);
2217 exprResult &:= stri;
2218 end while;
2219 end func;

2222const func float: exec_function (in defFnType: defFn, inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
2223 result
2224 var float: exprResult is 0.0;
2225 local
2226 var string: func_expr is "";
2227 var string: func_symbol is "";
2228 var string: formal_params is "";
2229 var string: formal_param is "";
2230 var string: unused_name is "";
2231 var array string: str_value_backup is 0 times "";
2232 var array float: num_value_backup is 0 times 0.0;
2233 begin
2234 write(log, "function " <& defFn.name);
2235 formal_params := defFn.params;
2236 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2237 if symbol = "(" then
2238 write(log, "(");
2239 repeat
2240 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2241 formal_param := get_symbol(formal_params);
2242 if formal_param[length(formal_param)] = '$' then
2243 if formal_param in string_var then
2244 str_value_backup &:= [] (string_var[formal_param]);
2245 else
2246 str_value_backup &:= [] ("");
2247 end if;
2248 string_var @:= [formal_param] exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
2249 write(log, string_var[formal_param]);
2250 else
2251 if formal_param in numeric_var then
2252 num_value_backup &:= [] (numeric_var[formal_param]);
2253 else
2254 num_value_backup &:= [] (0.0);
2255 end if;
2256 numeric_var @:= [formal_param] exec_expr(symbol, line);
2257 write(log, numeric_var[formal_param]);
2258 end if;
2259 write(log, symbol);
2260 until symbol <> ",";
2261 expect(")", symbol, line);
2262 end if;
2263 func_expr := defFn.expression;
2264 writeln(log, " = " <& func_expr);
2265 func_symbol := get_symbol(func_expr);
2266 exprResult := exec_expr(func_symbol, func_expr);
2267 formal_params := defFn.params;
2268 formal_param := get_symbol(formal_params);
2269 while formal_param <> "" do
2270 if formal_param[length(formal_param)] = '$' then
2271 string_var @:= [formal_param] str_value_backup[1];
2272 str_value_backup := str_value_backup[2 ..];
2273 else
2274 numeric_var @:= [formal_param] num_value_backup[1];
2275 num_value_backup := num_value_backup[2 ..];
2276 end if;
2277 formal_param := get_symbol(formal_params);
2278 end while;
2279 end func;
