2282const func float: exec_primary (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
2283 result
2284 var float: exprResult is 0.0;
2285 local
2286 var string: variable_name is "";
2287 var string: unused_name is "";
2288 var string: stri1 is "";
2289 var string: stri2 is "";
2290 var float: num1 is 0.0;
2291 var integer: index1 is 0;
2292 var integer: index2 is 0;
2293 var char: current_key is ' ';
2294 var time: time_now is time.value;
2295 var duration: since_midnight is duration.value;
2296 var string: func_name is "";
2297 var file: aFile is STD_NULL;
2298 begin
2299 case symbol of
2300 when {""}:
2301 error_marker;
2302 writeln(err, "EXPRESSION EXPECTED - FOUND END OF LINE.");
2303 when {"ABS"}:
2304 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2305 expect("(", symbol, line);
2306 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2307 expect(")", symbol, line);
2308 exprResult := abs(num1);
2309 writeln(log, "ABS(" <& num1 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2310 when {"ASC"}:
2311 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2312 expect("(", symbol, line);
2313 stri1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
2314 expect(")", symbol, line);
2315 if stri1 <> "" then
2316 exprResult := flt(ord(stri1[1]));
2317 writeln(log, "ASC(" <& literal(stri1) <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2318 else
2319 error_marker;
2320 writeln(err, "ASC(\"\") - ILLEGAL FUNCTION CALL");
2321 end if;
2322 when {"ATN"}:
2323 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2324 expect("(", symbol, line);
2325 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2326 expect(")", symbol, line);
2327 exprResult := atan(num1);
2328 writeln(log, "ATN(" <& num1 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2329 when {"CDBL"}:
2330 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2331 expect("(", symbol, line);
2332 exprResult := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2333 expect(")", symbol, line);
2334 writeln(log, "CDBL(" <& exprResult <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2335 when {"CINT"}:
2336 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2337 expect("(", symbol, line);
2338 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2339 expect(")", symbol, line);
2340 exprResult := flt(round(num1));
2341 writeln(log, "CINT(" <& num1 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2342 when {"CLNG"}:
2343 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2344 expect("(", symbol, line);
2345 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2346 expect(")", symbol, line);
2347 exprResult := flt(round(num1));
2348 writeln(log, "CLNG(" <& num1 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2349 when {"COS"}:
2350 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2351 expect("(", symbol, line);
2352 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2353 expect(")", symbol, line);
2354 exprResult := cos(num1);
2355 writeln(log, "COS(" <& num1 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2356 when {"CSNG"}:
2357 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2358 expect("(", symbol, line);
2359 exprResult := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2360 expect(")", symbol, line);
2361 writeln(log, "CSNG(" <& exprResult <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2362 when {"CSRLIN"}:
2363 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2364 exprResult := flt(line(win));
2365 writeln(log, "CSRLIN -> " <& exprResult);
2366 when {"CVD"}:
2367 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2368 expect("(", symbol, line);
2369 stri1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
2370 expect(")", symbol, line);
2371 if length(stri1) >= 8 then
2372 exprResult := float(bin64(stri1[.. 8], LE));
2373 writeln(log, "CVD(" <& literal(stri1) <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2374 else
2375 error_marker;
2376 writeln(err, "CVD(" <& literal(stri1) <& ") IS ILLEGAL.");
2377 exprResult := 0.0;
2378 end if;
2379 when {"CVDMBF"}:
2380 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2381 expect("(", symbol, line);
2382 stri1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
2383 expect(")", symbol, line);
2384 if length(stri1) >= 8 then
2385 exprResult := mbfBits2Float(bin64(stri1[.. 8], LE));
2386 writeln(log, "CVDMBF(" <& literal(stri1) <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2387 else
2388 error_marker;
2389 writeln(err, "CVDMBF(" <& literal(stri1) <& ") IS ILLEGAL.");
2390 exprResult := 0.0;
2391 end if;
2392 when {"CVI"}:
2393 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2394 expect("(", symbol, line);
2395 stri1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
2396 expect(")", symbol, line);
2397 if length(stri1) >= 2 then
2398 if ord(stri1[2]) >= 128 then
2399 exprResult := flt((ord(stri1[2]) - 256) * 256 + ord(stri1[1]));
2400 else
2401 exprResult := flt(ord(stri1[2]) * 256 + ord(stri1[1]));
2402 end if;
2403 writeln(log, "CVI(" <& literal(stri1) <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2404 else
2405 error_marker;
2406 writeln(err, "CVI(" <& literal(stri1) <& ") IS ILLEGAL.");
2407 exprResult := 0.0;
2408 end if;
2409 when {"CVL"}:
2410 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2411 expect("(", symbol, line);
2412 stri1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
2413 expect(")", symbol, line);
2414 if length(stri1) >= 4 then
2415 if ord(stri1[4]) >= 128 then
2416 exprResult := flt((((ord(stri1[4]) - 256) * 256 + ord(stri1[3])) * 256 +
2417 ord(stri1[2])) * 256 + ord(stri1[1]));
2418 else
2419 exprResult := flt(((ord(stri1[4]) * 256 + ord(stri1[3])) * 256 +
2420 ord(stri1[2])) * 256 + ord(stri1[1]));
2421 end if;
2422 writeln(log, "CVL(" <& literal(stri1) <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2423 else
2424 error_marker;
2425 writeln(err, "CVL(" <& literal(stri1) <& ") IS ILLEGAL.");
2426 exprResult := 0.0;
2427 end if;
2428 when {"CVS"}:
2429 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2430 expect("(", symbol, line);
2431 stri1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
2432 expect(")", symbol, line);
2433 if length(stri1) >= 4 then
2434 exprResult := float(bin32(stri1[.. 4], LE));
2435 writeln(log, "CVS(" <& literal(stri1) <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2436 else
2437 error_marker;
2438 writeln(err, "CVS(" <& literal(stri1) <& ") IS ILLEGAL.");
2439 exprResult := 0.0;
2440 end if;
2441 when {"CVSMBF"}:
2442 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2443 expect("(", symbol, line);
2444 stri1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
2445 expect(")", symbol, line);
2446 if length(stri1) >= 4 then
2447 exprResult := mbfBits2Float(bin32(stri1[.. 4], LE));
2448 writeln(log, "CVSMBF(" <& literal(stri1) <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2449 else
2450 error_marker;
2451 writeln(err, "CVSMBF(" <& literal(stri1) <& ") IS ILLEGAL.");
2452 exprResult := 0.0;
2453 end if;
2454 when {"EOF"}:
2455 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2456 expect("(", symbol, line);
2457 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
2458 expect(")", symbol, line);
2459 aFile := getFileValue(index1);
2460 if aFile <> STD_NULL then
2461 if hasNext(aFile) then
2462 exprResult := 0.0;
2463 else
2464 exprResult := -1.0;
2465 end if;
2466 writeln(log, "EOF(" <& index1 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2467 else
2468 error_marker;
2469 writeln(err, "FILE #" <& index1 <& " NOT OPEN IN EOF.");
2470 exprResult := -1.0;
2471 end if;
2472 when {"ERL"}:
2473 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2474 if error_linenum <> "" and error_linenum[1] in digit_char then
2475 exprResult := flt(integer(error_linenum));
2476 else
2477 exprResult := 0.0;
2478 end if;
2479 writeln(log, "ERL -> " <& exprResult);
2480 when {"ERR"}:
2481 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2482 exprResult := flt(error_code);
2483 writeln(log, "ERR -> " <& exprResult);
2484 when {"EXP"}:
2485 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2486 expect("(", symbol, line);
2487 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2488 expect(")", symbol, line);
2489 exprResult := exp(num1);
2490 writeln(log, "EXP(" <& num1 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2491 when {"FIX"}:
2492 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2493 expect("(", symbol, line);
2494 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2495 expect(")", symbol, line);
2496 exprResult := flt(trunc(num1));
2497 writeln(log, "FIX(" <& num1 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2498 when {"FN"}:
2499 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
2500 if variable_name <> "FN" or ("FN" & symbol) not in def_fn_list then
2501 exprResult := getNumericVar(variable_name);
2502 writeln(log, variable_name <& " is " <& exprResult);
2503 else
2504 func_name := "FN" & symbol;
2505 exprResult := exec_function(def_fn_list[func_name], symbol, line);
2506 writeln(log, "function " <& func_name <& " is " <& exprResult);
2507 end if;
2508 when {"FRE"}:
2509 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2510 expect("(", symbol, line);
2511 if isStringExpr(symbol) then
2512 stri1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
2513 else
2514 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2515 end if;
2516 expect(")", symbol, line);
2517 exprResult := 32767.0;
2518 writeln(log, "FRE -> " <& exprResult);
2519 when {"FREEFILE"}:
2520 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2521 index1 := 1;
2522 while getFileValue(index1) <> STD_NULL do
2523 incr(index1);
2524 end while;
2525 exprResult := flt(index1);
2526 writeln(log, "FREEFILE -> " <& exprResult);
2527 when {"INP"}:
2528 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2529 expect("(", symbol, line);
2530 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
2531 expect(")", symbol, line);
2532 case index1 of
2533 when {16#60}: # &H60/96 Get keyboard scan code
2534 if inputReady(KEYBOARD) then
2535 exprResult := flt(keyboardScanCode(getc(KEYBOARD)));
2536 else
2537 exprResult := 128.0; # This is a key release code
2538 end if;
2539 when {16#3DA}: # &H3DA/986 Indicate vertical retrace
2540 exprResult := flt(rand(0, 1) * 8);
2541 otherwise:
2542 exprResult := 0.0;
2543 end case;
2544 writeln(log, "**INP(" <& index1 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2545 when {"INSTR"}:
2546 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2547 expect("(", symbol, line);
2548 if isStringExpr(symbol) then
2549 index1 := 1;
2550 else
2551 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
2552 expect(",", symbol, line);
2553 end if;
2554 stri1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
2555 expect(",", symbol, line);
2556 stri2 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
2557 expect(")", symbol, line);
2558 if index1 >= 1 then
2559 exprResult := flt(pos(stri1, stri2, index1));
2560 write(log, "INSTR(");
2561 if index1 <> 1 then
2562 write(log, index1 <& ", ");
2563 end if;
2564 writeln(log, literal(stri1) <& ", " <& literal(stri2) <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2565 else
2566 error_marker;
2567 writeln(err, "INSTR(" <& index1 <& ", " <& literal(stri1) <& ", " <&
2568 literal(stri2) <& ") - ILLEGAL FUNCTION CALL");
2569 end if;
2570 when {"INT"}:
2571 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2572 expect("(", symbol, line);
2573 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2574 expect(")", symbol, line);
2575 exprResult := floor(num1);
2576 writeln(log, "INT(" <& num1 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2577 when {"LBOUND"}:
2578 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2579 expect("(", symbol, line);
2580 variable_name := symbol;
2581 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2582 if symbol = "," then
2583 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2584 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
2585 else
2586 index1 := 1;
2587 end if;
2588 expect(")", symbol, line);
2589 exprResult := flt(exec_lbound(variable_name, index1));
2590 writeln(log, "LBOUND(" <& variable_name <& ", " <& index1 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2591 when {"LEN"}:
2592 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2593 expect("(", symbol, line);
2594 stri1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
2595 expect(")", symbol, line);
2596 exprResult := flt(length(stri1));
2597 writeln(log, "LEN(" <& literal(stri1) <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2598 when {"LOF"}:
2599 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2600 expect("(", symbol, line);
2601 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
2602 expect(")", symbol, line);
2603 aFile := getFileValue(index1);
2604 if aFile <> STD_NULL then
2605 exprResult := flt(length(aFile));
2606 writeln(log, "LOF(" <& index1 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2607 else
2608 error_marker;
2609 writeln(err, "FILE #" <& index1 <& " NOT OPEN IN LOF.");
2610 end if;
2611 when {"LOG"}:
2612 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2613 expect("(", symbol, line);
2614 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2615 expect(")", symbol, line);
2616 if num1 > 0.0 then
2617 exprResult := log(num1);
2618 writeln(log, "LOG(" <& num1 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2619 else
2620 error_marker;
2621 writeln(err, "LOG(" <& num1 <& ") - ILLEGAL FUNCTION CALL");
2622 end if;
2623 when {"PEEK"}:
2624 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2625 expect("(", symbol, line);
2626 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
2627 expect(")", symbol, line);
2628 case index1 of
2629 when {16}: # Is it a bw or color screen?
2630 exprResult := 35.0;
2631 when {1040}: # Is it a bw or color screen?
2632 exprResult := 35.0;
2633 when {16#6c}: # &H6c contains the low order tick count of 0-255
2634 time_now := time(NOW);
2635 since_midnight := time_now - truncToDay(time_now);
2636 exprResult := 18.2 * (flt(toSeconds(since_midnight)) +
2637 flt(since_midnight.micro_second) / 1000000.0);
2638 exprResult -:= floor(exprResult / 256.0) * 256.0;
2639 index1 := round(exprResult);
2640 if index1 < 0 then
2641 exprResult := 0.0;
2642 elsif index1 > 255 then
2643 exprResult := 255.0;
2644 else
2645 exprResult := flt(index1);
2646 end if;
2647 when {49152, -16384}: # Read keyboard
2648 if inputReady(KEYBOARD) then
2649 current_key := getc(KEYBOARD);
2650 if current_key = KEY_NL then
2651 current_key := KEY_CR;
2652 elsif current_key >= '\128;' then
2653 current_key := '\0;';
2654 end if;
2655 # Return value >= 128 if a key has been pressed.
2656 exprResult := flt(ord(current_key) + 128);
2657 else
2658 exprResult := 0.0;
2659 end if;
2660 otherwise:
2661 exprResult := 0.0;
2662 end case;
2663 writeln(log, "**PEEK(" <& index1 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2664 when {"POINT"}:
2665 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2666 expect("(", symbol, line);
2667 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
2668 if symbol = "," then
2669 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2670 index2 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
2671 expect(")", symbol, line);
2672 exprResult := 0.0;
2673 writeln(log, "**POINT(" <& index1 <& ", " <& index2 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2674 else
2675 expect(")", symbol, line);
2676 exprResult := 0.0;
2677 writeln(log, "**POINT(" <& index1 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2678 end if;
2679 when {"POS"}:
2680 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2681 expect("(", symbol, line);
2682 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2683 expect(")", symbol, line);
2684 exprResult := flt(column(win));
2685 writeln(log, "POS -> " <& exprResult);
2686 when {"RND"}:
2687 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2688 if symbol = "(" then
2689 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2690 if symbol <> ")" then
2691 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2692 expect(")", symbol, line);
2693 if num1 <> 0.0 then
2694 lastRandomNumber := rand(0.0, 1.0);
2695 end if;
2696 else
2697 expect(")", symbol, line);
2698 lastRandomNumber := rand(0.0, 1.0);
2699 end if;
2700 else
2701 lastRandomNumber := rand(0.0, 1.0);
2702 end if;
2703 exprResult := lastRandomNumber;
2704 writeln(log, "RND -> " <& exprResult);
2705 when {"SCREEN"}:
2706 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2707 expect("(", symbol, line);
2708 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
2709 expect(",", symbol, line);
2710 index2 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
2711 if symbol = "," then
2712 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2713 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2714 end if;
2715 expect(")", symbol, line);
2716 exprResult := 32.0;
2717 writeln(log, "**SCREEN(" <& index1 <& ", " <& index2 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2718 when {"SGN"}:
2719 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2720 expect("(", symbol, line);
2721 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2722 expect(")", symbol, line);
2723 if num1 > 0.0 then
2724 exprResult := 1.0;
2725 elsif num1 = 0.0 then
2726 exprResult := 0.0;
2727 else
2728 exprResult := -1.0;
2729 end if;
2730 writeln(log, "SGN(" <& num1 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2731 when {"SIN"}:
2732 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2733 expect("(", symbol, line);
2734 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2735 expect(")", symbol, line);
2736 exprResult := sin(num1);
2737 writeln(log, "SIN(" <& num1 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2738 when {"SQR"}:
2739 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2740 expect("(", symbol, line);
2741 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2742 expect(")", symbol, line);
2743 if num1 >= 0.0 then
2744 exprResult := sqrt(num1);
2745 writeln(log, "SQR(" <& num1 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2746 else
2747 error_marker;
2748 writeln(err, "SQR(" <& num1 <& ") - ILLEGAL FUNCTION CALL");
2749 end if;
2750 when {"STRIG"}:
2751 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2752 expect("(", symbol, line);
2753 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
2754 expect(")", symbol, line);
2755 exprResult := 0.0;
2756 current_key := getc(KEYBOARD, NO_WAIT);
2757 case index1 of
2758 when {0, 1}:
2759 if current_key = KEY_MOUSE1 then
2760 current_key := getc(KEYBOARD);
2761 exprResult := -1.0;
2762 end if;
2763 when {4, 5}:
2764 if current_key = KEY_MOUSE3 then
2765 current_key := getc(KEYBOARD);
2766 exprResult := -1.0;
2767 end if;
2768 end case;
2769 writeln(log, "**STRIG(" <& index1 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2770 when {"TAN"}:
2771 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2772 expect("(", symbol, line);
2773 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2774 expect(")", symbol, line);
2775 exprResult := tan(num1);
2776 writeln(log, "TAN(" <& num1 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2777 when {"TIMER"}:
2778 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2779 time_now := time(NOW);
2780 since_midnight := time_now - truncToDay(time_now);
2781 exprResult := flt(toSeconds(since_midnight)) +
2782 flt(since_midnight.micro_second) / 1000000.0;
2783 writeln(log, "TIMER -> " <& exprResult);
2784 when {"UBOUND"}:
2785 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2786 expect("(", symbol, line);
2787 variable_name := symbol;
2788 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2789 if symbol = "," then
2790 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2791 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
2792 else
2793 index1 := 1;
2794 end if;
2795 expect(")", symbol, line);
2796 exprResult := flt(exec_ubound(variable_name, index1));
2797 writeln(log, "UBOUND(" <& variable_name <& ", " <& index1 <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2798 when {"VAL"}:
2799 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2800 expect("(", symbol, line);
2801 stri1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
2802 expect(")", symbol, line);
2803 stri2 := get_symbol(stri1);
2804 if stri2 = "-" then
2805 stri2 &:= get_symbol(stri1);
2806 elsif stri2 = "+" then
2807 stri2 := get_symbol(stri1);
2808 end if;
2809 block
2810 exprResult := float(stri2);
2811 exception
2812 catch RANGE_ERROR:
2813 exprResult := 0.0;
2814 end block;
2815 writeln(log, "VAL(" <& literal(stri2) <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2816 when {"VARPTR"}:
2817 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2818 expect("(", symbol, line);
2819 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
2820 expect(")", symbol, line);
2821 exprResult := flt(varptr(variable_name));
2822 writeln(log, "VARPTR(" <& variable_name <& ") -> " <& exprResult);
2823 when {"("}:
2824 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2825 exprResult := exec_expr(symbol, line);
2826 expect(")", symbol, line);
2827 when {"%"}:
2828 variable_name := "";
2829 repeat
2830 variable_name &:= symbol;
2831 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2832 if symbol <> "" and symbol[1] in alphanum_char then
2833 variable_name &:= symbol;
2834 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2835 end if;
2836 until symbol <> "_";
2837 append_index(variable_name, symbol, line);
2838 exprResult := getNumericVar(variable_name);
2839 writeln(log, variable_name <& " is " <& exprResult);
2840 otherwise:
2841 if symbol[1] in digit_char then
2842 if symbol[length(symbol)] in number_suffix then
2843 symbol := symbol[.. pred(length(symbol))];
2844 end if;
2845 block
2846 exprResult := float(symbol);
2847 exception
2848 catch RANGE_ERROR:
2849 error_marker;
2850 writeln(err, "ERROR IN PARSE NUMBER " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
2851 end block;
2852 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2853 elsif symbol[1] >= 'A' and symbol[1] <= 'Z' then
2854 if symbol in def_fn_list then
2855 func_name := symbol;
2856 exprResult := exec_function(def_fn_list[func_name], symbol, line);
2857 writeln(log, "function " <& func_name <& " is " <& exprResult);
2858 elsif symbol in subfunction then
2859 func_name := symbol;
2860 line_marker;
2861 writeln(log, "**CALL FUNCTION " <& symbol);
2862 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2863 if symbol = "(" then
2864 repeat
2865 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2866 until symbol = ")";
2867 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2868 end if;
2869 set_return_position(line);
2870 gosubReturn[1].subName := func_name;
2871 file_line_number := subfunction[func_name];
2872 line_marker;
2873 writeln(log, "EXECUTE FUNCTION " <& func_name);
2874 incr(file_line_number);
2875 execLines;
2876 file_line_number := gosubReturn[1].returnLine;
2877 gosubReturn := gosubReturn[2 .. ];
2878 exprResult := getNumericVar(func_name);
2879 line_marker;
2880 writeln(log, "RETURN FROM FUNCTION " <& func_name <& " -> " <& exprResult);
2881 else
2882 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
2883 exprResult := getNumericVar(variable_name);
2884 writeln(log, variable_name <& " is " <& exprResult);
2885 end if;
2886 else
2887 error_marker;
2888 writeln(err, "UNEXPECTED SYMBOL " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
2889 end if;
2890 end case;
2891 end func;

2894const func float: exec_exponentation (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
2895 result
2896 var float: exprResult is 0.0;
2897 local
2898 var float: num is 0.0;
2899 begin
2900 exprResult := exec_primary(symbol, line);
2901 if symbol = "^" then
2902 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2903 num := exec_primary(symbol, line);
2904 if flt(round(num)) = num then
2905 exprResult := exprResult ** round(num);
2906 else
2907 exprResult := exprResult ** num;
2908 end if;
2909 end if;
2910 end func;
2911
2912
2913const func float: exec_negation (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
2914 result
2915 var float: exprResult is 0.0;
2916 begin
2917 if symbol = "-" then
2918 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2919 exprResult := -exec_exponentation(symbol, line);
2920 elsif symbol = "+" then
2921 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2922 exprResult := exec_exponentation(symbol, line);
2923 else
2924 exprResult := exec_exponentation(symbol, line);
2925 end if;
2926 end func;

2928
2929const func float: exec_multdiv (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
2930 result
2931 var float: exprResult is 0.0;
2932 local
2933 var string: op is "";
2934 var float: num1 is 0.0;
2935 var float: num2 is 0.0;
2936 begin
2937 exprResult := exec_negation(symbol, line);
2938 while symbol = "*" or symbol = "/" or symbol = "\\" or symbol = "MOD" do
2939 op := symbol;
2940 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2941 num1 := exprResult;
2942 num2 := exec_negation(symbol, line);
2943 if op = "*" then
2944 exprResult := num1 * num2;
2945 else
2946 block
2947 if op = "/" then
2948 exprResult := num1 / num2;
2949 if abs(exprResult) = Infinity or isNaN(exprResult) then
2950 raise NUMERIC_ERROR;
2951 end if;
2952 elsif op = "\\" then
2953 exprResult := flt(round(num1) div round(num2));
2954 elsif op = "MOD" then
2955 exprResult := flt(round(num1) rem round(num2));
2956 end if;
2957 exception
2958 catch NUMERIC_ERROR:
2959 if on_error_label <> "" then
2960 error_code := 11; # Division by zero
2961 writeln(log);
2962 line_marker;
2963 writeln(log, error_code <& " DIVISION BY ZERO (" <&
2964 num1 <& " " <& op <& " " <& num2 <& ")" <&
2965 " - ON ERROR GOTO " <& on_error_label);
2966 goto_on_error(on_error_label, line);
2967 symbol := "";
2968 line := "";
2969 else
2970 error_marker;
2971 writeln(err, "DIVISION BY ZERO (" <&
2972 num1 <& " " <& op <& " " <& num2 <& ")");
2973 end if;
2974 if num1 >= 0.0 then
2975 exprResult := Infinity;
2976 else
2977 exprResult := -Infinity;
2978 end if;
2979 end block;
2980 end if;
2981 end while;
2982 end func;
2983

2985const func float: exec_addsub (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
2986 result
2987 var float: exprResult is 0.0;
2988 local
2989 var string: op is "";
2990 var float: num is 0.0;
2991 begin
2992 exprResult := exec_multdiv(symbol, line);
2993 while symbol = "+" or symbol = "-" do
2994 op := symbol;
2995 symbol := get_symbol(line);
2996 num := exec_multdiv(symbol, line);
2997 if op = "+" then
2998 exprResult := exprResult + num;
2999 elsif op = "-" then
3000 exprResult := exprResult - num;
3001 end if;
3002 end while;
3003 end func;

3006const func float: exec_comparison (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
3007 result
3008 var float: exprResult is 0.0;
3009 local
3010 var string: unused_name is "";
3011 var string: op is "";
3012 var string: stri1 is "";
3013 var string: stri2 is "";
3014 var float: num is 0.0;
3015 begin
3016 if isStringExpr(symbol) and symbol not in numeric_functions then
3017 stri1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
3018 if symbol = "=" or symbol = "<>" or
3019 symbol = "<" or symbol = ">" or
3020 symbol = "<=" or symbol = ">=" then
3021 op := symbol;
3022 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3023 stri2 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
3024 if op = "=" then
3025 exprResult := flt(-ord(stri1 = stri2));
3026 elsif op = "<>" then
3027 exprResult := flt(-ord(stri1 <> stri2));
3028 elsif op = "<" then
3029 exprResult := flt(-ord(stri1 < stri2));
3030 elsif op = ">" then
3031 exprResult := flt(-ord(stri1 > stri2));
3032 elsif op = "<=" then
3033 exprResult := flt(-ord(stri1 <= stri2));
3034 elsif op = ">=" then
3035 exprResult := flt(-ord(stri1 >= stri2));
3036 end if;
3037 else
3038 error_marker;
3039 writeln(err, "COMPARISON EXPECTED - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
3040 end if;
3041 else
3042 exprResult := exec_addsub(symbol, line);
3043 if symbol = "=" or symbol = "<>" or
3044 symbol = "<" or symbol = ">" or
3045 symbol = "<=" or symbol = ">=" then
3046 op := symbol;
3047 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3048 num := exec_addsub(symbol, line);
3049 if op = "=" then
3050 exprResult := flt(-ord(exprResult = num));
3051 elsif op = "<>" then
3052 exprResult := flt(-ord(exprResult <> num));
3053 elsif op = "<" then
3054 exprResult := flt(-ord(exprResult < num));
3055 elsif op = ">" then
3056 exprResult := flt(-ord(exprResult > num));
3057 elsif op = "<=" then
3058 exprResult := flt(-ord(exprResult <= num));
3059 elsif op = ">=" then
3060 exprResult := flt(-ord(exprResult >= num));
3061 end if;
3062 end if;
3063 end if;
3064 end func;
3065

3067const func float: exec_cond_not (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
3068 result
3069 var float: exprResult is 0.0;
3070 local
3071 var float: num is 0.0;
3072 begin
3073 if symbol = "NOT" then
3074 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3075 num := exec_comparison(symbol, line);
3076 exprResult := flt(-ord(num = 0.0));
3077 else
3078 exprResult := exec_comparison(symbol, line);
3079 end if;
3080 end func;

3083const func integer: binary_and (in var integer: number1, in var integer: number2) is func
3084 result
3085 var integer: exprResult is 0;
3086 local
3087 var integer: count is 0;
3088 begin
3089 for count range 0 to 15 do
3090 if odd(number1) and odd(number2) then
3091 exprResult +:= 2 ** count;
3092 end if;
3093 number1 := number1 div 2;
3094 number2 := number2 div 2;
3095 end for;
3096 end func;
3097
3098
3099const func float: exec_cond_and (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
3100 result
3101 var float: exprResult is 0.0;
3102 local
3103 var integer: number1 is 0;
3104 var integer: number2 is 0;
3105 begin
3106 exprResult := exec_cond_not(symbol, line);
3107 if startsWith(symbol, "AND") then
3108 line := symbol[4 ..] & line;
3109 symbol := "AND";
3110 end if;
3111 while symbol = "AND" do
3112 number1 := round(exprResult);
3113 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3114 number2 := round(exec_cond_not(symbol, line));
3115 exprResult := flt(binary_and(number1, number2));
3116 if startsWith(symbol, "AND") then
3117 line := symbol[4 ..] & line;
3118 symbol := "AND";
3119 end if;
3120 end while;
3121 end func;

3140const func integer: binary_xor (in var integer: number1, in var integer: number2) is func
3141 result
3142 var integer: exprResult is 0;
3143 local
3144 var integer: count is 0;
3145 begin
3146 for count range 0 to 15 do
3147 if odd(number1) <> odd(number2) then
3148 exprResult +:= 2 ** count;
3149 end if;
3150 number1 := number1 div 2;
3151 number2 := number2 div 2;
3152 end for;
3153 end func;

3155
3156const func float: exec_cond_or (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
3157 result
3158 var float: exprResult is 0.0;
3159 local
3160 var string: op is "";
3161 var integer: number1 is 0;
3162 var integer: number2 is 0;
3163 begin
3164 exprResult := exec_cond_and(symbol, line);
3165 if startsWith(symbol, "OR") then
3166 line := symbol[3 ..] & line;
3167 symbol := "OR";
3168 end if;
3169 while symbol = "OR" or symbol = "XOR" do
3170 number1 := round(exprResult);
3171 op := symbol;
3172 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3173 number2 := round(exec_cond_and(symbol, line));
3174 if op = "OR" then
3175 exprResult := flt(binary_or(number1, number2));
3176 elsif op = "XOR" then
3177 exprResult := flt(binary_xor(number1, number2));
3178 end if;
3179 if startsWith(symbol, "OR") then
3180 line := symbol[3 ..] & line;
3181 symbol := "OR";
3182 end if;
3183 end while;
3184 end func;
3185
3186
3187const func integer: binary_eqv (in var integer: number1, in var integer: number2) is func
3188 result
3189 var integer: exprResult is 0;
3190 local
3191 var integer: count is 0;
3192 begin
3193 for count range 0 to 15 do
3194 if odd(number1) = odd(number2) then
3195 exprResult +:= 2 ** count;
3196 end if;
3197 number1 := number1 div 2;
3198 number2 := number2 div 2;
3199 end for;
3200 end func;
3201
3202
3203const func float: exec_cond_eqv (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
3204 result
3205 var float: exprResult is 0.0;
3206 local
3207 var integer: number1 is 0;
3208 var integer: number2 is 0;
3209 begin
3210 exprResult := exec_cond_or(symbol, line);
3211 while symbol = "EQV" do
3212 number1 := round(exprResult);
3213 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3214 number2 := round(exec_cond_or(symbol, line));
3215 exprResult := flt(binary_eqv(number1, number2));
3216 end while;
3217 end func;

3220const func integer: binary_imp (in var integer: number1, in var integer: number2) is func
3221 result
3222 var integer: exprResult is 0;
3223 local
3224 var integer: count is 0;
3225 begin
3226 for count range 0 to 15 do
3227 if odd(number1) <= odd(number2) then
3228 exprResult +:= 2 ** count;
3229 end if;
3230 number1 := number1 div 2;
3231 number2 := number2 div 2;
3232 end for;
3233 end func;

3236const func float: exec_expr (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
3237 result
3238 var float: exprResult is 0.0;
3239 local
3240 var integer: number1 is 0;
3241 var integer: number2 is 0;
3242 begin
3243 exprResult := exec_cond_eqv(symbol, line);
3244 while symbol = "IMP" do
3245 number1 := round(exprResult);
3246 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3247 number2 := round(exec_cond_eqv(symbol, line));
3248 exprResult := flt(binary_imp(number1, number2));

3253const func string: getNameList (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
3254 result
3255 var string: nameList is "";
3256 begin
3257 nameList &:= symbol;
3258 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3259 while symbol = "," do
3260 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3261 if not endOfStatement(symbol) then
3262 nameList &:= ",";
3263 nameList &:= symbol;
3264 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3265 end if;
3266 end while;
3267 end func;

3270const func boolean: nameInList (in string: name, in var string: nameList) is func
3271 result
3272 var boolean: found is FALSE;
3273 local
3274 var string: symbol is "";
3275 begin
3276 repeat
3277 symbol := get_symbol(nameList);
3278 if name = symbol then
3279 found := TRUE;
3280 else
3281 symbol := get_symbol(nameList);
3282 end if;
3283 until symbol <> "," or found;
3284 end func;

3287const func string: removeNameFromList (in string: name, in var string: nameList) is func
3288 result

3295 symbol := get_symbol(nameList);
3296 if name = symbol then
3297 symbol := get_symbol(nameList);
3298 found := TRUE;
3299 else
3300 if newNameList <> "" then
3301 newNameList &:= ",";
3302 end if;
3303 newNameList &:= symbol;
3304 symbol := get_symbol(nameList);
3305 end if;
3306 until symbol <> "," or found;
3307 newNameList &:= nameList;

3311(**
3312 * Get the next BASIC symbol from the program.
3313 * When the end of the line is reached the search for a symbol is
3314 * continued in the next line.
3315 * @return the BASIC symbol or "" at the end of the program.
3316 *)
3317const func string: next_symbol (inout string: line) is func
3318 result
3319 var string: symbol is "";
3320 begin
3321 repeat
3322 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3323 if symbol = "" then
3324 incr(file_line_number);
3325 if file_line_number <= length(prg) then
3326 statement_label := prg[file_line_number].linenum;
3327 line := prg[file_line_number].line;
3328 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3329 end if;
3330 end if;
3331 until symbol <> "" or file_line_number > length(prg);
3332 end func;

3335(**
3336 * Search for a THEN in the current line.
3337 * @return "THEN" if a THEN was found, "" otherwise.
3338 *)
3339const func string: find_then (inout string: line) is func
3340 result
3341 var string: symbol is "";
3342 begin
3343 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3344 while symbol <> "THEN" and symbol <> "" do
3345 if ignoreRestOfLine(symbol) then
3346 line := "";
3347 end if;
3348 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3349 end while;
3350 end func;

3352
3353(**
3354 * Search for an ELSE in the current line.
3355 * If an IF is found a recursive call searches for a possible
3356 * inner ELSE which would belong to the inner IF. Such an inner ELSE
3357 * is skipped.
3358 * @param symbol contains the current symbol. After the call it
3359 * contains "ELSE" if a corresponding ELSE was found and
3360 * "" otherwise.
3361 * @param line contains the current line. After the call it contains
3362 * the rest of the line after the ELSE or "" if no ELSE was
3363 * found.
3364 *)
3365const proc: find_else (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
3366 begin
3367 if startsWith(symbol, "ELSE") and not is_let_statement(line) then
3368 line := symbol[5 ..] & line;
3369 symbol := "ELSE";
3370 end if;
3371 while symbol <> "ELSE" and symbol <> "" do
3372 if startsWith(symbol, "IF") and not is_let_statement(line) then
3373 line := symbol[3 ..] & line;
3374 symbol := "IF";
3375 end if;
3376 if symbol = "IF" then
3377 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3378 find_else(symbol, line);
3379 elsif ignoreRestOfLine(symbol) then
3380 line := "";
3381 end if;
3382 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3383 if startsWith(symbol, "ELSE") and not is_let_statement(line) then
3384 line := symbol[5 ..] & line;
3385 symbol := "ELSE";
3386 end if;
3387 end while;
3388 end func;
3389
3390
3391(**
3392 * Search for a NEXT matching a "FOR varName" statement.
3393 * If a FOR is found a recursive call searches for a possible
3394 * inner NEXT which would belong to the inner FOR. Such an inner NEXT
3395 * is skipped if it does not match a "FOR varName" statement.
3396 * @param symbol contains the current symbol. After the call it
3397 * contains the symbol behind the NEXT and the optional list
3398 * of variable names. If no NEXT was found, the parameter
3399 * contains "" after the call.
3400 * @param nameList returns the list of variable names found after
3401 * the NEXT or "" if no NEXT was found or no list list of
3402 * variable names is present after the NEXT.
3403 * @return TRUE if a corresponding NEXT was found, FALSE otherwise.
3404 *)
3405const func boolean: find_next (inout string: symbol, inout string: line,
3406 in string: varName, inout string: nameList) is func
3407 result
3408 var boolean: found is FALSE;
3409 local
3410 var string: label is "";
3411 var string: innerVarName is "";
3412 var string: innerNameList is "";
3413 begin
3414 while not found and symbol <> "NEXT" and symbol <> "" do
3415 if symbol = "FOR" then
3416 symbol := next_symbol(line);
3417 innerVarName := symbol;
3418 label := statement_label;
3419 if find_next(symbol, line, innerVarName, innerNameList) and
3420 (innerNameList = "" or nameInList(innerVarName, innerNameList)) then
3421 if nameInList(varName, innerNameList) then
3422 found := TRUE;
3423 nameList := innerNameList;
3424 end if;
3425 else
3426 error_marker(label);
3427 writeln(err, "NO CORRESPONDING \"NEXT\" OR \"NEXT " <& innerVarName <&
3428 "\" FOUND FOR \"FOR " <& innerVarName <& "\"");
3429 end if;
3430 elsif symbol = "EXIT" then
3431 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3432 elsif ignoreRestOfLine(symbol) then
3433 line := "";
3434 end if;
3435 if not found then
3436 symbol := next_symbol(line);
3437 end if;
3438 end while;
3439 if not found and symbol = "NEXT" then
3440 found := TRUE;
3441 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3442 if endOfStatement(symbol) then
3443 nameList := "";
3444 else
3445 nameList := getNameList(symbol, line);
3446 end if;
3447 end if;
3448 end func;
3449
3450
3451(**
3452 * Search for a NEXT matching a "FOR varName" statement.
3453 * If a FOR is found a recursive call searches for a possible
3454 * inner NEXT which would belong to the inner FOR. Such an inner NEXT
3455 * is skipped if it does not match a "FOR varName" statement.
3456 * @param symbol contains the current symbol or "" if the next
3457 * symbol should be read. After the call it contains the
3458 * symbol behind the NEXT and the optional list of variable
3459 * names. If no NEXT was found, the parameter contains ""
3460 * after the call.
3461 * @return TRUE if a corresponding NEXT was found, FALSE otherwise.
3462 *)
3463const func boolean: find_next (inout string: symbol, inout string: line,
3464 in string: varName) is func
3465 result
3466 var boolean: found is FALSE;
3467 local
3468 var string: nameList is "";
3469 begin
3470 if symbol = "" then
3471 symbol := next_symbol(line);
3472 end if;
3473 found := find_next(symbol, line, varName, nameList) and
3474 (nameList = "" or nameInList(varName, nameList));
3475 if found then
3476 line_marker;
3477 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
3478 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3479 end while;
3480 write(log, "LEAVE \"FOR " <& varName <& "\" - CONTINUE AFTER \"NEXT");
3481 if nameList <> "" then
3482 write(log, " " <& nameList);
3483 end if;
3484 writeln(log, "\"");
3485 end if;
3486 end func;

3676 result

3682 if symbol = "IF" then
3683 repeat
3684 symbol := find_then(line);
3685 if symbol = "THEN" then
3686 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3687 if symbol = "" or symbol = "'" or symbol = "REM" then
3688 symbol := find_end_if(line);
3689 if symbol = "IF" then
3690 symbol := "";
3691 end if;
3692 else
3693 symbol := "";
3694 line := "";
3695 end if;
3696 end if;
3697 until symbol <> "IF";
3698 elsif symbol = "CASE" then
3699 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3700 end if;

3702 line := "";
3703 end if;
3704 symbol := next_symbol(line);
3705 end while;

3711 line := "";
3712 end if;

3714 symbol := find_else_elseif_or_end_if(line);

3751
3752const proc: exec_elseif_else_chain (inout string: symbol, inout string: line,
3753 inout boolean: process_next) is func
3754 local
3755 var float: num1 is 0.0;
3756 var boolean: leaveChain is TRUE;
3757 begin
3758 repeat
3759 symbol := find_else_elseif_or_end_if(line);
3760 if symbol = "ELSE" then
3761 if upper(prg[file_line_number].line[.. 4]) <> "ELSE" then
3762 error_marker;
3763 writeln(err, "ELSE NOT AT BEGINNING OF LINE");
3764 end if;
3765 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3766 # Execute the following statements until "ELSE", "ELSEIF" or "END" "IF".
3767 line_marker;
3768 writeln(log, "ELSE - EXECUTE STATEMENT BLOCK");
3769 if symbol <> "" and symbol <> "'" and symbol <> "REM" then
3770 error_marker;
3771 writeln(err, "BLOCK STARTS DIRECTLY AFTER ELSE");
3772 process_next := TRUE;
3773 end if;
3774 leaveChain := TRUE;
3775 elsif symbol = "ELSEIF" then
3776 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3777 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
3778 if num1 <> 0.0 then
3779 expect("THEN", symbol, line);
3780 # Execute the following statements until "ELSE", "ELSEIF" or "END" "IF".
3781 line_marker;
3782 writeln(log, "ELSEIF " <& num1 <& " THEN - EXECUTE STATEMENT BLOCK");
3783 if symbol <> "" and symbol <> "'" and symbol <> "REM" then
3784 error_marker;
3785 writeln(err, "BLOCK STARTS DIRECTLY AFTER THEN");
3786 process_next := TRUE;
3787 end if;
3788 leaveChain := TRUE;
3789 else
3790 line_marker;
3791 writeln(log, "ELSEIF " <& num1 <& " THEN - SKIP STATEMENT BLOCK");
3792 leaveChain := FALSE;
3793 end if;
3794 elsif symbol = "IF" or symbol = "ENDIF" then
3795 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3796 line_marker;
3797 writeln(log, "END IF - NO \"THEN\" BLOCK WAS EXECUTED");
3798 leaveChain := TRUE;
3799 end if;
3800 until leaveChain;
3801 end func;

3804const proc: advance_after_statement (inout string: line) is func
3805 local
3806 var integer: length is 0;
3807 var integer: column is 0;
3808 var string: symbol is "";
3809 begin
3810 repeat
3811 length := length(line);
3812 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3813 until endOfStatement(symbol);
3814 column := length(prg[file_line_number].line) - length + 1;
3815 line := prg[file_line_number].line[column ..];
3816 end func;

3819const proc: exec_goto (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
3820 local
3821 var integer: index1 is 0;
3822 var integer: index2 is 0;
3823 begin
3824 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3825 if label_or_linenum(symbol) then
3826 line_marker;
3827 writeln(log, "GOTO " <& symbol);
3828 goto_label_or_linenum(symbol);
3829 symbol := "";
3830 line := "";
3831 elsif symbol in multipleDefinedLabel then
3832 error_marker;
3833 writeln(err, "GOTO MULTIPLE DEFINED LABEL " <& symbol <& ".");
3834 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3835 else
3836 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
3837 expect("OF", symbol, line);
3838 if index1 >= 1 then
3839 index2 := 1;
3840 while index2 < index1 do
3841 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3842 if symbol = "," then
3843 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3844 incr(index2);
3845 else
3846 index2 := succ(index1);
3847 end if;
3848 end while;
3849 if index2 = index1 then
3850 if label_or_linenum(symbol) then
3851 line_marker;
3852 writeln(log, "GOTO " <& index1 <& " OF " <& symbol);
3853 goto_label_or_linenum(symbol);
3854 symbol := "";
3855 line := "";
3856 else
3857 error_marker;
3858 writeln(err, "UNDEFINED LABEL " <& symbol <& " AFTER \"OF\".");
3859 end if;
3860 else
3861 line_marker;
3862 writeln(log, "GOTO " <& index1 <& " OF NEXT STATEMENT");
3863 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
3864 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3865 end while;
3866 end if;
3867 else
3868 line_marker;
3869 writeln(log, "GOTO " <& index1 <& " OF NEXT STATEMENT");
3870 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
3871 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3872 end while;
3873 end if;
3874 end if;
3875 end func;

3877
3878const proc: exec_gosub (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
3879 local
3880 var integer: index1 is 0;
3881 var integer: index2 is 0;
3882 begin
3883 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3884 if label_or_linenum(symbol) then
3885 line_marker;
3886 writeln(log, "GOSUB " <& symbol);
3887 set_return_position(line);
3888 goto_label_or_linenum(symbol);
3889 set_sub_entry_position;
3890 symbol := "";
3891 line := "";
3892 elsif symbol in multipleDefinedLabel then
3893 error_marker;
3894 writeln(err, "GOSUB TO MULTIPLE DEFINED LABEL " <& symbol <& ".");
3895 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3896 else
3897 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
3898 expect("OF", symbol, line);
3899 if index1 >= 1 then
3900 index2 := 1;
3901 while index2 < index1 do
3902 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3903 if symbol = "," then
3904 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3905 incr(index2);
3906 else
3907 index2 := succ(index1);
3908 end if;
3909 end while;
3910 if index2 = index1 then
3911 if label_or_linenum(symbol) then
3912 line_marker;
3913 writeln(log, "GOSUB " <& index1 <& " OF " <& symbol);
3914 advance_after_statement(line);
3915 set_return_position(line);
3916 goto_label_or_linenum(symbol);
3917 set_sub_entry_position;
3918 symbol := "";
3919 line := "";
3920 else
3921 error_marker;
3922 writeln(err, "UNDEFINED LABEL " <& symbol <& " AFTER \"OF\".");
3923 end if;
3924 else
3925 line_marker;
3926 writeln(log, "GOSUB " <& index1 <& " OF NEXT STATEMENT");
3927 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
3928 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3929 end while;
3930 end if;
3931 else
3932 line_marker;
3933 writeln(log, "GOSUB " <& index1 <& " OF NEXT STATEMENT");
3934 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
3935 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3936 end while;
3937 end if;
3938 end if;
3939 end func;
3940
3941
3942const proc: exec_let (in var string: variable_name,
3943 inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
3944 local
3945 var string: param1 is "";
3946 var float: num1 is 0.0;
3947 var string: unused_name is "";
3948 begin
3949 if isStringVar(variable_name) then
3950 append_index(variable_name, symbol, line);
3951 if symbol = "=" then
3952 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3953 param1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
3954 setStringVar(variable_name, param1);
3955 line_marker;
3956 writeln(log, "LET " <& variable_name <& "=" <& literal(param1));
3957 else
3958 error_marker;
3959 writeln(err, "\"=\" EXPECTED AFTER " <& literal(variable_name) <&
3960 " - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
3961 end if;
3962 elsif isNumericVar(variable_name) then
3963 append_index(variable_name, symbol, line);
3964 if symbol = "=" then
3965 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3966 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
3967 setNumericVar(variable_name, num1);
3968 line_marker;
3969 writeln(log, "LET " <& variable_name <& "=" <& num1);
3970 else
3971 error_marker;
3972 writeln(err, "\"=\" EXPECTED AFTER " <& literal(variable_name) <&
3973 " - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
3974 end if;
3975 else
3976 error_marker;
3977 writeln(err, "VARIABLE EXPECTED - FOUND " <& literal(variable_name) <& ".");
3978 end if;
3979 end func;
3980
3981
3982const proc: exec_mid_statement (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
3983 local
3984 var string: variable_name is "";
3985 var string: unused_name is "";
3986 var string: var_value is "";
3987 var string: stri is "";
3988 var integer: position is 0;
3989 var integer: length is 0;
3990 var integer: requested_length is 0;
3991 var boolean: with_length is FALSE;
3992 begin
3993 symbol := get_symbol(line);
3994 expect("(", symbol, line);
3995 if isStringVar(symbol) then
3996 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
3997 expect(",", symbol, line);
3998 position := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
3999 if symbol = "," then
4000 with_length := TRUE;
4001 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4002 requested_length := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
4003 length := requested_length;
4004 expect(")", symbol, line);
4005 expect("=", symbol, line);
4006 stri := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
4007 if length > length(stri) then
4008 length := length(stri);
4009 end if;
4010 else
4011 expect(")", symbol, line);
4012 expect("=", symbol, line);
4013 stri := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
4014 length := length(stri);
4015 end if;
4016 var_value := getStringVar(variable_name);
4017 if position <= length(var_value) then
4018 if succ(length(var_value) - position) < length then
4019 length := succ(length(var_value) - position);
4020 end if;
4021 var_value := var_value[ .. pred(position)] & stri[ .. length] &
4022 var_value[position + length ..];
4023 setStringVar(variable_name, var_value);
4024 write(log, "MID$(" <& variable_name <& ", " <& position);
4025 if with_length then
4026 write(log, ", " <& requested_length);
4027 end if;
4028 writeln(log, ")=" <& literal(stri));
4029 else
4030 error_marker;
4031 writeln(err, "MID$ POSITION " <& position <&
4032 " LARGER THAN LENGTH OF " <& literal(var_value));
4033 end if;
4034 else
4035 error_marker;
4036 writeln(err, "STRING VARIABLE EXPECTED - FOUND " <& literal(symbol));
4037 end if;
4038 end func;
4039
4040
4041const proc: exec_next_decision (inout string: symbol, inout string: line,
4042 val string: variable_name, in string: nameList) is func
4043 local
4044 var float: num1 is 0.0;
4045 begin
4046 if length(forLoop) >= 1 and variable_name = forLoop[1].varName then
4047 num1 := getNumericVar(variable_name);
4048 if (forLoop[1].stepValue > 0.0 and num1 + forLoop[1].stepValue <= forLoop[1].endValue) or
4049 (forLoop[1].stepValue < 0.0 and num1 + forLoop[1].stepValue >= forLoop[1].endValue) then
4050 line_marker;
4051 setNumericVar(variable_name, num1 + forLoop[1].stepValue);
4052 file_line_number := forLoop[1].bodyLine;
4053 statement_label := prg[file_line_number].linenum;
4054 line := prg[file_line_number].line[forLoop[1].bodyColumn .. ];
4055 if line <> "" then
4056 symbol := ":";
4057 else
4058 symbol := "";
4059 end if;
4060 write(log, "NEXT " <& variable_name <& " = " <& num1 + forLoop[1].stepValue <&
4061 " CONTINUE THE \"FOR " <& variable_name <& "\" LOOP AT LINE ");
4062 line_marker;
4063 writeln(log);
4064 else
4065 line_marker;
4066 writeln(log, "NEXT " <& variable_name <& " = " <& num1 <& " END FOR");
4067 forLoop := forLoop[2 .. ];
4068 if length(forLoop) >= 1 and forLoop[1].varName <> variable_name and
4069 nameInList(forLoop[1].varName, nameList) then
4070 line_marker;
4071 write(log, "THE \"FOR " <& forLoop[1].varName <&
4072 "\" LOOP AT LINE ");
4073 line_marker(forLoop[1].bodyLine);
4074 writeln(log, " IS ALSO HANDLED WITH THIS NEXT STATEMENT");
4075 exec_next_decision(symbol, line, forLoop[1].varName,
4076 removeNameFromList(variable_name, nameList));
4077 end if;
4078 end if;
4079 else
4080 error_marker;
4081 writeln(err, "\"NEXT " <& forLoop[1].varName <&
4082 "\" EXPECTED - FOUND \"NEXT " <& variable_name <& "\"");
4083 end if;
4084 end func;

4086
4087const proc: exec_if (inout string: symbol, inout string: line,
4088 inout boolean: process_next) is func
4089 local
4090 var string: param1 is "";
4091 var float: num1 is 0.0;
4092 begin
4093 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4094 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
4095 if startsWith(symbol, "THEN") then
4096 line := symbol[5 ..] & line;
4097 symbol := "THEN";
4098 elsif startsWith(symbol, "GOTO") then
4099 line := symbol[5 ..] & line;
4100 symbol := "GOTO";
4101 elsif startsWith(symbol, "GOSUB") then
4102 line := symbol[6 ..] & line;
4103 symbol := "GOSUB";
4104 end if;
4105 if num1 <> 0.0 then
4106 if symbol = "THEN" then
4107 line_marker;
4108 write(log, "IF " <& num1);
4109 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4110 if symbol = "" or symbol = "'" or symbol = "REM" then
4111 # Execute the following statements until "ELSE", "ELSEIF" or "END" "IF".
4112 writeln(log, " THEN - EXECUTE STATEMENT BLOCK");
4113 elsif label_or_linenum(symbol) then
4114 param1 := symbol;
4115 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4116 # A label and a variable can share the same name
4117 if symbol = "=" or symbol = "(" or symbol = "[" then
4118 # A let statement is recognized: Write log and exec the let statement.
4119 writeln(log, " THEN - EXECUTE STATEMENTS IN LINE UNTIL \"ELSE\"");
4120 exec_let(param1, symbol, line);
4121 else
4122 writeln(log, " THEN " <& param1 <& " - GOTO LINE");
4123 goto_label_or_linenum(param1);
4124 symbol := "";
4125 line := "";
4126 end if;
4127 else
4128 writeln(log, " THEN - EXECUTE STATEMENTS IN LINE UNTIL \"ELSE\"");
4129 process_next := TRUE;
4130 end if;
4131 elsif symbol = "GOTO" then
4132 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4133 line_marker;
4134 writeln(log, "IF " <& num1 <& " GOTO " <& symbol <& " - GOTO LINE");
4135 if label_or_linenum(symbol) then
4136 goto_label_or_linenum(symbol);
4137 symbol := "";
4138 line := "";
4139 else
4140 error_marker;
4141 writeln(err, "UNDEFINED LABEL " <& symbol <& " AFTER \"GOTO\".");
4142 end if;
4143 elsif symbol = "GOSUB" then
4144 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4145 line_marker;
4146 writeln(log, "IF " <& num1 <& " GOSUB " <& symbol <& " - GOSUB LINE");
4147 if label_or_linenum(symbol) then
4148 set_return_position(line);
4149 goto_label_or_linenum(symbol);
4150 set_sub_entry_position;
4151 symbol := "";
4152 line := "";
4153 else
4154 error_marker;
4155 writeln(err, "UNDEFINED LABEL " <& symbol <& " AFTER \"GOSUB\".");
4156 end if;
4157 else
4158 error_expect3("THEN", "GOTO", "GOSUB", symbol);
4159 end if;
4160 else
4161 if symbol = "THEN" or symbol = "GOTO" or symbol = "GOSUB" then
4162 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4163 else
4164 error_expect3("THEN", "GOTO", "GOSUB", symbol);
4165 end if;
4166 line_marker;
4167 write(log, "IF " <& num1);
4168 if symbol = "" or symbol = "'" or symbol = "REM" then
4169 writeln(log, " THEN - SKIP STATEMENT BLOCK");
4170 exec_elseif_else_chain(symbol, line, process_next);
4171 elsif label_or_linenum(symbol) then
4172 writeln(log, " THEN " <& symbol <& " - SKIP LABEL");
4173 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4174 if startsWith(symbol, "ELSE") and not is_let_statement(line) then
4175 line := symbol[5 ..] & line;
4176 symbol := "ELSE";
4177 end if;
4178 if symbol = "ELSE" then
4179 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4180 if label_or_linenum(symbol) then
4181 line_marker;
4182 writeln(log, "ELSE " <& symbol <& " - GOTO LINE");
4183 goto_label_or_linenum(symbol);
4184 symbol := "";
4185 line := "";
4186 else
4187 line_marker;
4188 writeln(log, "ELSE - EXECUTE STATEMENTS IN LINE");
4189 process_next := TRUE;
4190 end if;
4191 elsif symbol = ":" then
4192 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4193 if startsWith(symbol, "ELSE") and not is_let_statement(line) then
4194 line := symbol[5 ..] & line;
4195 symbol := "ELSE";
4196 end if;
4197 if symbol = "ELSE" then
4198 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4199 if label_or_linenum(symbol) then
4200 line_marker;
4201 writeln(log, "ELSE " <& symbol <& " - GOTO LINE");
4202 goto_label_or_linenum(symbol);
4203 symbol := "";
4204 line := "";
4205 else
4206 line_marker;
4207 writeln(log, "ELSE - EXECUTE STATEMENTS IN LINE");
4208 process_next := TRUE;
4209 end if;
4210 else
4211 line_marker;
4212 writeln(log, "NO ELSE - CONTINUE AFTER THE LABEL");
4213 process_next := TRUE;
4214 end if;
4215 else
4216 line_marker;
4217 writeln(log, "NO ELSE - CONTINUE AT NEXT LINE");
4218 symbol := "";
4219 line := "";
4220 end if;
4221 else
4222 writeln(log, " THEN - SKIP STATEMENTS IN LINE UNTIL \"ELSE\"");
4223 find_else(symbol, line);
4224 if symbol = "ELSE" then
4225 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4226 if label_or_linenum(symbol) then
4227 line_marker;
4228 writeln(log, "ELSE " <& symbol <& " - GOTO LINE");
4229 goto_label_or_linenum(symbol);
4230 symbol := "";
4231 line := "";
4232 else
4233 line_marker;
4234 writeln(log, "ELSE - EXECUTE STATEMENTS IN LINE");
4235 process_next := TRUE;
4236 end if;
4237 else
4238 line_marker;
4239 writeln(log, "NO ELSE - CONTINUE AT NEXT LINE");
4240 symbol := "";
4241 line := "";
4242 end if;
4243 end if;
4244 end if;
4245 end func;
4246
4247
4248const proc: exec_else (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
4249 begin
4250 line_marker;
4251 writeln(log, "ELSE - THE \"THEN\" BLOCK BEFORE WAS EXECUTED");
4252 if upper(prg[file_line_number].line[.. 4]) = "ELSE" then
4253 symbol := find_end_if(line);
4254 if symbol = "IF" then
4255 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4256 line_marker;
4257 writeln(log, "END IF");
4258 else
4259 error_marker;
4260 writeln(err, "ELSE - MISSING \"END IF\".");
4261 end if;
4262 else
4263 line := "";
4264 symbol := "";
4265 line_marker;
4266 writeln(log, "SKIP ELSE PART - CONTINUE AT NEXT LINE");
4267 end if;
4268 end func;

4270
4271const proc: exec_for (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
4272 local
4273 var string: variable_name is "";
4274 var float: num1 is 0.0;
4275 var float: num2 is 0.0;
4276 var float: num3 is 0.0;
4277 var integer: index1 is 0;
4278 var string: label is "";
4279 begin
4280 variable_name := get_symbol(line);
4281 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4282 expect("=", symbol, line);
4283 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
4284 setNumericVar(variable_name, num1);
4285 if symbol = "TO" then
4286 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4287 elsif startsWith(symbol, "TO") then
4288 line := symbol[3 ..] & line;
4289 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4290 else
4291 error_expect("TO", symbol);
4292 end if;
4293 num2 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
4294 if symbol = "STEP" then
4295 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4296 num3 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
4297 elsif startsWith(symbol, "STEP") then
4298 line := symbol[5 ..] & line;
4299 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4300 num3 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
4301 else
4302 num3 := 1.0;
4303 end if;
4304 if (num3 > 0.0 and num1 <= num2) or
4305 (num3 < 0.0 and num1 >= num2) then
4306 if symbol = "'" or symbol = "REM" then
4307 index1 := succ(length(prg[file_line_number].line));
4308 else
4309 index1 := length(prg[file_line_number].line) - length(line) + 1;
4310 end if;
4311 forLoop := [] (forLoopDescrType.value) & forLoop;
4312 forLoop[1].varName := variable_name;
4313 forLoop[1].endValue := num2;
4314 forLoop[1].stepValue := num3;
4315 forLoop[1].bodyLine := file_line_number;
4316 forLoop[1].bodyColumn := index1;
4317 line_marker;
4318 writeln(log, "FOR " <& variable_name <& "=" <& num1 <&
4319 " TO " <& num2 <& " STEP " <& num3);
4320 else
4321 line_marker;
4322 writeln(log, "EMPTY FOR " <& variable_name <& "=" <& num1 <&
4323 " TO " <& num2 <& " STEP " <& num3);
4324 label := statement_label;
4325 if not find_next(symbol, line, variable_name) then
4326 error_marker(label);
4327 writeln(err, "NO CORRESPONDING \"NEXT\" OR \"NEXT " <& variable_name <&
4328 "\" FOUND FOR \"FOR " <& variable_name <& "\"");
4329 end if;
4330 end if;
4331 end func;
4332
4333
4334const proc: exec_next (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
4335 local
4336 var string: variable_name is "";
4337 var string: param1 is "";
4338 var integer: index1 is 0;
4339 var integer: index2 is 0;
4340 begin
4341 if length(forLoop) >= 1 then
4342 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4343 if endOfStatement(symbol) then
4344 param1 := "";
4345 variable_name := forLoop[1].varName;
4346 else
4347 param1 := getNameList(symbol, line);
4348 if nameInList(forLoop[1].varName, param1) then
4349 variable_name := forLoop[1].varName;
4350 else
4351 index1 := 2;
4352 while index1 <= length(forLoop) and not nameInList(forLoop[index1].varName, param1) do
4353 incr(index1)
4354 end while;
4355 if index1 <= length(forLoop) and nameInList(forLoop[index1].varName, param1) then
4356 for index2 range 1 to pred(index1) do
4357 line_marker;
4358 write(log, "THE \"FOR " <& forLoop[index2].varName <& "\" LOOP AT LINE ");
4359 line_marker(forLoop[index2].bodyLine);
4360 writeln(log, " SEEMS TO HAVE BEEN LEFT");
4361 end for;
4362 forLoop := forLoop[index1 .. ];
4363 variable_name := forLoop[1].varName;
4364 elsif on_error_label <> "" then
4365 error_code := 1; # NEXT without FOR
4366 line_marker;
4367 writeln(log, error_code <& " NEXT WITHOUT FOR" <&
4368 " - ON ERROR GOTO " <& on_error_label);
4369 goto_on_error(on_error_label, line);
4370 symbol := "";
4371 line := "";
4372 variable_name := "";
4373 else
4374 error_marker;
4375 writeln(err, "NEXT " <& param1 <& " - NO MATCHING FOR FOUND");
4376 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
4377 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4378 end while;
4379 variable_name := param1;
4380 end if;
4381 end if;
4382 end if;
4383 exec_next_decision(symbol, line, variable_name, param1);
4384 elsif on_error_label <> "" then
4385 error_code := 1; # NEXT without FOR
4386 line_marker;
4387 writeln(log, error_code <& " NEXT " <& variable_name <& " WITHOUT FOR" <&
4388 " - ON ERROR GOTO " <& on_error_label);
4389 goto_on_error(on_error_label, line);
4390 symbol := "";
4391 line := "";
4392 else
4393 error_marker;
4394 writeln(err, "NEXT " <& variable_name <& " WITHOUT FOR");
4395 repeat
4396 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4397 until endOfStatement(symbol);
4398 end if;
4399 end func;
4400
4401
4402const proc: exec_on (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
4403 local
4404 var string: param1 is "";
4405 var integer: index1 is 0;
4406 var integer: index2 is 0;
4407 var integer: keywordPos is 0;
4408 begin
4409 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4410 if symbol = "ERROR" then
4411 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4412 expect("GOTO", symbol, line);
4413 if symbol = "0" then
4414 on_error_label := "";
4415 line_marker;
4416 writeln(log, "ON ERROR GOTO 0 - DISABLE ERROR HANDLING");
4417 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4418 elsif label_or_linenum(symbol) then
4419 on_error_label := symbol;
4420 line_marker;
4421 writeln(log, "ON ERROR GOTO " <& literal(symbol) <&
4422 " LINE: " <& label[symbol]);
4423 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4424 else
4425 error_marker;
4426 writeln(err, "ON ERROR GOTO NEEDS A LABEL NOT " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
4427 end if;
4428 elsif symbol = "KEY" then
4429 line_marker;
4430 writeln(log, "**ON KEY " <& line);
4431 repeat
4432 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4433 until endOfStatement(symbol);
4434 elsif symbol = "TIMER" then
4435 line_marker;
4436 writeln(log, "**ON TIMER " <& line);
4437 repeat
4438 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4439 until endOfStatement(symbol);
4440 else
4441 if symbol not in numeric_var and symbol not in def_fn_list and
4442 symbol not in subfunction then
4443 keywordPos := pos(symbol, "GOTO");
4444 if keywordPos <> 0 then
4445 line := symbol[keywordPos ..] & line;
4446 symbol := symbol[.. pred(keywordPos)];
4447 else
4448 keywordPos := pos(symbol, "GOSUB");
4449 if keywordPos <> 0 then
4450 line := symbol[keywordPos ..] & line;
4451 symbol := symbol[.. pred(keywordPos)];
4452 end if;
4453 end if;
4454 end if;
4455 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
4456 if startsWith(symbol, "GOTO") then
4457 line := symbol[5 ..] & line;
4458 symbol := "GOTO";
4459 elsif startsWith(symbol, "GOSUB") then
4460 line := symbol[6 ..] & line;
4461 symbol := "GOSUB";
4462 end if;
4463 if symbol = "GOTO" or symbol = "GOSUB" then
4464 param1 := symbol;
4465 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4466 if index1 >= 1 then
4467 index2 := 1;
4468 while index2 < index1 do
4469 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4470 if symbol = "," then
4471 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4472 incr(index2);
4473 else
4474 index2 := succ(index1);
4475 end if;
4476 end while;
4477 if index2 = index1 then
4478 if label_or_linenum(symbol) then
4479 line_marker;
4480 writeln(log, "ON " <& index1 <& " " <& param1 <& " " <& symbol);
4481 if param1 = "GOSUB" then
4482 advance_after_statement(line);
4483 set_return_position(line);
4484 goto_label_or_linenum(symbol);
4485 set_sub_entry_position;
4486 else
4487 goto_label_or_linenum(symbol);
4488 end if;
4489 symbol := "";
4490 line := "";
4491 else
4492 error_marker;
4493 writeln(err, "UNDEFINED LABEL " <& symbol <& " AFTER \"" <&
4494 "ON " <& index1 <& " " <& param1 <& "\".");
4495 end if;
4496 else
4497 line_marker;
4498 writeln(log, "ON " <& index1 <& " GOTO NEXT STATEMENT");
4499 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
4500 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4501 end while;
4502 end if;
4503 else
4504 line_marker;
4505 writeln(log, "ON " <& index1 <& " GOTO NEXT STATEMENT");
4506 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
4507 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4508 end while;
4509 end if;
4510 else
4511 error_expect2("GOTO", "GOSUB", symbol);
4512 end if;
4513 end if;
4514 end func;
4515
4516
4517const proc: exec_do (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
4518 local
4519 var float: num1 is 0.0;
4520 var string: headLabel is "";
4521 var integer: headLine is 0;
4522 var integer: headColumn is 0;
4523 begin
4524 headLine := file_line_number;
4525 headColumn := length(prg[file_line_number].line) - length(line) + 1;
4526 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4527 if symbol = "WHILE" then
4528 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4529 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
4530 line_marker;
4531 writeln(log, "DO WHILE " <& num1);
4532 if num1 <> 0.0 then
4533 doLoop := [] (doLoopDescrType.value) & doLoop;
4534 doLoop[1].headLine := headLine;
4535 doLoop[1].headColumn := headColumn;
4536 else
4537 line_marker;
4538 writeln(log, "EMPTY \"DO WHILE\"");
4539 if symbol <> "LOOP" then
4540 headLabel := statement_label;
4541 symbol := find_loop(line);
4542 end if;
4543 if symbol = "LOOP" then
4544 repeat
4545 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4546 until endOfStatement(symbol);
4547 line_marker;
4548 writeln(log, "CONTINUE AFTER \"DO WHILE ... LOOP\"");
4549 else
4550 error_marker(headLabel);
4551 writeln(err, "NO CORRESPONDING \"LOOP\" FOUND FOR \"DO WHILE\"");
4552 end if;
4553 end if;
4554 elsif symbol = "UNTIL" then
4555 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4556 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
4557 line_marker;
4558 writeln(log, "DO UNTIL " <& num1);
4559 if num1 = 0.0 then
4560 doLoop := [] (doLoopDescrType.value) & doLoop;
4561 doLoop[1].headLine := headLine;
4562 doLoop[1].headColumn := headColumn;
4563 else
4564 line_marker;
4565 writeln(log, "EMPTY \"DO UNTIL\"");
4566 if symbol <> "LOOP" then
4567 headLabel := statement_label;
4568 symbol := find_loop(line);
4569 end if;
4570 if symbol = "LOOP" then
4571 repeat
4572 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4573 until endOfStatement(symbol);
4574 line_marker;
4575 writeln(log, "CONTINUE AFTER \"DO UNTIL ... LOOP\n");
4576 else
4577 error_marker(headLabel);
4578 writeln(err, "NO CORRESPONDING \"LOOP\" FOUND FOR \"DO UNTIL\"");
4579 end if;
4580 end if;
4581 elsif symbol = "=" or symbol = "(" or symbol = "[" then
4582 exec_let("DO", symbol, line);
4583 else
4584 line_marker;
4585 writeln(log, "DO ... LOOP");
4586 doLoop := [] (doLoopDescrType.value) & doLoop;
4587 doLoop[1].headLine := headLine;
4588 doLoop[1].headColumn := headColumn;
4589 end if;
4590 end func;
4591
4592
4593const proc: exec_loop (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
4594 local
4595 var string: param1 is "";
4596 var string: param2 is "";
4597 var float: num1 is 0.0;
4598 var integer: headLine is 0;
4599 var integer: headColumn is 0;
4600 var integer: tailLine is 0;
4601 var integer: tailColumn is 0;
4602 begin
4603 tailLine := file_line_number;
4604 tailColumn := length(prg[file_line_number].line) - length(line) + 1;
4605 if doLoopHeaderPresent(tailLine, tailColumn, headLine, headColumn) then
4606 if length(doLoop) >= 1 then
4607 if doLoop[1].headLine <> headLine or
4608 doLoop[1].headColumn <> headColumn then
4609 error_marker;
4610 writeln(err, "LOOP - \"DO\" LOOP ENTERED BY A GOTO");
4611 doLoop := [] (doLoopDescrType.value) & doLoop;
4612 doLoop[1].headLine := headLine;
4613 doLoop[1].headColumn := headColumn;
4614 end if;
4615 else
4616 error_marker;
4617 writeln(err, "LOOP - \"DO\" LOOP ENTERED BY A GOTO");
4618 doLoop := [] (doLoopDescrType.value) & doLoop;
4619 doLoop[1].headLine := headLine;
4620 doLoop[1].headColumn := headColumn;
4621 end if;
4622 else
4623 error_marker;
4624 writeln(err, "LOOP - NO STATICALLY CORRESPONDING \"DO\" STATEMENT FOUND");
4625 end if;
4626 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4627 if symbol = "WHILE" then
4628 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4629 if length(doLoop) >= 1 then
4630 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
4631 if num1 <> 0.0 then
4632 line_marker;
4633 file_line_number := doLoop[1].headLine;
4634 statement_label := prg[file_line_number].linenum;
4635 line := prg[file_line_number].line[doLoop[1].headColumn .. ];
4636 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4637 if symbol <> "WHILE" and symbol <> "UNTIL" then
4638 writeln(log, "LOOP - CONTINUE \"DO ... LOOP WHILE\"");
4639 else
4640 error_marker;
4641 writeln(err, "ILLEGAL - \"DO " <& symbol <& " ... LOOP WHILE\"");
4642 repeat
4643 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4644 until endOfStatement(symbol);
4645 end if;
4646 else
4647 doLoop := doLoop[2 .. ];
4648 line_marker;
4649 writeln(log, "LOOP - LEAVE \"DO ... LOOP WHILE\"");
4650 end if;
4651 else
4652 error_marker;
4653 writeln(err, "UNEXPECTED \"LOOP WHILE\"");
4654 end if;
4655 elsif symbol = "UNTIL" then
4656 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4657 if length(doLoop) >= 1 then
4658 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
4659 if num1 = 0.0 then
4660 line_marker;
4661 file_line_number := doLoop[1].headLine;
4662 statement_label := prg[file_line_number].linenum;
4663 line := prg[file_line_number].line[doLoop[1].headColumn .. ];
4664 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4665 if symbol <> "WHILE" and symbol <> "UNTIL" then
4666 writeln(log, "LOOP - CONTINUE \"DO ... LOOP UNTIL\"");
4667 else
4668 error_marker;
4669 writeln(err, "ILLEGAL - \"DO " <& symbol <& " .. LOOP UNTIL\"");
4670 repeat
4671 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4672 until endOfStatement(symbol);
4673 end if;
4674 else
4675 doLoop := doLoop[2 .. ];
4676 line_marker;
4677 writeln(log, "LOOP - LEAVE \"DO ... LOOP UNTIL\"");
4678 end if;
4679 else
4680 error_marker;
4681 writeln(err, "UNEXPECTED \"LOOP UNTIL\"");
4682 end if;
4683 else
4684 if length(doLoop) >= 1 then
4685 headLine := doLoop[1].headLine;
4686 param2 := prg[headLine].line[doLoop[1].headColumn .. ];
4687 param1 := get_symbol(param2);
4688 if param1 = "WHILE" then
4689 param1 := get_symbol(param2);
4690 num1 := exec_expr(param1, param2);
4691 if num1 <> 0.0 then
4692 line_marker;
4693 file_line_number := headLine;
4694 statement_label := prg[file_line_number].linenum;
4695 symbol := param1;
4696 line := param2;
4697 writeln(log, "LOOP - CONTINUE \"DO WHILE ... LOOP\"");
4698 else
4699 doLoop := doLoop[2 .. ];
4700 line_marker;
4701 writeln(log, "LOOP - LEAVE \"DO WHILE ... LOOP\"");
4702 end if;
4703 elsif param1 = "UNTIL" then
4704 param1 := get_symbol(param2);
4705 num1 := exec_expr(param1, param2);
4706 if num1 = 0.0 then
4707 line_marker;
4708 file_line_number := headLine;
4709 statement_label := prg[file_line_number].linenum;
4710 symbol := param1;
4711 line := param2;
4712 writeln(log, "LOOP - CONTINUE \"DO UNTIL ... LOOP\"");
4713 else
4714 doLoop := doLoop[2 .. ];
4715 line_marker;
4716 writeln(log, "LOOP - LEAVE \"DO UNTIL ... LOOP\"");
4717 end if;
4718 else
4719 line_marker;
4720 file_line_number := headLine;
4721 statement_label := prg[file_line_number].linenum;
4722 symbol := param1;
4723 line := param2;
4724 writeln(log, "LOOP - CONTINUE \"DO ... LOOP\"");
4725 end if;
4726 else
4727 error_marker;
4728 writeln(err, "UNEXPECTED \"LOOP UNTIL\"");
4729 end if;
4730 end if;
4731 end func;

4734const proc: exec_select (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
4735 local
4736 var string: unused_name is "";
4737 var string: param1 is "";
4738 var string: param2 is "";
4739 var string: param3 is "";
4740 var float: num1 is 0.0;
4741 var float: num2 is 0.0;
4742 var float: num3 is 0.0;
4743 var boolean: found is FALSE;
4744 var boolean: end_select is FALSE;
4745 var boolean: end_case is FALSE;
4746 var string: comparison is "";
4747 begin
4748 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4749 if symbol = "CASE" then
4750 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4751 if isStringExpr(symbol) then
4752 param1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
4753 line_marker;
4754 writeln(log, "SELECT CASE " <& literal(param1));
4755 repeat
4756 if ignoreRestOfLine(symbol) then
4757 line := "";
4758 end if;
4759 symbol := find_case_or_end_select(line);
4760 if symbol = "CASE" then
4761 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4762 if symbol = "ELSE" then
4763 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4764 found := TRUE;
4765 line_marker;
4766 writeln(log, "CASE ELSE - FOUND");
4767 else
4768 end_case := FALSE;
4769 repeat
4770 if symbol = "IS" then
4771 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4772 end if;
4773 if symbol = "=" or symbol = "<>" or
4774 symbol = "<" or symbol = ">" or
4775 symbol = "<=" or symbol = ">=" then
4776 comparison := symbol;
4777 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4778 else
4779 comparison := "=";
4780 end if;
4781 param2 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
4782 if symbol = "TO" then
4783 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4784 param3 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
4785 line_marker;
4786 write(log, "CASE " <& literal(param2) <& " TO " <&
4787 literal(param3));
4788 if param1 >= param2 and param1 <= param3 then
4789 found := TRUE;
4790 write(log, " - FOUND");
4791 end if;
4792 writeln(log);
4793 else
4794 if comparison = "=" then
4795 found := param1 = param2;
4796 elsif comparison = "<>" then
4797 found := param1 <> param2;
4798 elsif comparison = "<" then
4799 found := param1 < param2;
4800 elsif comparison = ">" then
4801 found := param1 > param2;
4802 elsif comparison = "<=" then
4803 found := param1 <= param2;
4804 elsif comparison = ">=" then
4805 found := param1 >= param2;
4806 end if;
4807 line_marker;
4808 write(log, "CASE IS " <& comparison <& " " <&
4809 literal(param2));
4810 if found then
4811 write(log, " - FOUND");
4812 end if;
4813 writeln(log);
4814 end if;
4815 if symbol = "," then
4816 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4817 else
4818 end_case := TRUE;
4819 end if;
4820 until found or end_case;
4821 end if;
4822 else
4823 end_select := TRUE;
4824 end if;
4825 until found or end_select;
4826 if not found then
4827 line_marker;
4828 writeln(log, "END SELECT - NO CASE FOUND FOR " <& literal(param1));
4829 end if;
4830 else
4831 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
4832 line_marker;
4833 writeln(log, "SELECT CASE " <& num1);
4834 repeat
4835 if ignoreRestOfLine(symbol) then
4836 line := "";
4837 end if;
4838 symbol := find_case_or_end_select(line);
4839 if symbol = "CASE" then
4840 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4841 if symbol = "ELSE" then
4842 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4843 found := TRUE;
4844 line_marker;
4845 writeln(log, "CASE ELSE - FOUND");
4846 else
4847 end_case := FALSE;
4848 repeat
4849 if symbol = "IS" then
4850 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4851 end if;
4852 if symbol = "=" or symbol = "<>" or
4853 symbol = "<" or symbol = ">" or
4854 symbol = "<=" or symbol = ">=" then
4855 comparison := symbol;
4856 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4857 else
4858 comparison := "=";
4859 end if;
4860 num2 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
4861 if symbol = "TO" then
4862 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4863 num3 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
4864 line_marker;
4865 write(log, "CASE " <& num2 <& " TO " <& num3);
4866 if num1 >= num2 and num1 <= num3 then
4867 found := TRUE;
4868 write(log, " - FOUND");
4869 end if;
4870 writeln(log);
4871 else
4872 if comparison = "=" then
4873 found := num1 = num2;
4874 elsif comparison = "<>" then
4875 found := num1 <> num2;
4876 elsif comparison = "<" then
4877 found := num1 < num2;
4878 elsif comparison = ">" then
4879 found := num1 > num2;
4880 elsif comparison = "<=" then
4881 found := num1 <= num2;
4882 elsif comparison = ">=" then
4883 found := num1 >= num2;
4884 end if;
4885 line_marker;
4886 write(log, "CASE IS " <& comparison <& " " <& num2);
4887 if found then
4888 write(log, " - FOUND");
4889 end if;
4890 writeln(log);
4891 end if;
4892 if symbol = "," then
4893 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4894 else
4895 end_case := TRUE;
4896 end if;
4897 until found or end_case;
4898 end if;
4899 else
4900 end_select := TRUE;
4901 end if;
4902 until found or end_select;
4903 if not found then
4904 line_marker;
4905 writeln(log, "END SELECT - NO CASE FOUND FOR " <& num1);
4906 end if;
4907 end if;
4908 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
4909 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4910 end while;
4911 else
4912 error_marker;
4913 writeln(err, "\"CASE\" EXPECTED AFTER \"SELECT\"");
4914 end if;
4915 end func;
4916
4917
4918const func boolean: continueWithPrintStatement (in var string: line) is func
4919 result
4920 var boolean: continueWithPrintStatement is FALSE;
4921 local
4922 var string: symbol is "";
4923 begin
4924 repeat
4925 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4926 until symbol <> ":";
4927 if symbol = "" or symbol[1] = '\"' or symbol = "TAB" then
4928 continueWithPrintStatement := TRUE;
4929 end if;
4930 end func;
