4933const proc: exec_print_using (inout file: outFile,
4934 inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
4935 local
4936 var string: unused_name is "";
4937 var string: param1 is "";
4938 var string: param2 is "";
4939 var float: num1 is 0.0;
4940 var integer: index1 is 0;
4941 var integer: index2 is 0;
4942 var integer: index3 is 0;
4943 var integer: index4 is 0;
4944 var char: ch1 is ' ';
4945 var char: ch2 is ' ';
4946 var integer: implicit_semicolon_pos is -1;
4947 begin
4948 write(log, "USING ");
4949 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4950 if isStringExpr(symbol) then
4951 param1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
4952 writeln(log, literal(param1));
4953 expect(";", symbol, line);
4954 repeat
4955 index1 := 1;
4956 while index1 <= length(param1) do
4957 ch1 := param1[index1];
4958 case ch1 of
4959 when {'!', '\\', '&'}:
4960 if symbol = ";" or symbol = "," then
4961 symbol := get_symbol(line);
4962 end if;
4963 if isStringExpr(symbol) then
4964 param2 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
4965 if ch1 = '!' then
4966 param2 := param2[1 len 1] rpad 1;
4967 write(outFile, param2);
4968 write(log, " " <& literal(param2));
4969 elsif ch1 = '\\' then
4970 index2 := index1;
4971 repeat
4972 incr(index1);
4973 if index1 <= length(param1) then
4974 ch1 := param1[index1];
4975 else
4976 ch1 := '\0;';
4977 end if;
4978 until ch1 <> ' ';
4979 if ch1 = '\\' then
4980 param2 := param2[1 len succ(index1 - index2)] rpad succ(index1 - index2);
4981 write(outFile, param2);
4982 write(log, " " <& literal(param2));
4983 else
4984 error_marker;
4985 writeln(err, "'\\' - FOUND " <& literal(ch1) <& ".");
4986 end if;
4987 elsif ch1 = '&' then
4988 write(outFile, param2);
4989 write(log, " " <& literal(param2));
4990 end if;
4991 else
4992 error_marker;
4993 writeln(err, "STRING EXPECTED - FOUND " <& symbol <& ".");
4994 end if;
4995 when {'#', '+', '.'}:
4996 if index1 < length(param1) then
4997 ch2 := param1[succ(index1)];
4998 else
4999 ch2 := '\0;';
5000 end if;
5001 if ch1 = '#' or
5002 ch1 = '+' and ch2 in {'#', '.'} or
5003 ch1 = '.' and ch2 = '#' then
5004 if symbol = ";" or symbol = "," then
5005 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5006 end if;
5007 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
5008 if ch1 = '+' then
5009 if num1 >= 0.0 then
5010 write(outFile, '+');
5011 write(log, '+');
5012 end if;
5013 ch1 := ch2;
5014 incr(index1);
5015 end if;
5016 index2 := index1;
5017 index3 := 0;
5018 index4 := 0;
5019 while ch1 = '#' do
5020 incr(index2);
5021 incr(index3);
5022 if index2 <= length(param1) then
5023 ch1 := param1[index2];
5024 else
5025 ch1 := '\0;';
5026 end if;
5027 if index2 < length(param1) then
5028 ch2 := param1[succ(index2)];
5029 else
5030 ch2 := '\0;';
5031 end if;
5032 if ch1 = ',' and ch2 = '#' then
5033 ch1 := ch2;
5034 incr(index2);
5035 end if;
5036 end while;
5037 if ch1 = '.' then
5038 incr(index2);
5039 if index2 <= length(param1) then
5040 ch1 := param1[index2];
5041 else
5042 ch1 := '\0;';
5043 end if;
5044 while ch1 = '#' do
5045 incr(index2);
5046 incr(index4);
5047 if index2 <= length(param1) then
5048 ch1 := param1[index2];
5049 else
5050 ch1 := '\0;';
5051 end if;
5052 if index2 < length(param1) then
5053 ch2 := param1[succ(index2)];
5054 else
5055 ch2 := '\0;';
5056 end if;
5057 if ch1 = ',' and ch2 = '#' then
5058 ch1 := ch2;
5059 incr(index2);
5060 end if;
5061 end while;
5062 end if;
5063 if index4 = 0 then
5064 param2 := num1 digits 0 lpad index3;
5065 else
5066 param2 := num1 digits index4 lpad index3 + index4 + 1;
5067 end if;
5068 write(log, num1 <& " " <& "#" mult index3 <& "." <&
5069 "#" mult index4 <& " " <& literal(param2));
5070 index3 := 1;
5071 while index1 < index2 do
5072 if index1 <= length(param1) then
5073 ch1 := param1[index1];
5074 else
5075 ch1 := '\0;';
5076 end if;
5077 ch2 := param2[index3];
5078 if ch1 = ',' then
5079 if index3 >= 2 and param2[pred(index3)] in digit_char then
5080 param2 := param2[.. pred(index3)] & "," & param2[index3 ..];
5081 else
5082 param2 := param2[.. pred(index3)] & " " & param2[index3 ..];
5083 end if;
5084 end if;
5085 incr(index1);
5086 incr(index3);
5087 end while;
5088 write(outFile, param2);
5089 write(log, " " <& literal(param2));
5090 index1 := pred(index2);
5091 else
5092 write(outFile, ch1);
5093 write(log, ch1);
5094 end if;
5095 when {'*'}:
5096 noop;
5097 when {'$'}:
5098 noop;
5099 when {'_'}:
5100 incr(index1);
5101 if index1 <= length(param1) then
5102 ch1 := param1[index1];
5103 write(outFile, ch1);
5104 write(log, ch1);
5105 end if;
5106 otherwise:
5107 write(outFile, ch1);
5108 write(log, ch1);
5109 end case;
5110 incr(index1);
5111 end while;
5112 if endOfStatement(symbol) then
5113 writeln(outFile);
5114 if symbol = ":" then
5115 # A colon can be a statement separator or it encodes a line break.
5116 if continueWithPrintStatement(line) then
5117 # The PRINT statement continues after the line break (:).
5118 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5119 write(log, ":");
5120 while symbol = ":" do
5121 writeln(win);
5122 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5123 write(log, ":");
5124 end while;
5125 else
5126 # After the statement separator (:) comes the next statement.
5127 symbol := ":";
5128 end if;
5129 end if;
5130 elsif symbol = ";" then
5131 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5132 elsif symbol = "," then
5133 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5134 else
5135 # This is the next thing to be printed.
5136 if implicit_semicolon_pos <> length(line) then
5137 implicit_semicolon_pos := length(line);
5138 write(log, " (;) ");
5139 else
5140 writeln(log);
5141 error_marker;
5142 writeln(err, "IGNORE " <& literal(symbol));
5143 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5144 end if;
5145 end if;
5146 until endOfStatement(symbol);
5147 writeln(log);
5148 end if;
5149 end func;
5150
5151
5152const proc: exec_print (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
5153 local
5154 var string: unused_name is "";
5155 var string: param1 is "";
5156 var float: num1 is 0.0;
5157 var integer: implicit_semicolon_pos is -1;
5158 begin
5159 line_marker;
5160 write(log, "PRINT ");
5161 repeat
5162 if isStringExpr(symbol) then
5163 param1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
5164 write(win, param1);
5165 write(log, literal(param1));
5166 elsif symbol = "TAB" then
5167 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5168 expect("(", symbol, line);
5169 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
5170 expect(")", symbol, line);
5171 if column(win) < round(num1) then
5172 write(win, "" rpad round(num1) - column(win));
5173 end if;
5174 write(log, "TAB(" <& round(num1) <& ")");
5175 elsif symbol = "SPC" then
5176 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5177 expect("(", symbol, line);
5178 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
5179 expect(")", symbol, line);
5180 write(win, "" rpad round(num1));
5181 write(log, "SPC(" <& round(num1) <& ")");
5182 elsif symbol = "USING" then
5183 exec_print_using(win, symbol, line);
5184 elsif symbol <> ";" and symbol <> "," and not endOfStatement(symbol) then
5185 write(win, " ");
5186 write(log, " ");
5187 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
5188 param1 := str(num1);
5189 if param1[length(param1) - 1 .. ] = ".0" then
5190 param1 := param1[ .. length(param1) - 2];
5191 end if;
5192 write(win, param1);
5193 write(log, num1);
5194 if not endOfStatement(symbol) then
5195 write(win, " ");
5196 write(log, " ");
5197 end if;
5198 end if;
5199 if endOfStatement(symbol) then
5200 writeln(win);
5201 if symbol = ":" then
5202 # A colon can be a statement separator or it encodes a line break.
5203 if continueWithPrintStatement(line) then
5204 # The PRINT statement continues after the line break (:).
5205 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5206 write(log, ":");
5207 while symbol = ":" do
5208 writeln(win);
5209 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5210 write(log, ":");
5211 end while;
5212 else
5213 # After the statement separator (:) comes the next statement.
5214 symbol := ":";
5215 end if;
5216 end if;
5217 elsif symbol = ";" then
5218 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5219 write(log, "; ");
5220 elsif symbol = "," then
5221 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5222 write(win, "" rpad 15 - column(win) rem 14);
5223 write(log, ", ");
5224 else
5225 # This is the next thing to be printed.
5226 if implicit_semicolon_pos <> length(line) then
5227 implicit_semicolon_pos := length(line);
5228 write(log, " (;) ");
5229 else
5230 writeln(log);
5231 error_marker;
5232 writeln(err, "IGNORE " <& literal(symbol));
5233 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5234 end if;
5235 end if;
5236 until endOfStatement(symbol);
5237 flush(win);
5238 writeln(log);
5239 end func;

5242const proc: exec_print (inout file: outFile,
5243 inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
5244 local
5245 var string: unused_name is "";
5246 var string: param1 is "";
5247 var float: num1 is 0.0;
5248 var integer: implicit_semicolon_pos is -1;
5249 begin
5250 if endOfStatement(symbol) then
5251 writeln(outFile);
5252 else
5253 repeat
5254 if isStringExpr(symbol) then
5255 param1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
5256 write(outFile, param1);
5257 write(log, literal(param1));
5258 elsif symbol = "TAB" then
5259 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5260 expect("(", symbol, line);
5261 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
5262 expect(")", symbol, line);
5263 write(outFile, " ");
5264 write(log, "TAB(" <& round(num1) <& ")");
5265 elsif symbol = "SPC" then
5266 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5267 expect("(", symbol, line);
5268 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
5269 expect(")", symbol, line);
5270 write(outFile, "" rpad round(num1));
5271 write(log, "SPC(" <& round(num1) <& ")");
5272 else
5273 write(outFile, " ");
5274 write(log, " ");
5275 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
5276 param1 := str(num1);
5277 if param1[length(param1) - 1 .. ] = ".0" then
5278 param1 := param1[ .. length(param1) - 2];
5279 end if;
5280 write(outFile, param1);
5281 write(log, num1);
5282 if not endOfStatement(symbol) then
5283 write(outFile, " ");
5284 write(log, " ");
5285 end if;
5286 end if;
5287 if endOfStatement(symbol) then
5288 writeln(outFile);
5289 elsif symbol = ";" then
5290 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5291 write(log, "; ");
5292 elsif symbol = "," then
5293 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5294 write(outFile, " ");
5295 write(log, ", ");
5296 else
5297 # This is the next thing to be printed.
5298 if implicit_semicolon_pos <> length(line) then
5299 implicit_semicolon_pos := length(line);
5300 write(log, " (;) ");
5301 else
5302 writeln(log);
5303 error_marker;
5304 writeln(err, "IGNORE " <& literal(symbol));
5305 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5306 end if;
5307 end if;
5308 until endOfStatement(symbol);
5309 end if;
5310 flush(outFile);
5311 writeln(log);
5312 end func;
5313
5314
5315const proc: exec_print_to_file (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
5316 local
5317 var integer: file_number is 0;
5318 var file: aFile is STD_NULL;
5319 begin
5320 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5321 file_number := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
5322 aFile := getFileValue(file_number);
5323 expect(",", symbol, line);
5324 if aFile <> STD_NULL then
5325 line_marker;
5326 write(log, "PRINT #" <& file_number <& ", ");
5327 if symbol = "USING" then
5328 exec_print_using(aFile, symbol, line);
5329 else
5330 exec_print(aFile, symbol, line);
5331 end if;
5332 elsif on_error_label <> "" then
5333 error_code := 52; # Bad file number
5334 line_marker;
5335 writeln(log, error_code <& " BAD FILE NUMBER #" <& file_number <&
5336 " - ON ERROR GOTO " <& on_error_label);
5337 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
5338 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5339 end while;
5340 goto_on_error(on_error_label, line);
5341 symbol := "";
5342 line := "";
5343 else
5344 error_marker;
5345 writeln(err, "BAD FILE NUMBER #" <& file_number <& " IN PRINT.");
5346 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
5347 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5348 end while;
5349 end if;
5350 end func;

5353const proc: exec_write_to_file (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
5354 local
5355 var integer: file_number is 0;
5356 var file: aFile is STD_NULL;
5357 var string: variable_name is "";
5358 var string: param1 is "";
5359 var float: num1 is 0.0;
5360 begin
5361 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5362 file_number := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
5363 aFile := getFileValue(file_number);
5364 if aFile <> STD_NULL then
5365 while symbol = "," do
5366 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5367 if isStringExpr(symbol) then
5368 param1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, variable_name);
5369 write(aFile, literal(param1));
5370 line_marker;
5371 writeln(log, "WRITE #" <& file_number <& ", " <& literal(param1));
5372 else
5373 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
5374 write(aFile, num1);
5375 line_marker;
5376 writeln(log, "WRITE #" <& file_number <& ", " <& num1);
5377 end if;
5378 if symbol = "," then
5379 write(aFile, ", ");
5380 end if;
5381 end while;
5382 writeln(aFile);
5383 flush(aFile);
5384 elsif on_error_label <> "" then
5385 error_code := 52; # Bad file number
5386 line_marker;
5387 writeln(log, error_code <& " BAD FILE NUMBER #" <& file_number <&
5388 " - ON ERROR GOTO " <& on_error_label);
5389 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
5390 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5391 end while;
5392 goto_on_error(on_error_label, line);
5393 symbol := "";
5394 line := "";
5395 else
5396 error_marker;
5397 writeln(err, "BAD FILE NUMBER #" <& file_number <& " IN WRITE.");
5398 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
5399 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5400 end while;
5401 end if;
5402 end func;

5405const proc: exec_write (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
5406 local
5407 var string: variable_name is "";
5408 var string: param1 is "";
5409 var float: num1 is 0.0;
5410 var boolean: finished is FALSE;
5411 begin
5412 if endOfStatement(symbol) then
5413 writeln(win);
5414 flush(win);
5415 writeln(log, "WRITE");
5416 else
5417 repeat
5418 if isStringExpr(symbol) then
5419 param1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, variable_name);
5420 write(win, literal(param1));
5421 line_marker;
5422 writeln(log, "WRITE " <& literal(param1));
5423 else
5424 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
5425 write(win, num1);
5426 line_marker;
5427 writeln(log, "WRITE " <& num1);
5428 end if;
5429 if symbol = "," then
5430 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5431 write(win, ", ");
5432 else
5433 finished := TRUE;
5434 end if;
5435 until finished;
5436 writeln(win);
5437 flush(win);
5438 end if;
5439 end func;

5441
5442const proc: exec_read (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
5443 local
5444 var string: variable_name is "";
5445 var string: data_elem is "";
5446 var string: param1 is "";
5447 var float: num1 is 0.0;
5448 begin
5449 repeat
5450 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5451 if isStringVar(symbol) then
5452 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
5453 param1 := get_data_field(symbol, line);
5454 if not in_error_handler then
5455 setStringVar(variable_name, param1);
5456 line_marker;
5457 write(log, "READ " <& variable_name <& " " <& literal(param1) <&
5458 " IN DATA LINE ");
5459 line_marker(data_line_number);
5460 writeln(log);
5461 end if;
5462 elsif isNumericVar(symbol) then
5463 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
5464 data_elem := trim(get_data_field(symbol, line));
5465 if not in_error_handler then
5466 if data_elem = "" then
5467 # Empty DATA fields can be read as 0.0.
5468 setNumericVar(variable_name, 0.0);
5469 line_marker;
5470 write(log, "READ " <& variable_name <& " 0.0 IN DATA LINE ");
5471 line_marker(data_line_number);
5472 writeln(log);
5473 else
5474 param1 := get_symbol(data_elem);
5475 if param1 = "-" then
5476 param1 &:= get_symbol(data_elem);
5477 elsif param1 = "+" then
5478 param1 := get_symbol(data_elem);
5479 end if;
5480 block
5481 num1 := float(param1);
5482 setNumericVar(variable_name, num1);
5483 line_marker;
5484 write(log, "READ " <& variable_name <& " " <& num1 <& " IN DATA LINE ");
5485 line_marker(data_line_number);
5486 writeln(log);
5487 exception
5488 catch RANGE_ERROR:
5489 error_marker;
5490 write(err, "NUMBER EXPECTED IN READ FOUND " <& literal(param1) <&
5491 " IN DATA LINE ");
5492 line_marker(data_line_number);
5493 writeln(err, ".");
5494 end block;
5495 if data_elem <> "" then
5496 error_marker;
5497 write(err, "FOUND " <& literal(data_elem) <& " AFTER " <&
5498 literal(param1) <& " IN DATA LINE ");
5499 line_marker(data_line_number);
5500 writeln(err, ".");
5501 end if;
5502 end if;
5503 end if;
5504 else
5505 error_marker;
5506 writeln(err, "VARIABLE EXPECTED - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
5507 end if;
5508 until symbol <> "," or in_error_handler;
5509 end func;

5511
5512const proc: exec_input_from_file (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
5513 local
5514 var integer: file_number is 0;
5515 var file: aFile is STD_NULL;
5516 var string: variable_name is "";
5517 var string: param1 is "";
5518 var float: num1 is 0.0;
5519 begin
5520 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5521 file_number := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
5522 aFile := getFileValue(file_number);
5523 if aFile <> STD_NULL then
5524 if eof(aFile) then
5525 aFile.bufferChar := EOF;
5526 elsif aFile.bufferChar = EOF then
5527 # Not eof() and buffer = EOF means the buffer is empty.
5528 aFile.bufferChar := getc(aFile);
5529 end if;
5530 while symbol = "," do
5531 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5532 skip_space_cr_lf(aFile);
5533 if isStringVar(symbol) then
5534 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
5535 param1 := read_input_string(aFile);
5536 setStringVar(variable_name, param1);
5537 line_marker;
5538 writeln(log, "INPUT #" <& file_number <& ", " <& variable_name <&
5539 " " <& literal(param1));
5540 elsif isNumericVar(symbol) then
5541 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
5542 param1 := read_input_number(aFile);
5543 block
5544 num1 := float(param1);
5545 setNumericVar(variable_name, num1);
5546 line_marker;
5547 writeln(log, "INPUT #" <& file_number <& ", " <& variable_name <&
5548 " " <& num1);
5549 exception
5550 catch RANGE_ERROR:
5551 error_marker;
5552 writeln(err, "NUMBER EXPECTED FOR INPUT OF " <& variable_name <&
5553 " FOUND " <& literal(param1) <& ".");
5554 end block;
5555 else
5556 error_marker;
5557 writeln(err, "VARIABLE EXPECTED - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
5558 end if;
5559 skipSpace(aFile);
5560 if aFile.bufferChar = ',' or aFile.bufferChar = '\r' then
5561 aFile.bufferChar := getc(aFile);
5562 end if;
5563 end while;
5564 elsif on_error_label <> "" then
5565 error_code := 52; # Bad file number
5566 line_marker;
5567 writeln(log, error_code <& " BAD FILE NUMBER #" <& file_number <&
5568 " - ON ERROR GOTO " <& on_error_label);
5569 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
5570 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5571 end while;
5572 goto_on_error(on_error_label, line);
5573 symbol := "";
5574 line := "";
5575 else
5576 error_marker;
5577 writeln(err, "BAD FILE NUMBER #" <& file_number <& " IN INPUT.");
5578 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
5579 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5580 end while;
5581 end if;
5582 end func;
5583
5584
5585const proc: read_input (inout file: inFile,
5586 inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
5587 local
5588 var string: variable_name is "";
5589 var string: param1 is "";
5590 begin
5591 while symbol = "," do
5592 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5593 skipSpace(inFile);
5594 if isStringVar(symbol) then
5595 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
5596 param1 := read_input_string(inFile);
5597 assign_input_string(variable_name, param1);
5598 elsif isNumericVar(symbol) then
5599 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
5600 param1 := read_input_number(inFile);
5601 assign_input_number(variable_name, param1);
5602 else
5603 error_marker;
5604 writeln(err, "VARIABLE EXPECTED - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
5605 end if;
5606 if inFile.bufferChar = ',' then
5607 inFile.bufferChar := getc(inFile);
5608 end if;
5609 end while;
5610 end func;

5613const proc: exec_input (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
5614 local
5615 var string: variable_name is "";
5616 var string: param1 is "";
5617 var string: param2 is "";
5618 begin
5619 if symbol = ";" then
5620 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5621 end if;
5622 if isStringExpr(symbol) then
5623 param1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, variable_name);
5624 if symbol = ";" or (variable_name = "" and (symbol = "," or symbol = ":")) then
5625 write(win, param1);
5626 line_marker;
5627 write(log, "INPUT " <& literal(param1));
5628 if symbol = ";" or symbol = ":" then
5629 if symbol = ";" then
5630 # Comma or colon are used to suppress the question mark.
5631 write(win, "? ");
5632 write(log, "? ");
5633 end if;
5634 symbol := ",";
5635 end if;
5636 flush(win);
5637 writeln(log);
5638 IN.bufferChar := getc(IN);
5639 read_input(IN, symbol, line);
5640 elsif variable_name <> "" then
5641 write(win, "? ");
5642 flush(win);
5643 line_marker;
5644 writeln(log, "INPUT ? " <& variable_name);
5645 IN.bufferChar := getc(IN);
5646 skipSpace(IN);
5647 param2 := read_input_string(IN);
5648 assign_input_string(variable_name, param2);
5649 if IN.bufferChar = ',' then
5650 IN.bufferChar := getc(IN);
5651 end if;
5652 read_input(IN, symbol, line);
5653 else
5654 error_expect2(";", ",", symbol);
5655 end if;
5656 elsif isNumericVar(symbol) then
5657 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
5658 write(win, "? ");
5659 flush(win);
5660 line_marker;
5661 writeln(log, "INPUT ? " <& variable_name);
5662 IN.bufferChar := getc(IN);
5663 skipSpace(IN);
5664 param1 := read_input_number(IN);
5665 assign_input_number(variable_name, param1);
5666 if IN.bufferChar = ',' then
5667 IN.bufferChar := getc(IN);
5668 end if;
5669 read_input(IN, symbol, line);
5670 else
5671 error_marker;
5672 writeln(err, "VARIABLE OR STRING EXPECTED - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
5673 end if;
5674 end func;

5819const proc: exec_linput (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
5820 local
5821 var string: variable_name is "";
5822 var string: param1 is "";
5823 var string: param2 is "";
5824 begin
5825 if isStringExpr(symbol) then
5826 param1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, variable_name);
5827 if symbol = ":" then
5828 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5829 write(win, param1);
5830 flush(win);
5831 if isStringVar(symbol) then
5832 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
5833 line_marker;
5834 write(log, "LINPUT " <& literal(param1) <& ": " <& variable_name);
5835 flush(log);
5836 readln(param2);
5837 writeln(win);
5838 flush(win);
5839 setStringVar(variable_name, param2);
5840 writeln(log, " <- " <& literal(param2));
5841 else
5842 error_marker;
5843 writeln(err, "STRING VARIABLE EXPECTED FOR LINPUT - FOUND " <&
5844 symbol <& ".");
5845 end if;
5846 elsif variable_name <> "" then
5847 write(win, "? ");
5848 flush(win);
5849 line_marker;
5850 write(log, "LINPUT " <& variable_name);
5851 flush(log);
5852 readln(param2);
5853 writeln(win);
5854 flush(win);
5855 setStringVar(variable_name, param2);
5856 writeln(log, " <- " <& literal(param2));
5857 else
5858 error_expect(":", symbol);
5859 end if;
5860 else
5861 error_marker;
5862 writeln(err, "STRING EXPECTED FOR LINPUT - FOUND " <&
5863 symbol <& ".");
5864 end if;
5865 end func;

5868const proc: exec_display (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
5869 local
5870 const set of string: display_keywords is {"AT", "BEEP", "ERASE", "SIZE"};
5871 var integer: row is 0;
5872 var integer: column is 0;
5873 var integer: count is 0;
5874 var string: unused_name is "";
5875 var string: param1 is "";
5876 var float: num1 is 0.0;
5877 var boolean: finished is FALSE;
5878 begin
5879 line_marker;
5880 write(log, "DISPLAY ");
5881 if symbol in display_keywords then
5882 repeat
5883 if symbol = "AT" then
5884 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5885 expect("(", symbol, line);
5886 row := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
5887 expect(",", symbol, line);
5888 column := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
5889 expect(")", symbol, line);
5890 write(log, "AT(" <& row <& ", " <& column <& ") ");
5891 setPos(win, row, column);
5892 end if;
5893 if symbol = "BEEP" then
5894 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5895 write(log, "DISPLAY **BEEP ");
5896 end if;
5897 if symbol = "ERASE" then
5898 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5899 expect("ALL", symbol, line);
5900 clear(win);
5901 write(log, "ERASE ALL ");
5902 end if;
5903 if symbol = "SIZE" then
5904 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5905 expect("(", symbol, line);
5906 count := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
5907 expect(")", symbol, line);
5908 write(win, " " mult count);
5909 write(win, "\b" mult count);
5910 write(log, "SIZE(" <& count <& ") ");
5911 end if;
5912 until symbol not in display_keywords;
5913 expect(":", symbol, line);
5914 write(log, ": ");
5915 end if;
5916 repeat
5917 if isStringExpr(symbol) then
5918 param1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
5919 write(win, literal(param1));
5920 write(log, literal(param1));
5921 else
5922 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
5923 write(win, num1);
5924 write(log, num1);
5925 end if;
5926 if symbol = "," then
5927 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5928 write(log, ", ");
5929 elsif symbol = ";" then
5930 symbol := get_symbol(line);
5931 write(log, "; ");
5932 else
5933 finished := TRUE;
5934 end if;
5935 until finished;
5936 writeln(log);
5937 end func;

5939
5940const func file: basicOpen (in var string: filePath, in string: access) is func
5941 result
5942 var file: fileOpened is STD_NULL;
5943 local
5944 var array string: pathElems is 0 times "";
5945 var integer: startElem is 1;
5946 var integer: number is 0;
5947 var array string: directoryContent is 0 times "";
5948 var string: directoryElement is "";
5949 var boolean: foundTwice is FALSE;
5950 var string: foundElement is "";
5951 var boolean: path_okay is TRUE;
5952 var string: path is "";
5953 begin
5954 # writeln("basicOpen(\"" <& filePath <& "\")");
5955 if filePath <> "" then
5956 filePath := convDosPath(filePath);
5957 pathElems := split(filePath, '/');
5958 if length(pathElems) >= 1 and pathElems[1] = "" then
5959 # absolute path
5960 path := "/";
5961 startElem := 2;
5962 else
5963 # relative path
5964 path := getcwd;
5965 startElem := 1;
5966 end if;
5967 for number range startElem to length(pathElems) do
5968 # writeln(log, literal(path) <& " " <& literal(pathElems[number]));
5969 if fileType(path & "/" & pathElems[number]) <> FILE_ABSENT then
5970 path &:= "/" & pathElems[number];
5971 elsif fileType(path) = FILE_DIR then
5972 directoryContent := readDir(path);
5973 foundTwice := FALSE;
5974 foundElement := "";
5975 for directoryElement range directoryContent do
5976 if upper(pathElems[number]) = upper(directoryElement) then
5977 if foundElement = "" then
5978 foundElement := directoryElement;
5979 else
5980 foundTwice := TRUE;
5981 end if;
5982 end if;
5983 end for;
5984 if foundElement <> "" and not foundTwice and
5985 fileType(path & "/" & foundElement) <> FILE_ABSENT then
5986 path &:= "/" & foundElement;
5987 elsif access[1 len 1] <> "r" then
5988 path &:= "/" & pathElems[number];
5989 else
5990 path_okay := FALSE;
5991 end if;
5992 else
5993 path_okay := FALSE;
5994 end if;
5995 end for;
5996 else
5997 path_okay := FALSE;
5998 end if;
5999 if path_okay then
6000 fileOpened := open(path, access);
6001 # Set buffer to empty:
6002 fileOpened.bufferChar := EOF;
6003 end if;
6004 end func;
6005
6006
6007const proc: exec_open (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
6008 local
6009 var string: unused_name is "";
6010 var string: param1 is "";
6011 var string: param2 is "";
6012 var string: param_for is "";
6013 var string: param_access is "";
6014 var string: mode is "";
6015 var string: file_name is "";
6016 var integer: index1 is 0;
6017 var file: aFile is STD_NULL;
6018 begin
6019 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6020 param1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
6021 if symbol = "FOR" then
6022 param_for := get_symbol(line);
6023 if param_for = "INPUT" then
6024 mode := "r";
6025 elsif param_for = "OUTPUT" then
6026 mode := "w";
6027 elsif param_for = "APPEND" then
6028 mode := "a";
6029 elsif param_for = "RANDOM" then
6030 mode := "r+";
6031 elsif param_for = "BINARY" then
6032 mode := "r+";
6033 else
6034 mode := "r";
6035 error_marker;
6036 writeln(err, "ILLEGAL - OPEN FOR " <& param_for);
6037 end if;
6038 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6039 else
6040 mode := "r+";
6041 end if;
6042 if symbol = "ACCESS" then
6043 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6044 if symbol = "READ" then
6045 param_access := symbol;
6046 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6047 end if;
6048 if symbol = "WRITE" then
6049 if param_access <> "" then
6050 param_access &:= " ";
6051 end if;
6052 param_access &:= symbol;
6053 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6054 end if;
6055 end if;
6056 if symbol = "SHARED" then
6057 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6058 elsif symbol = "LOCK" then
6059 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6060 if symbol = "READ" then
6061 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6062 end if;
6063 if symbol = "WRITE" then
6064 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6065 end if;
6066 end if;
6067 if symbol = "AS" or symbol = "AS#" then
6068 if symbol = "AS#" then
6069 symbol := "#";
6070 else
6071 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6072 end if;
6073 if symbol = "#" then
6074 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6075 end if;
6076 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
6077 if symbol = "LEN" then
6078 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6079 expect("=", symbol, line);
6080 reclen_value[index1] := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
6081 else
6082 reclen_value[index1] := 0;
6083 end if;
6084 file_name := param1;
6085 aFile := basicOpen(file_name, mode);
6086 if aFile = STD_NULL and param_access = "" and
6087 (param_for = "" or param_for = "RANDOM" or param_for = "BINARY") then
6088 mode := "w+"; # Try to open a new file with read/write mode
6089 aFile := basicOpen(file_name, mode);
6090 if aFile = STD_NULL then
6091 mode := "w"; # Try to open a new file with write-only mode
6092 aFile := basicOpen(file_name, mode);
6093 if aFile = STD_NULL then
6094 mode := "r"; # Try to open a new file with read-only mode
6095 aFile := basicOpen(file_name, mode);
6096 end if;
6097 end if;
6098 end if;
6099 if aFile <> STD_NULL then
6100 setFileValue(index1, aFile);
6101 end if;
6102 line_marker;
6103 write(log, "OPEN " <& param1);
6104 if param_for <> "" then
6105 write(log, " FOR " <& param_for);
6106 end if;
6107 if param_access <> "" then
6108 write(log, " ACCESS " <& param_access);
6109 end if;
6110 writeln(log, " AS #" <& index1 <&
6111 " - open(" <& literal(file_name) <& ", " <& literal(mode) <& ")");
6112 else
6113 if param1 <> "" then
6114 if param1[.. 1] = "I" then
6115 mode := "r";
6116 elsif param1[.. 1] = "O" then
6117 mode := "w";
6118 elsif param1[.. 1] = "R" then
6119 mode := "r+";
6120 elsif param1[.. 1] = "B" then
6121 mode := "r+";
6122 end if;
6123 end if;
6124 if mode = "" then
6125 mode := "r";
6126 error_marker;
6127 writeln(err, "ILLEGAL - OPEN " <& param1);
6128 end if;
6129 expect(",", symbol, line);
6130 if symbol = "#" then
6131 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6132 end if;
6133 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
6134 expect(",", symbol, line);
6135 param2 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
6136 file_name := param2;
6137 line_marker;
6138 aFile := basicOpen(file_name, mode);
6139 if aFile <> STD_NULL then
6140 setFileValue(index1, aFile);
6141 end if;
6142 if symbol = "," then
6143 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6144 reclen_value[index1] := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
6145 else
6146 reclen_value[index1] := 0;
6147 end if;
6148 line_marker;
6149 write(log, "OPEN " <& literal(param1) <& ", #" <& index1 <&
6150 ", " <& literal(param2));
6151 writeln(log, " - open(" <& literal(file_name) <& ", " <& literal(mode) <& ")");
6152 end if;
6153 if aFile = STD_NULL then
6154 if on_error_label <> "" then
6155 error_code := 53; # File not found
6156 line_marker;
6157 writeln(log, error_code <& " FILE NOT FOUND " <& literal(file_name) <&
6158 " - ON ERROR GOTO " <& on_error_label);
6159 goto_on_error(on_error_label, line);
6160 symbol := "";
6161 line := "";
6162 else
6163 error_marker;
6164 writeln(err, "FILE NOT FOUND " <& literal(file_name));
6165 end if;
6166 end if;
6167 end func;

6169
6170const proc: exec_close (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
6171 local
6172 var integer: file_number is 0;
6173 var file: aFile is STD_NULL;
6174 var boolean: okay is FALSE;
6175 begin
6176 if symbol = "CLOSE#" then
6177 symbol := "#";
6178 else
6179 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6180 end if;
6181 if endOfStatement(symbol) then
6182 closeAllFiles;
6183 line_marker;
6184 writeln(log, "CLOSE");
6185 else
6186 repeat
6187 if symbol = "#" then
6188 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6189 end if;
6190 file_number := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
6191 aFile := getFileValue(file_number);
6192 if aFile <> STD_NULL then
6193 close(aFile);
6194 setFileValue(file_number, STD_NULL);
6195 line_marker;
6196 writeln(log, "CLOSE #" <& file_number);
6197 else
6198 line_marker;
6199 writeln(log, "CLOSE #" <& file_number <& " - FILE ALREADY CLOSED.");
6200 end if;
6201 if symbol = "," then
6202 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6203 else
6204 okay := TRUE;
6205 end if;
6206 until okay;
6207 end if;
6208 end func;

6211const proc: exec_file_put (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
6212 local
6213 var integer: file_number is 0;
6214 var file: outFile is STD_NULL;
6215 var integer: position is 0;
6216 var boolean: with_position is FALSE;
6217 var integer: reclen is 0;
6218 var string: variable_name is "";
6219 var string: field is "";
6220 begin
6221 if symbol = "#" then
6222 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6223 end if;
6224 file_number := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
6225 outFile := getFileValue(file_number);
6226 if outFile <> STD_NULL then
6227 if symbol = "," then
6228 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6229 if symbol <> "," and not endOfStatement(symbol) then
6230 position := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
6231 with_position := TRUE;
6232 end if;
6233 if symbol = "," then
6234 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6235 if isStringVar(symbol) then
6236 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
6237 end if;
6238 end if;
6239 end if;
6240 if with_position then
6241 if position >= 1 then
6242 if reclen_value[file_number] <> 0 then
6243 reclen := reclen_value[file_number];
6244 else
6245 if length(field_value[file_number]) >= 1 then
6246 reclen := 0;
6247 for field range field_value[file_number] do
6248 reclen +:= length(getStringVar(field));
6249 end for;
6250 error_marker;
6251 writeln(err, "PUT #" <& file_number <&
6252 " FILE HAS NO RECORD LENGTH SPECIFIED - USE THE FIELD SIZE: " <& reclen);
6253 elsif variable_name <> "" then
6254 reclen := length(getStringVar(variable_name));
6255 error_marker;
6256 writeln(err, "PUT #" <& file_number <&
6257 " FILE HAS NO RECORD LENGTH SPECIFIED - USE THE SIZE OF THE VARIABLE: " <& reclen);
6258 else
6259 reclen := 0;
6260 error_marker;
6261 writeln(err, "PUT #" <& file_number <&
6262 " FILE HAS NO RECORD LENGTH SPECIFIED - POSITION IGNORED");
6263 end if;
6264 end if;
6265 if reclen <> 0 then
6266 seek(outFile, succ(pred(position) * reclen));
6267 end if;
6268 else
6269 error_marker;
6270 writeln(err, "PUT #" <& file_number <&
6271 " WITH A RECORD NUMBER OF " <& position);
6272 end if;
6273 end if;
6274 if length(field_value[file_number]) >= 1 then
6275 for field range field_value[file_number] do
6276 write(outFile, getStringVar(field));
6277 end for;
6278 elsif variable_name <> "" then
6279 write(outFile, getStringVar(variable_name));
6280 else
6281 error_marker;
6282 writeln(err, "PUT #" <& file_number <&
6283 " - NO STRING VARIABLE PRESENT");
6284 end if;
6285 line_marker;
6286 write(log, "PUT #" <& file_number <& ", ");
6287 if with_position then
6288 write(log, position);
6289 end if;
6290 if length(field_value[file_number]) >= 1 then
6291 for field range field_value[file_number] do
6292 write(log, ", " <& field <& "=" <&
6293 literal(getStringVar(field)));
6294 end for;
6295 elsif variable_name <> "" then
6296 write(log, ", " <& variable_name <& "=" <&
6297 literal(getStringVar(variable_name)));
6298 end if;
6299 writeln(log);
6300 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
6301 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6302 end while
6303 elsif on_error_label <> "" then
6304 error_code := 52; # Bad file number
6305 line_marker;
6306 writeln(log, error_code <& " BAD FILE NUMBER #" <& file_number <&
6307 " - ON ERROR GOTO " <& on_error_label);
6308 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
6309 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6310 end while;
6311 goto_on_error(on_error_label, line);
6312 symbol := "";
6313 line := "";
6314 else
6315 error_marker;
6316 writeln(err, "BAD FILE NUMBER #" <& file_number <& " IN PUT.");
6317 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
6318 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6319 end while;
6320 end if;
6321 end func;

6324const proc: exec_file_get (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
6325 local
6326 var integer: file_number is 0;
6327 var file: inFile is STD_NULL;
6328 var integer: position is 0;
6329 var boolean: with_position is FALSE;
6330 var integer: reclen is 0;
6331 var string: variable_name is "";
6332 var string: field is "";
6333 begin
6334 if symbol = "#" then
6335 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6336 end if;
6337 file_number := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
6338 inFile := getFileValue(file_number);
6339 if inFile <> STD_NULL then
6340 if symbol = "," then
6341 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6342 if symbol <> "," and not endOfStatement(symbol) then
6343 position := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
6344 with_position := TRUE;
6345 end if;
6346 if symbol = "," then
6347 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6348 if isStringVar(symbol) then
6349 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
6350 end if;
6351 end if;
6352 end if;
6353 if with_position then
6354 if position >= 1 then
6355 if reclen_value[file_number] <> 0 then
6356 reclen := reclen_value[file_number];
6357 else
6358 if length(field_value[file_number]) >= 1 then
6359 reclen := 0;
6360 for field range field_value[file_number] do
6361 reclen +:= length(getStringVar(field));
6362 end for;
6363 error_marker;
6364 writeln(err, "GET #" <& file_number <&
6365 " FILE HAS NO RECORD LENGTH SPECIFIED - USE THE FIELD SIZE: " <& reclen);
6366 elsif variable_name <> "" then
6367 reclen := length(getStringVar(variable_name));
6368 error_marker;
6369 writeln(err, "GET #" <& file_number <&
6370 " FILE HAS NO RECORD LENGTH SPECIFIED - USE THE SIZE OF THE VARIABLE: " <& reclen);
6371 else
6372 reclen := 0;
6373 error_marker;
6374 writeln(err, "GET #" <& file_number <&
6375 " FILE HAS NO RECORD LENGTH SPECIFIED - POSITION IGNORED");
6376 end if;
6377 end if;
6378 if reclen <> 0 then
6379 # writeln(log, "seek(succ(prd(" <& position <& ") * " <& reclen <& ")) " <&
6380 # succ(pred(position) * reclen));
6381 seek(inFile, succ(pred(position) * reclen));
6382 end if;
6383 else
6384 error_marker;
6385 writeln(err, "GET #" <& file_number <&
6386 " WITH A RECORD NUMBER OF " <& position);
6387 end if;
6388 end if;
6389 if length(field_value[file_number]) >= 1 then
6390 for field range field_value[file_number] do
6391 setStringVar(field, gets(inFile, length(getStringVar(field))));
6392 end for;
6393 elsif variable_name <> "" then
6394 setStringVar(variable_name, gets(inFile,
6395 length(getStringVar(variable_name))));
6396 else
6397 error_marker;
6398 writeln(err, "GET #" <& file_number <&
6399 " - NO STRING VARIABLE PRESENT");
6400 end if;
6401 line_marker;
6402 write(log, "GET #" <& file_number <& ", ");
6403 if with_position then
6404 write(log, position);
6405 end if;
6406 if length(field_value[file_number]) >= 1 then
6407 for field range field_value[file_number] do
6408 write(log, ", " <& field <& "=" <& literal(getStringVar(field)));
6409 end for;
6410 elsif variable_name <> "" then
6411 write(log, ", " <& variable_name <& "=" <& literal(getStringVar(variable_name)));
6412 end if;
6413 writeln(log);
6414 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
6415 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6416 end while
6417 elsif on_error_label <> "" then
6418 error_code := 52; # Bad file number
6419 line_marker;
6420 writeln(log, error_code <& " BAD FILE NUMBER #" <& file_number <&
6421 " - ON ERROR GOTO " <& on_error_label);
6422 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
6423 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6424 end while;
6425 goto_on_error(on_error_label, line);
6426 symbol := "";
6427 line := "";
6428 else
6429 error_marker;
6430 writeln(err, "BAD FILE NUMBER #" <& file_number <& " IN GET.");
6431 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
6432 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6433 end while;
6434 end if;
6435 end func;

6466 " - ON ERROR GOTO " <& on_error_label);
6467 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
6468 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6469 end while;
6470 goto_on_error(on_error_label, line);
6471 symbol := "";
6472 line := "";
6473 else
6474 error_marker;
6475 writeln(err, "BAD FILE NUMBER #" <& file_number <& " IN SEEK.");
6476 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
6477 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6478 end while;
6479 end if;
6480 end func;

6489 def_fn_list := def_fn_hash.EMPTY_HASH;
6490 defstr_var := (set of char).EMPTY_SET;
6491 data_line_number := 0;

6493 end func;

6508const func string: parseType (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
6509 result
6510 var string: typeName is "";
6511 begin
6512 typeName := get_symbol(line);
6513 if typeName = "SHARED" then
6514 typeName := get_symbol(line);
6515 end if;
6516 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6517 end func;

6520const proc: initArray (in var string: arrayName, in boolean: isStringVar,
6521 in integer: dimension, in dimensionType: dimensionBounds) is func
6522 local
6523 var integer: index is 0;
6524 begin
6525 if dimension <= length(dimensionBounds) then
6526 if dimension = 1 then
6527 arrayName &:= "(";
6528 else
6529 arrayName &:= ",";
6530 end if;
6531 for index range dimensionBounds[dimension].lbound to dimensionBounds[dimension].ubound do
6532 if dimension = length(dimensionBounds) then
6533 if isStringVar then
6534 setStringVar(arrayName & str(index) & ")", "");
6535 else
6536 setNumericVar(arrayName & str(index) & ")", 0.0);
6537 end if;
6538 else
6539 initArray(arrayName & str(index), isStringVar, succ(dimension), dimensionBounds);
6540 end if;
6541 end for;
6542 end if;
6543 end func;
6544
6545
6546const proc: exec_dim (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
6547 local
6548 var string: variableName is "";
6549 var dimensionType: dimensionBounds is 0 times boundsType.value;
6550 var boundsType: bounds is boundsType.value;
6551 var string: typeName is "";
6552 var integer: dimension is 0;
6553 var boolean: finished is FALSE;
6554 begin
6555 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6556 if symbol = "SHARED" then
6557 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6558 end if;
6559 repeat
6560 if symbol[1] >= 'A' and symbol[1] <= 'Z' then
6561 variableName := symbol;
6562 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6563 if symbol = "(" or symbol = "[" then
6564 dimensionBounds := 0 times boundsType.value;
6565 repeat
6566 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6567 bounds.ubound := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
6568 if symbol = "TO" then
6569 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6570 bounds.lbound := bounds.ubound;
6571 bounds.ubound := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
6572 else
6573 bounds.lbound := 0;
6574 end if;
6575 dimensionBounds &:= [] (bounds);
6576 until symbol <> ",";
6577 if symbol =")" or symbol = "]" then
6578 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6579 if symbol = "AS" then
6580 typeName := parseType(symbol, line);
6581 if typeName = "STRING" then
6582 incl(string_var_name, variableName);
6583 end if;
6584 else
6585 typeName := "";
6586 end if;
6587 initArray(variableName, isStringVar(variableName), 1, dimensionBounds);
6588 # writeln(log, "addr=" <& varptr(variableName) <& " name=" <& variableName);
6589 ignore(varptr(variableName));
6590 line_marker;
6591 write(log, "DIM " <& variableName <& "(");
6592 for dimension range 1 to length(dimensionBounds) do
6593 if dimension <> 1 then
6594 write(log, ", ");
6595 end if;
6596 write(log, dimensionBounds[dimension].lbound <& " TO " <&
6597 dimensionBounds[dimension].ubound);
6598 end for;
6599 write(log, ")");
6600 if typeName <> "" then
6601 write(log, " AS " <& typeName);
6602 end if;
6603 writeln(log);
6604 end if;
6605 else
6606 if symbol = "AS" then
6607 typeName := parseType(symbol, line);
6608 if typeName = "STRING" then
6609 incl(string_var_name, variableName);
6610 end if;
6611 else
6612 typeName := "";
6613 end if;
6614 line_marker;
6615 write(log, "DIM " <& variableName);
6616 if typeName <> "" then
6617 write(log, " AS " <& typeName);
6618 end if;
6619 writeln(log);
6620 end if;
6621 end if;
6622 if symbol = "," then
6623 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6624 else
6625 finished := TRUE;
6626 end if;
6627 until finished;
6628 end func;

6631const proc: exec_defType_numeric (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
6632 local
6633 var string: statement is "";
6634 var string: param1 is "";
6635 var string: param2 is "";
6636 var char: ch1 is ' ';
6637 var boolean: okay is FALSE;
6638 begin
6639 statement := symbol;
6640 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6641 okay := FALSE;
6642 repeat
6643 if length(symbol) = 1 and symbol >= "A" and symbol <= "Z" then
6644 param1 := symbol;
6645 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6646 if symbol = "-" then
6647 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6648 if length(symbol) = 1 and symbol >= param1 and symbol <= "Z" then
6649 param2 := symbol;
6650 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6651 for ch1 range param1[1] to param2[1] do
6652 excl(defstr_var, ch1);
6653 end for;
6654 line_marker;
6655 writeln(log, statement <& " " <& param1 <& "-" <& param2);
6656 else
6657 error_marker;
6658 writeln(err, "ILLEGAL " <& statement <& " " <& param1 <& "-" <& symbol);
6659 end if;
6660 else
6661 excl(defstr_var, param1[1]);
6662 line_marker;
6663 writeln(log, statement <& " " <& param1);
6664 end if;
6665 else
6666 error_marker;
6667 writeln(err, "ILLEGAL " <& statement <& " " <& symbol);
6668 end if;
6669 if symbol = "," then
6670 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6671 else
6672 okay := TRUE;
6673 end if;
6674 until okay;
6675 end func;

6678const proc: exec_defstr (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
6679 local
6680 var string: param1 is "";
6681 var string: param2 is "";
6682 var char: ch1 is ' ';
6683 var boolean: okay is FALSE;
6684 begin
6685 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6686 defstr_var := (set of char).EMPTY_SET;
6687 okay := FALSE;
6688 repeat
6689 if length(symbol) = 1 and symbol >= "A" and symbol <= "Z" then
6690 param1 := symbol;
6691 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6692 if symbol = "-" then
6693 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6694 if length(symbol) = 1 and symbol >= param1 and symbol <= "Z" then
6695 param2 := symbol;
6696 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6697 for ch1 range param1[1] to param2[1] do
6698 incl(defstr_var, ch1);
6699 end for;
6700 line_marker;
6701 writeln(log, "DEFSTR " <& param1 <& "-" <& param2);
6702 else
6703 error_marker;
6704 writeln(err, "ILLEGAL DEFSTR " <& param1 <& "-" <& symbol);
6705 end if;
6706 else
6707 incl(defstr_var, param1[1]);
6708 line_marker;
6709 writeln(log, "DEFSTR " <& param1);
6710 end if;
6711 else
6712 error_marker;
6713 writeln(err, "ILLEGAL DEFSTR " <& symbol);
6714 end if;
6715 if symbol = "," then
6716 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6717 else
6718 okay := TRUE;
6719 end if;
6720 until okay;
6721 end func;

6724const proc: exec_type (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
6725 begin
6726 symbol := next_symbol(line);
6727 line_marker;
6728 writeln(log, "**TYPE " <& symbol);
6729 while symbol <> "END" and symbol <> "" do
6730 if ignoreRestOfLine(symbol) then
6731 line := "";
6732 end if;
6733 symbol := next_symbol(line);
6734 end while;
6735 if symbol = "END" then
6736 repeat
6737 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6738 until symbol <> "END";
6739 if ignoreRestOfLine(symbol) then
6740 line := "";
6741 end if;
6742 if symbol <> "TYPE" then
6743 exec_type(symbol, line);
6744 else
6745 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6746 end if;
6747 end if;
6748 end func;

6751const func string: readVarNameFromBloadFile (inout file: aFile, inout integer: byteIndex) is func
6752 result
6753 var string: bloadName is "";
6754 local
6755 var integer: twoTimes is 0;
6756 var integer: number is 0;
6757 var integer: count is 0;
6758 var char: ch is ' ';
6759 begin
6760 for twoTimes range 1 to 2 do
6761 number := ord(getc(aFile));
6762 for count range 1 to number do
6763 ch := getc(aFile);
6764 incr(byteIndex);
6765 if ch >= '\128;' then
6766 ch := chr(ord(ch) - 128);
6767 end if;
6768 bloadName &:= str(ch);
6769 end for;
6770 end for;
6771 end func;

6774const proc: exec_bload (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
6775 local
6776 var string: unused_name is "";
6777 var string: file_name is "";
6778 var string: variable_name is "";
6779 var string: arrayName is "";
6780 var string: bloadName is "";
6781 var integer: address is 0;
6782 var file: aFile is STD_NULL;
6783 var integer: sizeInBytes is 0;
6784 var integer: byteIndex is 0;
6785 var string: name_start is "";
6786 var string: name_end is "";
6787 var integer: lbound is 0;
6788 var integer: ubound is 0;
6789 var integer: intIndex is 0;
6790 var integer: number is 0;
6791 begin
6792 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6793 file_name := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
6794 if symbol = "," then
6795 symbol := get_symbol(line);
6796 address := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
6797 variable_name := varname(address);
6798 end if;
6799 if variable_name = "" then
6800 variable_name := varseg_variable;
6801 end if;
6802 if variable_name <> "" then
6803 lbound := getFirstIndex(variable_name, name_start, name_end);
6804 if name_start = "" then
6805 arrayName := variable_name;
6806 lbound := exec_lbound(arrayName, 1);
6807 ubound := exec_ubound(arrayName, 1);
6808 name_start := arrayName & "(";
6809 name_end := ")";
6810 else
6811 arrayName := name_start[ .. pred(length(name_start))];
6812 ubound := exec_ubound(arrayName, 1);
6813 end if;
6814 intIndex := lbound;
6815 # writeln(log, "arrayName=" <& arrayName);
6816 # writeln(log, "lbound=" <& lbound);
6817 # writeln(log, "ubound=" <& ubound);
6818 # writeln(log, "name_start=" <& name_start);
6819 # writeln(log, "name_end=" <& name_end);
6820 aFile := basicOpen(file_name, "r");
6821 if aFile <> STD_NULL then
6822 if getc(aFile) = '\16#FD;' then
6823 ignore(gets(aFile, 4));
6824 sizeInBytes := ord(getc(aFile)) + 256 * ord(getc(aFile));
6825 writeln(log, "sizeInBytes=" <& sizeInBytes);
6826 for byteIndex range 0 to pred(sizeInBytes) step 2 do
6827 if intIndex > ubound then
6828 # writeln(log, "varptr(arrayName)=" <& varptr(arrayName));
6829 arrayName := varname(succ(varptr(arrayName)));
6830 lbound := exec_lbound(arrayName, 1);
6831 ubound := exec_ubound(arrayName, 1);
6832 name_start := arrayName & "(";
6833 name_end := ")";
6834 intIndex := lbound;
6835 # writeln(log, "arrayName=" <& arrayName);
6836 # writeln(log, "lbound=" <& lbound);
6837 # writeln(log, "ubound=" <& ubound);
6838 # writeln(log, "name_start=" <& name_start);
6839 # writeln(log, "name_end=" <& name_end);
6840 # writeln(log, "byteIndex=" <& byteIndex);
6841 bloadName := readVarNameFromBloadFile(aFile, byteIndex);
6842 # writeln(log, literal(gets(aFile, 5)));
6843 ignore(literal(gets(aFile, 5)));
6844 byteIndex +:= 5;
6845 if bloadName <> arrayName then
6846 byteIndex := sizeInBytes;
6847 end if;
6848 end if;
6849 number := ord(getc(aFile)) + 256 * ord(getc(aFile));
6850 setNumericVar(name_start & str(intIndex) & name_end, flt(number));
6851 # writeln(log, name_start & str(intIndex) & name_end <& "=" <& flt(number));
6852 incr(intIndex);
6853 end for;
6854 end if;
6855 close(aFile);
6856 else
6857 if on_error_label <> "" then
6858 error_code := 53; # File not found
6859 line_marker;
6860 writeln(log, error_code <& " FILE NOT FOUND " <& literal(file_name) <&
6861 " - ON ERROR GOTO " <& on_error_label);
6862 goto_on_error(on_error_label, line);
6863 symbol := "";
6864 line := "";
6865 else
6866 error_marker;
6867 writeln(err, "FILE NOT FOUND " <& literal(file_name));
6868 end if;
6869 end if;
6870 end if;
6871 line_marker;
6872 writeln(log, "BLOAD " <& literal(file_name) <& ", VARPTR(" <& variable_name <& ")");
6873 end func;

6879 var string: unused_name is "";
6880 var string: fileName is ""

6894 end func;

6897const func PRIMITIVE_WINDOW: getCga2ImageFromBytes (in string: bytes) is func
6898 result
6899 var PRIMITIVE_WINDOW: image is PRIMITIVE_WINDOW.value;
6900 local
6901 var integer: width is 0;
6902 var integer: height is 0;
6903 var integer: bytesPerLine is 0;
6904 var integer: lineStartByte is 0;
6905 var integer: xPos is 0;
6906 var integer: yPos is 0;
6907 var integer: byteIndex is 0;
6908 var integer: imageByte is 0;
6909 var integer: colorNum is 0;
6910 begin
6911 if bytes <> "" then
6912 width := bytes2Int(bytes[1 fixLen 2], UNSIGNED, LE);
6913 height := bytes2Int(bytes[3 fixLen 2], UNSIGNED, LE);
6914 # writeln(log, "width=" <& width <& " height=" <& height);
6915 image := newPixmap(width, height);
6916 bytesPerLine := pred(width) mdiv 8 + 1;
6917 for yPos range 0 to pred(height) do
6918 lineStartByte := yPos * bytesPerLine;
6919 for xPos range 0 to pred(width) do
6920 colorNum := 0;
6921 byteIndex := lineStartByte + xPos mdiv 8;
6922 imageByte := ord(bytes[5 + byteIndex]);
6923 if (imageByte >> (7 - xPos mod 8)) mod 2 = 1 then
6924 point(image, xPos, yPos, white);
6925 else
6926 point(image, xPos, yPos, black);
6927 end if;
6928 end for;
6929 end for;
6930 end if;
6931 end func;
6932
6933
6934const func PRIMITIVE_WINDOW: getCga4ImageFromBytes (in string: bytes) is func
6935 result
6936 var PRIMITIVE_WINDOW: image is PRIMITIVE_WINDOW.value;
6937 local
6938 var integer: width is 0;
6939 var integer: height is 0;
6940 var integer: bytesPerLine is 0;
6941 var integer: lineStartByte is 0;
6942 var integer: xPos is 0;
6943 var integer: yPos is 0;
6944 var integer: byteIndex is 0;
6945 var integer: imageByte is 0;
6946 var integer: colorNum is 0;
6947 const array color: palette1 is [] (black, light_green, light_red, brown);
6948 begin
6949 if bytes <> "" then
6950 width := bytes2Int(bytes[1 fixLen 2], UNSIGNED, LE);
6951 height := bytes2Int(bytes[3 fixLen 2], UNSIGNED, LE);
6952 # writeln(log, "width=" <& width <& " height=" <& height);
6953 width := width div 2;
6954 image := newPixmap(width, height);
6955 bytesPerLine := pred(width) mdiv 4 + 1;
6956 for yPos range 0 to pred(height) do
6957 lineStartByte := yPos * bytesPerLine;
6958 for xPos range 0 to pred(width) do
6959 colorNum := 0;
6960 byteIndex := lineStartByte + xPos mdiv 4;
6961 imageByte := ord(bytes[5 + byteIndex]);
6962 colorNum := (imageByte >> (6 - xPos mod 4 * 2)) mod 4;
6963 point(image, xPos, yPos, palette1[succ(colorNum)]);
6964 end for;
6965 end for;
6966 end if;
6967 end func;

6970const func PRIMITIVE_WINDOW: getEgaImageFromBytes (in string: bytes) is func
6971 result
6972 var PRIMITIVE_WINDOW: image is PRIMITIVE_WINDOW.value;
6973 local
6974 var integer: width is 0;
6975 var integer: height is 0;
6976 var integer: bytesPerLine is 0;
6977 var integer: lineStartByte is 0;
6978 var integer: xPos is 0;
6979 var integer: yPos is 0;
6980 var integer: colorBitNum is 0;
6981 var integer: byteIndex is 0;
6982 var integer: imageByte is 0;
6983 var integer: colorNum is 0;
6984 begin
6985 if bytes <> "" then
6986 width := bytes2Int(bytes[1 fixLen 2], UNSIGNED, LE);
6987 height := bytes2Int(bytes[3 fixLen 2], UNSIGNED, LE);
6988 # writeln(log, "width=" <& width <& " height=" <& height);
6989 image := newPixmap(width, height);
6990 bytesPerLine := pred(width) mdiv 8 + 1;
6991 for yPos range 0 to pred(height) do
6992 lineStartByte := yPos * 4 * bytesPerLine;
6993 for xPos range 0 to pred(width) do
6994 colorNum := 0;
6995 for colorBitNum range 0 to 3 do
6996 byteIndex := lineStartByte + colorBitNum * bytesPerLine + xPos mdiv 8;
6997 imageByte := ord(bytes[5 + byteIndex]);
6998 colorNum +:= ((imageByte >> (7 - xPos mod 8)) mod 2) << colorBitNum;
6999 end for;
7000 point(image, xPos, yPos, color_num(colorNum));
7001 end for;
7002 end for;
7003 end if;
7004 end func;

7007const func PRIMITIVE_WINDOW: getVgaImageFromBytes (in string: bytes) is func
7008 result
7009 var PRIMITIVE_WINDOW: image is PRIMITIVE_WINDOW.value;
7010 local
7011 var integer: width is 0;
7012 var integer: height is 0;
7013 var integer: bytesPerLine is 0;
7014 var integer: lineStartByte is 0;
7015 var integer: xPos is 0;
7016 var integer: yPos is 0;
7017 var integer: byteIndex is 0;
7018 var integer: imageByte is 0;
7019 begin
7020 if bytes <> "" then
7021 width := bytes2Int(bytes[1 fixLen 2], UNSIGNED, LE) div 8;
7022 height := bytes2Int(bytes[3 fixLen 2], UNSIGNED, LE);
7023 # writeln(log, "width=" <& width <& " height=" <& height);
7024 image := newPixmap(width, height);
7025 bytesPerLine := width;
7026 for yPos range 0 to pred(height) do
7027 lineStartByte := yPos * bytesPerLine;
7028 for xPos range 0 to pred(width) do
7029 byteIndex := lineStartByte + xPos;
7030 imageByte := ord(bytes[5 + byteIndex]);
7031 point(image, xPos, yPos, color_num(imageByte));
7032 end for;
7033 end for;
7034 end if;
7035 end func;

7038const func string: getBytesFromArray (in string: name_start,
7039 in string: name_end, in integer: lbound, in integer: ubound) is func
7040 result
7041 var string: bytes is "";
7042 local
7043 var integer: index is 0;
7044 var float: element is 0.0;
7045 var string: bytesFromInt2 is "";
7046 var string: bytesFromFlt4 is "";
7047 var string: bytesFromDbl8 is "";
7048 var boolean: allInteger is TRUE;
7049 var boolean: allFloat is TRUE;
7050 begin
7051 # writeln(log, "getBytesFromArray(" <& literal(name_start) <& ", " <&
7052 # literal(name_end) <& ", " <& lbound <& ", " <& ubound <& ")");
7053 for index range lbound to ubound do
7054 element := getNumericVar(name_start & str(index) & name_end);
7055 if element >= -32768.0 and element <= 65535.0 then
7056 bytesFromInt2 &:= bytes(round(element) mod 65536, UNSIGNED, LE, 2);
7057 else
7058 allInteger := FALSE;
7059 end if;
7060 if element >= -3.4028235e38 and element <= 3.4028235e38 or
7061 abs(element) = Infinity or isNaN(element) then
7062 bytesFromFlt4 &:= bytes(bin32(element), LE, 4);
7063 else
7064 allFloat := FALSE;
7065 end if;
7066 bytesFromDbl8 &:= bytes(bin64(element), LE, 8);
7067 end for;
7068 if allInteger then
7069 bytes := bytesFromInt2;
7070 elsif allFloat then
7071 bytes := bytesFromFlt4;
7072 else
7073 bytes := bytesFromDbl8;
7074 end if;
7075 # writeln(log, "getBytesFromArray -> " <& literal(bytes));
7076 end func;
7077
7078
7079const func PRIMITIVE_WINDOW: getImageFromArray (in string: name_start,
7080 in string: name_end, in integer: lbound, in integer: ubound) is func
7081 result
7082 var PRIMITIVE_WINDOW: image is PRIMITIVE_WINDOW.value;
7083 begin
7084 # writeln(log, "getImageFromArray: " <& screenMode);
7085 case screenMode of
7086 when {1}:
7087 image := getCga4ImageFromBytes(
7088 getBytesFromArray(name_start, name_end, lbound, ubound));
7089 when {2, 3}:
7090 image := getCga2ImageFromBytes(
7091 getBytesFromArray(name_start, name_end, lbound, ubound));
7092 when {4, 7, 8}:
7093 image := getEgaImageFromBytes(
7094 getBytesFromArray(name_start, name_end, lbound, ubound));
7095 when {13}:
7096 image := getVgaImageFromBytes(
7097 getBytesFromArray(name_start, name_end, lbound, ubound));
7098 otherwise:
7099 error_marker;
7100 writeln(err, "CANNOT GET IMAGE FOR MODE: " <& screenMode);
7101 end case;
7102 end func;

7105const func PRIMITIVE_WINDOW: getImageFromArray (in string: variable_name) is func
7106 result
7107 var PRIMITIVE_WINDOW: image is PRIMITIVE_WINDOW.value;
7108 local
7109 var string: name_start is "";
7110 var string: name_end is "";
7111 var integer: lbound is 0;
7112 var integer: ubound is 0;

7115 if name_start = "" then
7116 lbound := exec_lbound(variable_name, 1);
7117 ubound := exec_ubound(variable_name, 1);
7118 image := getImageFromArray(variable_name & "(", ")", lbound, ubound);
7119 else
7120 ubound := exec_ubound(name_start[ .. pred(length(name_start))], 1);
7121 # writeln(log, "name_start=" <& literal(name_start) <& " name_end=" <& literal(name_end) <&
7122 # " lbound=" <& lbound <& " ubound=" <& ubound);
7123 image := getImageFromArray(name_start, name_end, lbound, ubound);
7124 end if;
7125 end func;

7128const proc: exec_screen (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
7129 local
7130 var integer: newScreenMode is 0;
7131 var integer: colorswitch is 0;
7132 var integer: active is 0;
7133 var integer: visible is 0;
7134 begin
7135 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7136 newScreenMode := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7137 if symbol = "," then
7138 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7139 if symbol <> "," then
7140 colorswitch := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7141 end if;
7142 end if;
7143 if symbol = "," then
7144 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7145 if symbol <> "," then
7146 active := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7147 end if;
7148 end if;
7149 if symbol = "," then
7150 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7151 if symbol <> "," then
7152 visible := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7153 end if;
7154 end if;
7155 if newScreenMode <> screenMode then
7156 case newScreenMode of
7157 when {0}: # Text mode
7158 # Some programs set screen to 0 and draw...
7159 # curr_win := PRIMITIVE_WINDOW.value;
7160 scr := open(CONSOLE);
7161 win := openWindow(scr, 1, 1, TEXT_LINES, TEXT_COLUMNS);
7162 KEYBOARD := CONSOLE_KEYBOARD;
7163 OUT := win;
7164 IN := openEcho(KEYBOARD, OUT);
7165 IN := openLine(IN);
7166 screenMode := newScreenMode;
7167
7168 when {1}: # 320 x 200 pixel, 40 x 25 text, 8 x 8 chars
7169 screen(320, 200);
7170 win := open(curr_win, 8);
7171 screenMode := newScreenMode;
7172
7173 when {2}: # 640 x 200 pixel, 80 x 25 text, 8 x 8 chars
7174 screen(640, 200);
7175 win := open(curr_win, 8);
7176 screenMode := newScreenMode;
7177
7178 when {7}: # 320 x 200 pixel, 40 x 25 text, 8 x 8 chars
7179 screen(320, 200);
7180 win := open(curr_win, 8);
7181 screenMode := newScreenMode;
7182
7183 when {8}: # 640 x 200 pixel, 80 x 25 text, 8 x 8 chars
7184 screen(640, 200);
7185 win := open(curr_win, 8);
7186 screenMode := newScreenMode;
7187
7188 when {9}: # 640 x 350 pixel, 80 x 25 text, 8 x 14 chars
7189 screen(640, 350);
7190 win := open(curr_win, 14);
7191 screenMode := newScreenMode;
7192
7193 when {10}: # 640 x 350 pixel, 80 x 25 text, 8 x 14 chars
7194 screen(640, 350);
7195 win := open(curr_win, 14);
7196 screenMode := newScreenMode;
7197
7198 when {11}: # 640 x 480 pixel, 80 x 30 text, 8 x 16 chars
7199 screen(640, 480);
7200 win := open(curr_win, 16);
7201 screenMode := newScreenMode;
7202
7203 when {12}: # 640 x 480 pixel, 80 x 30 text, 8 x 16 chars
7204 screen(640, 480);
7205 win := open(curr_win, 16);
7206 screenMode := newScreenMode;
7207
7208 when {13}: # 320 x 200 pixel, 40 x 25 text, 8 x 8 chars
7209 screen(320, 200);
7210 win := open(curr_win, 16);
7211 screenMode := newScreenMode;
7212
7213 otherwise:
7214 error_marker;
7215 writeln(err, "ILLEGAL SCREEN NUMBER: " <& newScreenMode);
7216 end case;
7217 if screenMode <> 0 and curr_win <> PRIMITIVE_WINDOW.value then
7218 clear(curr_win, white);
7219 color(white, black);
7220 scr := open(curr_win);
7221 KEYBOARD := GRAPH_KEYBOARD;
7222 OUT := win;
7223 IN := openEcho(KEYBOARD, OUT);
7224 IN := openLine(IN);
7225 end if;
7226 end if;
7227 line_marker;
7228 writeln(log, "SCREEN " <& newScreenMode <& ", " <&
7229 colorswitch <& ", " <& active <& ", " <& visible);
7230 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
7231 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7232 end while;
7233 end func;

7236const proc: exec_pset (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
7237 local
7238 var integer: col is 0;
7239 begin
7240 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7241 if symbol = "STEP" then
7242 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7243 expect("(", symbol, line);
7244 currX +:= round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7245 expect(",", symbol, line);
7246 currY +:= round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7247 expect(")", symbol, line);
7248 else
7249 expect("(", symbol, line);
7250 currX := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7251 expect(",", symbol, line);
7252 currY := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7253 expect(")", symbol, line);
7254 end if;
7255 if symbol = "," then
7256 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7257 col := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7258 else
7259 col := foreground_color;
7260 end if;
7261 point(currX, currY, color_num(col));
7262 flushGraphic;
7263 line_marker;
7264 writeln(log, "PSET (" <& currX <& ", " <& currY <& "), " <& col);
7265 end func;

7269 local
7270 var integer: col is 0;
7271 begin

7273 if symbol = "STEP" then
7274 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7275 expect("(", symbol, line);
7276 currX +:= round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7277 expect(",", symbol, line);
7278 currY +:= round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7279 expect(")", symbol, line);
7280 else
7281 expect("(", symbol, line);
7282 currX := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7283 expect(",", symbol, line);
7284 currY := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7285 expect(")", symbol, line);
7286 end if;
7287 if symbol = "," then
7288 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7289 col := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7290 else
7291 col := background_color;
7292 end if;
7293 point(currX, currY, color_num(col));
7294 flushGraphic;
7295 line_marker;
7296 writeln(log, "PRESET (" <& currX <& ", " <& currY <& "), " <& col);
7297 end func;
7298
7299
7300const proc: exec_line (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
7301 local
7302 var string: param1 is "";
7303 var integer: x1 is 0;
7304 var integer: y1 is 0;
7305 var integer: col is 0;
7306 var boolean: style_present is FALSE;
7307 var integer: style is 0;
7308 begin
7309 if symbol = "STEP" then
7310 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7311 expect("(", symbol, line);
7312 x1 := currX + round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7313 expect(",", symbol, line);
7314 y1 := currY + round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7315 expect(")", symbol, line);
7316 elsif symbol = "-" then
7317 x1 := currX;
7318 y1 := currY;
7319 else
7320 expect("(", symbol, line);
7321 x1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7322 expect(",", symbol, line);
7323 y1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7324 expect(")", symbol, line);
7325 end if;
7326 expect("-", symbol, line);
7327 if symbol = "STEP" then
7328 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7329 expect("(", symbol, line);
7330 currX := x1 + round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7331 expect(",", symbol, line);
7332 currY := y1 + round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7333 else
7334 expect("(", symbol, line);
7335 currX := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7336 expect(",", symbol, line);
7337 currY := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7338 end if;
7339 expect(")", symbol, line);
7340 col := foreground_color;
7341 if symbol = "," then
7342 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7343 if symbol <> "," then
7344 col := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7345 end if;
7346 if symbol = "," then
7347 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7348 if symbol <> "," then
7349 param1 := symbol;
7350 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7351 end if;
7352 if symbol = "," then
7353 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7354 style := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7355 style_present := TRUE;
7356 end if;
7357 end if;
7358 end if;
7359 if param1 = "BF" then
7360 rectTo(x1, y1, currX, currY, color_num(col));
7361 elsif param1 = "B" then
7362 boxTo(x1, y1, currX, currY, color_num(col));
7363 else
7364 lineTo(x1, y1, currX, currY, color_num(col));
7365 end if;
7366 flushGraphic;
7367 line_marker;
7368 write(log, "LINE (" <& x1 <& ", " <& y1 <&
7369 ") - (" <& currX <& ", " <& currY <& "), " <& col);
7370 if param1 <> "" then
7371 write(log, ", " <& param1);
7372 elsif style_present then
7373 write(log, ", ");
7374 end if;
7375 if style_present then
7376 write(log, ", " <& style);
7377 end if;
7378 writeln(log);
7379 end func;

7382const proc: exec_circle (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
7383 local
7384 var integer: radius is 0;
7385 var integer: col is 0;
7386 var integer: start is 0;
7387 var integer: stop is 0;
7388 var integer: aspect is 0;
7389 begin
7390 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7391 if symbol = "STEP" then
7392 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7393 expect("(", symbol, line);
7394 currX +:= round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7395 expect(",", symbol, line);
7396 currY +:= round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7397 else
7398 expect("(", symbol, line);
7399 currX := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7400 expect(",", symbol, line);
7401 currY := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7402 end if;
7403 expect(")", symbol, line);
7404 expect(",", symbol, line);
7405 radius := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7406 col := foreground_color;
7407 if symbol = "," then
7408 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7409 if symbol <> "," then
7410 col := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7411 end if;
7412 end if;
7413 if symbol = "," then
7414 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7415 if symbol <> "," then
7416 start := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7417 end if;
7418 end if;
7419 if symbol = "," then
7420 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7421 if symbol <> "," then
7422 stop := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7423 end if;
7424 end if;
7425 if symbol = "," then
7426 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7427 if symbol <> "," then
7428 aspect := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7429 end if;
7430 end if;
7431 circle(currX, currY, radius, color_num(col));
7432 flushGraphic;
7433 line_marker;
7434 writeln(log, "CIRCLE (" <& currX <& ", " <& currY <& "), " <&
7435 radius <& ", " <& col);
7436 end func;

7439const proc: exec_put (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
7440 local
7441 var integer: x1 is 0;
7442 var integer: y1 is 0;
7443 var string: variable_name is "";
7444 var PRIMITIVE_WINDOW: image is PRIMITIVE_WINDOW.value;
7445 begin
7446 expect("(", symbol, line);
7447 x1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7448 expect(",", symbol, line);
7449 y1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7450 expect(")", symbol, line);
7451 expect(",", symbol, line);
7452 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
7453 if symbol = "," then
7454 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7455 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7456 end if;
7457 if variable_name in image_var then
7458 image := image_var[variable_name];
7459 else
7460 image := getImageFromArray(variable_name);
7461 if image <> PRIMITIVE_WINDOW.value then
7462 line_marker;
7463 writeln(log, "LOAD IMAGE VARIABLE FROM ARRAY " <& literal(variable_name));
7464 image_var @:= [variable_name] image;
7465 else
7466 error_marker;
7467 writeln(err, "CANNOT LOAD IMAGE VARIABLE FROM ARRAY " <& literal(variable_name));
7468 end if;
7469 end if;
7470 if image <> PRIMITIVE_WINDOW.value then
7471 line_marker;
7472 writeln(log, "PUT (" <& x1 <& ", " <& y1 <& "), " <& variable_name);
7473 put(x1, y1, image);
7474 else
7475 error_marker;
7476 writeln(err, "UNDEFINED IMAGE VARIABLE " <& literal(variable_name));
7477 end if;
7478 end func;

7481const proc: exec_get (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
7482 local
7483 var integer: x1 is 0;
7484 var integer: y1 is 0;
7485 var integer: x2 is 0;
7486 var integer: y2 is 0;
7487 var integer: help is 0;
7488 var string: variable_name is "";
7489 var PRIMITIVE_WINDOW: image is PRIMITIVE_WINDOW.value;
7490 begin
7491 expect("(", symbol, line);
7492 x1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7493 expect(",", symbol, line);
7494 y1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7495 expect(")", symbol, line);
7496 expect("-", symbol, line);
7497 if symbol = "STEP" then
7498 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7499 expect("(", symbol, line);
7500 x2 := x1 + round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7501 expect(",", symbol, line);
7502 y2 := y1 + round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7503 else
7504 expect("(", symbol, line);
7505 x2 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7506 expect(",", symbol, line);
7507 y2 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7508 end if;
7509 expect(")", symbol, line);
7510 expect(",", symbol, line);
7511 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
7512 if x1 > x2 or y1 > y2 then
7513 error_marker;
7514 write(err, "GET (" <& x1 <& ", " <& y1 <&
7515 ") - (" <& x2 <& ", " <& y2 <& ") = ");
7516 end if;
7517 if x1 > x2 and y1 > y2 then
7518 writeln(err, "GET (LOWER RIGHT) - (UPPER LEFT)");
7519 help := x1;
7520 x1 := x2;
7521 x2 := help;
7522 help := y1;
7523 y1 := y2;
7524 y2 := help;
7525 elsif x1 > x2 then
7526 writeln(err, "GET (UPPER RIGHT) - (LOWER LEFT)");
7527 help := x1;
7528 x1 := x2;
7529 x2 := help;
7530 elsif y1 > y2 then
7531 writeln(err, "GET (LOWER LEFT) - (UPPER RIGHT)");
7532 help := y1;
7533 y1 := y2;
7534 y2 := help;
7535 end if;
7536 image := getPixmap(x1, y1, x2 - x1 + 1, y2 - y1 + 1);
7537 image_var @:= [variable_name] image;
7538 line_marker;
7539 writeln(log, "GET (" <& x1 <& ", " <& y1 <&
7540 ") - (" <& x2 <& ", " <& y2 <& "), " <& variable_name);
7541 end func;
7542
7543
7544const func string: getChar (inout string: stri) is func
7545 result
7546 var string: symbol is "";
7547 begin
7548 symbol := stri[1 len 1];
7549 stri := stri[2 ..];
7550 end func;
7551
7552
7553const func string: getSign (inout string: stri) is func
7554 result
7555 var string: symbol is "";
7556 begin
7557 symbol := stri[1 len 1];
7558 if symbol = "+" or symbol = "-" then
7559 stri := stri[2 ..];
7560 else
7561 symbol := "";
7562 end if;
7563 end func;

7566const proc: exec_draw (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
7567 local
7568 var string: cmdStri is "";
7569 var string: unused_name is "";
7570 var integer: xPos is 1;
7571 var integer: yPos is 1;
7572 var integer: xOld is 1;
7573 var integer: yOld is 1;
7574 var char: currCmd is ' ';
7575 var string: param1 is "";
7576 var string: sign is "";
7577 var integer: num1 is 0;
7578 var integer: num2 is 0;
7579 var boolean: pen_down is TRUE;
7580 var boolean: move_back is FALSE;
7581 var integer: scale_factor is 1;
7582 var integer: turn_factor is 0;
7583 begin
7584 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7585 cmdStri := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
7586 line_marker;
7587 writeln(log, "**DRAW " <& literal(cmdStri));
7588 skipWhiteSpace(cmdStri);
7589 while cmdStri <> "" do
7590 currCmd := upper(getChar(cmdStri)[1]);
7591 skipWhiteSpace(cmdStri);
7592 if currCmd = 'B' then
7593 pen_down := FALSE;
7594 writeln(log, "B - PEN UP");
7595 if cmdStri <> "" then
7596 currCmd := upper(getChar(cmdStri)[1]);
7597 else
7598 currCmd := ' ';
7599 end if;
7600 skipWhiteSpace(cmdStri);
7601 elsif currCmd = 'N' then
7602 move_back := TRUE;
7603 if cmdStri <> "" then
7604 currCmd := upper(getChar(cmdStri)[1]);
7605 else
7606 currCmd := ' ';
7607 end if;
7608 skipWhiteSpace(cmdStri);
7609 end if;
7610 xOld := xPos;
7611 yOld := yPos;
7612 case currCmd of
7613 when {' '}:
7614 noop;
7615 when {'U'}:
7616 param1 := getDigits(cmdStri);
7617 if param1 <> "" then
7618 yPos -:= scale_factor * integer(param1);
7619 if pen_down then
7620 lineTo(xOld, yOld, xPos, yPos, color_num(foreground_color));
7621 end if;
7622 end if;
7623 when {'D'}:
7624 param1 := getDigits(cmdStri);
7625 if param1 <> "" then
7626 yPos +:= scale_factor * integer(param1);
7627 if pen_down then
7628 lineTo(xOld, yOld, xPos, yPos, color_num(foreground_color));
7629 end if;
7630 end if;
7631 when {'L'}:
7632 param1 := getDigits(cmdStri);
7633 if param1 <> "" then
7634 xPos -:= scale_factor * integer(param1);
7635 if pen_down then
7636 lineTo(xOld, yOld, xPos, yPos, color_num(foreground_color));
7637 end if;
7638 end if;
7639 when {'R'}:
7640 param1 := getDigits(cmdStri);
7641 if param1 <> "" then
7642 xPos +:= scale_factor * integer(param1);
7643 if pen_down then
7644 lineTo(xOld, yOld, xPos, yPos, color_num(foreground_color));
7645 end if;
7646 end if;
7647 when {'E'}:
7648 param1 := getDigits(cmdStri);
7649 if param1 <> "" then
7650 num1 := integer(param1);
7651 xPos +:= scale_factor * num1;
7652 yPos -:= scale_factor * num1;
7653 if pen_down then
7654 lineTo(xOld, yOld, xPos, yPos, color_num(foreground_color));
7655 end if;
7656 end if;
7657 when {'F'}:
7658 param1 := getDigits(cmdStri);
7659 if param1 <> "" then
7660 num1 := integer(param1);
7661 xPos +:= scale_factor * num1;
7662 yPos +:= scale_factor * num1;
7663 if pen_down then
7664 lineTo(xOld, yOld, xPos, yPos, color_num(foreground_color));
7665 end if;
7666 end if;
7667 when {'G'}:
7668 param1 := getDigits(cmdStri);
7669 if param1 <> "" then
7670 num1 := integer(param1);
7671 xPos -:= scale_factor * num1;
7672 yPos +:= scale_factor * num1;
7673 if pen_down then
7674 lineTo(xOld, yOld, xPos, yPos, color_num(foreground_color));
7675 end if;
7676 end if;
7677 when {'H'}:
7678 param1 := getDigits(cmdStri);
7679 if param1 <> "" then
7680 num1 := integer(param1);
7681 xPos -:= scale_factor * num1;
7682 yPos -:= scale_factor * num1;
7683 if pen_down then
7684 lineTo(xOld, yOld, xPos, yPos, color_num(foreground_color));
7685 end if;
7686 end if;
7687 when {'M'}:
7688 skipWhiteSpace(cmdStri);
7689 sign := getSign(cmdStri);
7690 param1 := getDigits(cmdStri);
7691 if param1 <> "" then
7692 num1 := integer(param1);
7693 if sign = "" then
7694 xPos := scale_factor * num1;
7695 else
7696 xPos -:= scale_factor * num1;
7697 end if;
7698 skipWhiteSpace(cmdStri);
7699 param1 := getChar(cmdStri);
7700 if param1 = "," then
7701 skipWhiteSpace(cmdStri);
7702 sign := getSign(cmdStri);
7703 param1 := getDigits(cmdStri);
7704 if param1 <> "" then
7705 num2 := integer(param1);
7706 if sign = "" then
7707 yPos := scale_factor * num2;
7708 else
7709 yPos -:= scale_factor * num2;
7710 end if;
7711 if pen_down then
7712 lineTo(xOld, yOld, xPos, yPos, color_num(foreground_color));
7713 end if;
7714 writeln(log, "MOVE");
7715 end if;
7716 end if;
7717 end if;
7718 when {'C'}:
7719 param1 := getDigits(cmdStri);
7720 if param1 <> "" then
7721 foreground_color := integer(param1);
7722 writeln(log, "COLOR " <& foreground_color);
7723 end if;
7724 when {'S'}:
7725 param1 := getDigits(cmdStri);
7726 if param1 <> "" then
7727 scale_factor := integer(param1);
7728 writeln(log, "SCALE " <& scale_factor);
7729 end if;
7730 when {'T'}:
7731 currCmd := upper(getChar(cmdStri)[1]);
7732 if currCmd = 'A' then
7733 param1 := getDigits(cmdStri);
7734 if param1 <> "" then
7735 turn_factor := integer(param1);
7736 writeln(log, "TURN ANGLE " <& turn_factor);
7737 end if;
7738 end if;
7739 when {'\3;'}:
7740 num1 := bytes2Int(cmdStri[1 fixLen 2], UNSIGNED, LE);
7741 param1 := varname(num1);
7742 cmdStri := getStringVar(param1) & cmdStri[3 ..];
7743 writeln(log, "VARPTR$(" <& param1 <& ")");
7744 end case;
7745 pen_down := TRUE;
7746 move_back := FALSE;
7747 end while;
7748 end func;
7749
7750
7751const proc: exec_plot (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func

7753 var integer: currX is 0;
7754 var integer: currY is 0;
7755 var integer: col is 0;

7768const proc: exec_hplot (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
7769 local
7770 var integer: col is 0;
7771 var integer: currX is 0;
7772 var integer: currY is 0;
7773 var integer: destX is 0;
7774 var integer: destY is 0;
7775 begin
7776 col := round(getNumericVar("HCOLOR"));
7777 currX := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7778 expect(",", symbol, line);
7779 currY := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7780 if symbol = "TO" then
7781 repeat
7782 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7783 destX := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7784 expect(",", symbol, line);
7785 destY := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7786 lineTo(currX, currY, destX, destY,
7787 hiresColor[col mod length(hiresColor)]);
7788 flushGraphic;
7789 line_marker;
7790 writeln(log, "HPLOT " <& currX <& ", " <& currY <&
7791 " TO " <& destX <& ", " <& destY);
7792 currX := destX;
7793 currY := destY;
7794 until symbol <> "TO";
7795 else
7796 point(currX, currY, hiresColor[col mod length(hiresColor)]);
7797 flushGraphic;
7798 line_marker;
7799 writeln(log, "HPLOT " <& currX <& ", " <& currY);
7800 end if;
7801 end func;

7804const proc: setup_graphic is func
7805 begin
7806 if screenMode <> -1 then
7807 screen(1024, 768);
7808 clear(curr_win, light_cyan);
7809 win := openPixmapFontFile(curr_win);
7810 color(win, black, light_cyan);
7811 KEYBOARD := GRAPH_KEYBOARD;
7812 OUT := win;
7813 IN := openEcho(KEYBOARD, win);
7814 IN := openLine(IN);
7815 scale(win, 4);
7816 currentFont := font8x8;
7817 setFont(win, currentFont);
7818 screenMode := -1;
7819 end if;
7820 end func;
