7823const proc: exec_call_char (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
7824 local
7825 var integer: character_code is 0;
7826 var string: patternArgument is "";
7827 var string: unused_name is "";
7828 var array string: charPicture is 8 times " " mult 8;
7829 var integer: patternStartPos is 1;
7830 var char: patternChar is ' ';
7831 var string: pattern is "";
7832 var integer: pos is 0;
7833 var integer: patternLine is 1;
7834 var boolean: right is FALSE;
7835 var integer: number is 0;
7836 var integer: bit is 0;
7837 begin
7838 setup_graphic;
7839 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7840 expect("(", symbol, line);
7841 character_code := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7842 expect(",", symbol, line);
7843 patternArgument := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
7844 expect(")", symbol, line);
7845 patternChar := chr(character_code);
7846 repeat
7847 pattern := patternArgument[patternStartPos len 16];
7848 patternLine := 1;
7849 for pos range 1 to length(pattern) do
7850 number := integer(pattern[pos fixLen 1], 16);
7851 for bit range 1 to 4 do
7852 if odd(number) then
7853 charPicture[patternLine] @:= [ord(right) * 4 + 5 - bit] 'X';
7854 end if;
7855 number >>:= 1;
7856 end for;
7857 if right then
7858 incr(patternLine);
7859 end if;
7860 right := not right;
7861 end for;
7862 currentFont.fontPictures @:= [patternChar] charPicture;
7863 setFont(win, currentFont);
7864 patternStartPos +:= 16;
7865 incr(patternChar);
7866 until patternStartPos > length(patternArgument);
7867 line_marker;
7868 writeln(log, "CALL CHAR(" <& character_code <& ", " <& literal(patternArgument) <& ")");
7869 end func;
7870

7872const proc: exec_call_clear (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
7873 begin
7874 setup_graphic;
7875 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7876 clear(curr_win, light_cyan);
7877 line_marker;
7878 writeln(log, "CALL CLEAR");
7879 end func;

7882const proc: exec_call_color (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
7883 local
7884 var integer: character_set is 0;
7885 var integer: foreground is 0;
7886 var integer: background is 0;
7887 var boolean: done is FALSE;
7888 begin
7889 setup_graphic;
7890 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7891 expect("(", symbol, line);
7892 if symbol = "#" then
7893 repeat
7894 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7895 character_set := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7896 expect(",", symbol, line);
7897 foreground := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7898 line_marker;
7899 writeln(log, "CALL COLOR(#" <& character_set <& ", " <&
7900 foreground <& ")");
7901 until symbol <> ",";
7902 else
7903 repeat
7904 character_set := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7905 expect(",", symbol, line);
7906 foreground := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7907 expect(",", symbol, line);
7908 background := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7909 line_marker;
7910 writeln(log, "CALL COLOR(" <& character_set <& ", " <&
7911 foreground <& ", " <& background <& ")");
7912 if symbol = "," then
7913 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7914 else
7915 done := TRUE;
7916 end if;
7917 until done;
7918 end if;
7919 expect(")", symbol, line);
7920 end func;

7923const proc: exec_call_hchar (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
7924 local
7925 var integer: row is 0;
7926 var integer: column is 0;
7927 var integer: character_code is 0;
7928 var integer: repetition is 1;
7929 begin
7930 setup_graphic;
7931 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7932 expect("(", symbol, line);
7933 row := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7934 expect(",", symbol, line);
7935 column := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7936 expect(",", symbol, line);
7937 character_code := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7938 if symbol = "," then
7939 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7940 repetition := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7941 end if;
7942 expect(")", symbol, line);
7943 for repetition do
7944 setPos(win, row, column);
7945 write(win, chr(character_code));
7946 if column < 32 then
7947 incr(column);
7948 else
7949 incr(row);
7950 column := 1;
7951 end if;
7952 end for;
7953 line_marker;
7954 writeln(log, "CALL HCHAR(" <& row <& ", " <& column <& ", " <&
7955 character_code <& ", " <& repetition <& ")");
7956 end func;

7959const proc: exec_call_key (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
7960 local
7961 var integer: key_unit is 0;
7962 var string: return_variable is "";
7963 var string: status_variable is "";
7964 begin
7965 setup_graphic;
7966 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7967 expect("(", symbol, line);
7968 key_unit := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7969 expect(",", symbol, line);
7970 return_variable := get_name(symbol, line);
7971 expect(",", symbol, line);
7972 status_variable := get_name(symbol, line);
7973 expect(")", symbol, line);
7974 if inputReady(KEYBOARD) then
7975 setNumericVar(return_variable, flt(ord(getc(KEYBOARD))));
7976 setNumericVar(status_variable, 1.0);
7977 else
7978 setNumericVar(return_variable, -1.0);
7979 setNumericVar(status_variable, 0.0);
7980 end if;
7981 line_marker;
7982 writeln(log, "CALL KEY(" <& key_unit <& ", " <& return_variable <& ", " <& status_variable <& ")");
7983 end func;
7984

7986const proc: exec_call_screen (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
7987 local
7988 var integer: color_code is 0;
7989 begin
7990 setup_graphic;
7991 symbol := get_symbol(line);
7992 expect("(", symbol, line);
7993 color_code := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
7994 expect(")", symbol, line);
7995 line_marker;
7996 writeln(log, "CALL SCREEN(" <& color_code <& ")");
7997 end func;

8000const proc: exec_call_sound (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
8001 local
8002 var float: duration is 0.0;
8003 var integer: frequency is 0;
8004 var integer: volume is 0;
8005 begin
8006 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8007 expect("(", symbol, line);
8008 duration := exec_expr(symbol, line);
8009 expect(",", symbol, line);
8010 frequency := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
8011 expect(",", symbol, line);
8012 volume := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
8013 expect(")", symbol, line);
8014 line_marker;
8015 writeln(log, "CALL SOUND(" <& duration <& ", " <& frequency <& ", " <& volume <& ")");
8016 end func;

8018
8019const proc: exec_call_vchar (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
8020 local
8021 var integer: row is 0;
8022 var integer: column is 0;
8023 var integer: character_code is 0;
8024 var integer: repetition is 1;
8025 begin
8026 setup_graphic;
8027 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8028 expect("(", symbol, line);
8029 row := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
8030 expect(",", symbol, line);
8031 column := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
8032 expect(",", symbol, line);
8033 character_code := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
8034 if symbol = "," then
8035 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8036 repetition := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
8037 end if;
8038 expect(")", symbol, line);
8039 for repetition do
8040 setPos(win, row, column);
8041 write(win, chr(character_code));
8042 if row < 24 then
8043 incr(row);
8044 else
8045 incr(column);
8046 row := 1;
8047 end if;
8048 end for;
8049 line_marker;
8050 writeln(log, "CALL VCHAR(" <& row <& ", " <& column <& ", " <&
8051 character_code <& ", " <& repetition <& ")");
8052 end func;

8054
8055const proc: exec_let (inout string: symbol, inout string: line,
8056 inout boolean: process_next) is func
8057 local
8058 var boolean: is_let_statement is TRUE;
8059 var string: variable_name is "";
8060 var string: unused_name is "";
8061 var string: backup_line is "";
8062 var string: param1 is "";
8063 var float: num1 is 0.0;
8064 begin
8065 if symbol = "LET" then
8066 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8067 elsif not is_let_statement(line) then
8068 # If no "=" follows it is probably a statement
8069 # which is not separated with a space
8070 is_let_statement := FALSE;
8071 if startsWith(symbol, "REM") then
8072 line_marker;
8073 writeln(log, "REM " <& symbol <& line);
8074 symbol := "";
8075 elsif startsWith(symbol, "IF") then
8076 line := symbol[3 ..] & line;
8077 exec_if(symbol, line, process_next);
8078 elsif startsWith(symbol, "GOTO") then
8079 line := symbol[5 ..] & line;
8080 exec_goto(symbol, line);
8081 elsif startsWith(symbol, "GOSUB") then
8082 line := symbol[6 ..] & line;
8083 exec_gosub(symbol, line);
8084 elsif startsWith(symbol, "ELSE") and not startsWith(symbol, "ELSEIF") then
8085 line := symbol[5 ..] & line;
8086 exec_else(symbol, line);
8087 elsif startsWith(symbol, "NEXT") then
8088 line := symbol[5 ..] & line;
8089 exec_next(symbol, line);
8090 elsif startsWith(symbol, "ON") then
8091 line := symbol[3 ..] & line;
8092 exec_on(symbol, line);
8093 elsif startsWith(symbol, "PRINT") then
8094 line := symbol[6 ..] & line;
8095 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8096 exec_print(symbol, line);
8097 elsif startsWith(symbol, "LPRINT") then
8098 line := symbol[7 ..] & line;
8099 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8100 exec_print(symbol, line);
8101 elsif startsWith(symbol, "INPUT") then
8102 line := symbol[6 ..] & line;
8103 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8104 exec_input(symbol, line);
8105 elsif startsWith(symbol, "READ") then
8106 line := symbol[5 ..] & line;
8107 exec_read(symbol, line);
8108 elsif startsWith(symbol, "CLEAR") then
8109 line := symbol[6 ..] & line;
8110 exec_clear(symbol, line);
8111 elsif startsWith(symbol, "DIM") then
8112 line := symbol[4 ..] & line;
8113 exec_dim(symbol, line);
8114 elsif symbol in label then
8115 param1 := symbol;
8116 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8117 if symbol = ":" then
8118 line_marker;
8119 writeln(log, "SKIP LABEL: " <& param1);
8120 else
8121 error_marker;
8122 writeln(err, "COLON EXPECTED AFTER LABEL " <& param1 <&
8123 " - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
8124 end if;
8125 elsif symbol in usedLabel and symbol in multipleDefinedLabel then
8126 param1 := symbol;
8127 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8128 if symbol = ":" then
8129 line_marker;
8130 writeln(log, "SKIP MULTIPLE DEFINED LABEL: " <& param1);
8131 else
8132 error_marker;
8133 writeln(err, "COLON EXPECTED AFTER LABEL " <& param1 <&
8134 " - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
8135 end if;
8136 else
8137 is_let_statement := TRUE;
8138 end if;
8139 end if;
8140 if is_let_statement then
8141 if isStringVar(symbol) then
8142 backup_line := symbol & line;
8143 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
8144 backup_line := backup_line[.. length(backup_line) - length(line)];
8145 if symbol = "=" then
8146 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8147 param1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
8148 if startsWith(variable_name, "IF") and startsWith(symbol, "THEN") then
8149 line := backup_line[3 ..] & "\"" & param1 & "\"" & symbol & line;
8150 line_marker;
8151 writeln(log, "IF RECOGNIZED: IF " <& literal(line));
8152 exec_if(symbol, line, process_next);
8153 else
8154 setStringVar(variable_name, param1);
8155 line_marker;
8156 writeln(log, "LET " <& variable_name <& "=" <& literal(param1));
8157 end if;
8158 else
8159 error_marker;
8160 writeln(err, "\"=\" EXPECTED AFTER " <& literal(variable_name) <&
8161 " - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
8162 end if;
8163 elsif isNumericVar(symbol) then
8164 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
8165 if symbol = "=" then
8166 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8167 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
8168 if startsWith(variable_name, "IF") and startsWith(symbol, "THEN") then
8169 line := variable_name[3 ..] & "=" & str(num1) & symbol & line;
8170 line_marker;
8171 writeln(log, "IF RECOGNIZED: IF " <& literal(line));
8172 exec_if(symbol, line, process_next);
8173 elsif startsWith(variable_name, "FOR") and startsWith(symbol, "TO") then
8174 line := variable_name[4 ..] & "=" & str(num1) & symbol & line;
8175 line_marker;
8176 writeln(log, "FOR RECOGNIZED: FOR " <& literal(line));
8177 exec_for(symbol, line);
8178 else
8179 setNumericVar(variable_name, num1);
8180 line_marker;
8181 writeln(log, "LET " <& variable_name <& "=" <& num1);
8182 end if;
8183 else
8184 error_marker;
8185 writeln(err, "\"=\" EXPECTED AFTER " <& literal(variable_name) <&
8186 " - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
8187 end if;
8188 else
8189 error_marker;
8190 writeln(err, "VARIABLE EXPECTED - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
8191 end if;
8192 end if;
8193 end func;
8194
8195
8196const func boolean: runOrChain (in string: cmd, in string: name) is forward;
8197
8198
8199const func boolean: execCmd (inout string: symbol, inout string: line) is func
8200 result
8201 var boolean: running is TRUE;
8202 local
8203 var string: variable_name is "";
8204 var string: variable2_name is "";
8205 var string: unused_name is "";
8206 var string: param1 is "";
8207 var string: param2 is "";
8208 var string: param3 is "";
8209 var float: num1 is 0.0;
8210 var float: num2 is 0.0;
8211 var integer: index1 is 0;
8212 var integer: index2 is 0;
8213 var integer: index3 is 0;
8214 var char: current_key is ' ';
8215 var boolean: okay is FALSE;
8216 var boolean: process_next is FALSE;
8217 begin
8218 # writeln(log, literal(symbol));
8219 repeat
8220 process_next := FALSE;
8221 case symbol of
8222 when {""}:
8223 noop;
8224 when {"BEEP"}:
8225 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8226 line_marker;
8227 writeln(log, "**BEEP");
8228 when {"BLOAD"}:
8229 exec_bload(symbol, line);
8230 when {"CALL"}:
8231 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8232 if symbol in subprogram then
8233 line_marker;
8234 writeln(log, "CALL " <& symbol);
8235 advance_after_statement(line);
8236 set_return_position(line);
8237 gosubReturn[1].subName := symbol;
8238 file_line_number := subprogram[symbol];
8239 statement_label := prg[file_line_number].label;
8240 line := prg[file_line_number].line;
8241 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8242 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8243 set_sub_entry_position;
8244 line_marker;
8245 writeln(log, "EXECUTE SUB " <& symbol);
8246 elsif symbol in sub_declared then
8247 error_marker;
8248 writeln(err, "CALL DECLARED BUT UNDEFINED SUB " <& symbol);
8249 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
8250 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8251 end while;
8252 elsif symbol = "+" or symbol = "-" or
8253 symbol <> "" and symbol[1] in digit_char then
8254 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
8255 error_marker;
8256 writeln(err, "CALL UNDEFINED SUB " <& index1 <& ".");
8257 elsif symbol = "CHAR" then
8258 exec_call_char(symbol, line);
8259 elsif symbol = "CLEAR" then
8260 exec_call_clear(symbol, line);
8261 elsif symbol = "COLOR" then
8262 exec_call_color(symbol, line);
8263 elsif symbol = "HCHAR" then
8264 exec_call_hchar(symbol, line);
8265 elsif symbol = "KEY" then
8266 exec_call_key(symbol, line);
8267 elsif symbol = "SCREEN" then
8268 exec_call_screen(symbol, line);
8269 elsif symbol = "SOUND" then
8270 exec_call_sound(symbol, line);
8271 elsif symbol = "VCHAR" then
8272 exec_call_vchar(symbol, line);
8273 else
8274 error_marker;
8275 writeln(err, "CALL UNDEFINED SUB " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
8276 end if;
8277 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
8278 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8279 end while;
8280 when {"CASE"}:
8281 line_marker;
8282 writeln(log, "CASE - SKIP TO \"END SELECT\"");
8283 symbol := find_end_select(line);
8284 if symbol = "SELECT" then
8285 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8286 line_marker;
8287 writeln(log, "END SELECT");
8288 else
8289 error_marker;
8290 writeln(err, "NO CORRESPONDING \"END SELECT\" FOUND");
8291 end if;
8292 when {"CHAIN"}:
8293 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8294 if isStringExpr(symbol) then
8295 param1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, variable_name);
8296 if runOrChain("CHAIN", param1) then
8297 writeln(log, "load program finished");
8298 line_marker;
8299 writeln(log, "CHAIN " <& literal(param1) <& " - " <&
8300 length(prg) <& " LINES");
8301 file_line_number := 0;
8302 data_line_number := 0;
8303 symbol := "";
8304 line := "";
8305 elsif on_error_label <> "" then
8306 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8307 error_code := 53; # File not found
8308 line_marker;
8309 writeln(log, error_code <& " CHAIN " <& literal(param1) <&
8310 " - FILE NOT FOUND - ON ERROR GOTO " <& on_error_label);
8311 goto_on_error(on_error_label, line);
8312 symbol := "";
8313 line := "";
8314 else
8315 error_marker;
8316 writeln(err, "CHAIN " <& literal(param1) <& " - FILE NOT FOUND.");
8317 end if;
8318 else
8319 error_marker;
8320 writeln(err, "STRING EXPECTED FOR CHAIN - FOUND " <& symbol <& ".");
8321 end if;
8322 when {"CIRCLE"}:
8323 exec_circle(symbol, line);
8324 when {"CLEAR"}:
8325 exec_clear(symbol, line);
8326 when {"CLOSE", "CLOSE#"}:
8327 exec_close(symbol, line);
8328 when {"CLS"}:
8329 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8330 if symbol = "0" or symbol = "1" or symbol = "2" then
8331 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8332 end if;
8333 clear(win);
8334 setPos(win, 1, 1);
8335 line_marker;
8336 writeln(log, "CLS");
8337 when {"COLOR"}:
8338 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8339 if symbol = "=" or symbol = "(" or symbol = "[" then
8340 exec_let("COLOR", symbol, line);
8341 elsif symbol = ":" and "COLOR" in usedLabel then
8342 line_marker;
8343 writeln(log, "SKIP LABEL: COLOR");
8344 else
8345 if symbol <> "," then
8346 foreground_color := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
8347 end if;
8348 if symbol = "," then
8349 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8350 background_color := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
8351 if symbol = "," then
8352 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8353 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
8354 end if;
8355 end if;
8356 line_marker;
8357 writeln(log, "**COLOR " <& foreground_color <& "," <& background_color);
8358 end if;
8359 when {"COMMON"}:
8360 line_marker;
8361 writeln(log, "**COMMON " <& line);
8362 repeat
8363 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8364 until endOfStatement(symbol);
8365 when {"CONST"}:
8366 repeat
8367 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8368 if isStringVar(symbol) then
8369 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
8370 if symbol = "=" then
8371 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8372 param3 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
8373 setStringVar(variable_name, param3);
8374 line_marker;
8375 writeln(log, "CONST " <& variable_name <& "=" <& literal(param3));
8376 else
8377 error_marker;
8378 writeln(err, "\"=\" EXPECTED AFTER " <& literal(variable_name) <&
8379 " - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
8380 end if;
8381 elsif isNumericVar(symbol) then
8382 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
8383 if symbol = "=" then
8384 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8385 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
8386 setNumericVar(variable_name, num1);
8387 line_marker;
8388 writeln(log, "CONST " <& variable_name <& "=" <& num1);
8389 else
8390 error_marker;
8391 writeln(err, "\"=\" EXPECTED AFTER " <& literal(variable_name) <&
8392 " - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
8393 end if;
8394 else
8395 error_marker;
8396 writeln(err, "VARIABLE EXPECTED - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
8397 end if;
8398 until symbol <> ",";
8399 when {"DATA", "DATA&"}:
8400 symbol := "";
8401 line_marker;
8402 writeln(log, "DATA");
8403 when {"DECLARE"}:
8404 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8405 if symbol = "SUB" then
8406 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8407 sub_declared @:= [symbol] file_line_number;
8408 line_marker;
8409 writeln(log, "**DECLARE SUB " <& symbol <& " " <& line);
8410 repeat
8411 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8412 until endOfStatement(symbol);
8413 elsif symbol = "FUNCTION" then
8414 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8415 line_marker;
8416 writeln(log, "**DECLARE FUNCTION " <& symbol <& " " <& line);
8417 repeat
8418 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8419 until endOfStatement(symbol);
8420 else
8421 error_marker;
8422 writeln(err, "ILLEGAL DECLARE " <& symbol);
8423 end if;
8424 when {"DECR"}:
8425 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8426 if symbol = "=" or symbol = "(" or symbol = "[" then
8427 exec_let("DECR", symbol, line);
8428 elsif symbol = ":" and "DECR" in usedLabel then
8429 line_marker;
8430 writeln(log, "SKIP LABEL: DECR");
8431 else
8432 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
8433 if symbol = "," then
8434 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8435 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
8436 else
8437 num1 := 1.0;
8438 end if;
8439 setNumericVar(variable_name, getNumericVar(variable_name) - num1);
8440 line_marker;
8441 writeln(log, "DECR " <& variable_name <& " BY " <& num1);
8442 end if;
8443 when {"DEF"}:
8444 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8445 if symbol = "SEG" then
8446 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8447 if symbol = "=" then
8448 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8449 if symbol = "VARSEG" then
8450 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8451 expect("(", symbol, line);
8452 varseg_variable := get_name(symbol, line);
8453 expect(")", symbol, line);
8454 line_marker;
8455 writeln(log, "**DEF SEG = VARSEG(" <& varseg_variable <& ")");
8456 else
8457 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
8458 line_marker;
8459 writeln(log, "**DEF SEG = " <& index1);
8460 end if;
8461 else
8462 line_marker;
8463 writeln(log, "**DEF SEG");
8464 end if;
8465 else
8466 variable_name := symbol;
8467 if variable_name[1] >= 'A' and variable_name[1] <= 'Z' then
8468 define_function(variable_name, symbol, line, TRUE);
8469 end if;
8470 end if;
8471 when {"DEFDBL"}:
8472 exec_defType_numeric(symbol, line);
8473 when {"DEFINT"}:
8474 exec_defType_numeric(symbol, line);
8475 when {"DEFLNG"}:
8476 exec_defType_numeric(symbol, line);
8477 when {"DEFSNG"}:
8478 exec_defType_numeric(symbol, line);
8479 when {"DEFSTR"}:
8480 exec_defstr(symbol, line);
8481 when {"DELAY"}:
8482 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8483 if symbol = "=" or symbol = "(" or symbol = "[" then
8484 exec_let("DELAY", symbol, line);
8485 elsif symbol = ":" and "DELAY" in usedLabel then
8486 line_marker;
8487 writeln(log, "SKIP LABEL: DELAY");
8488 else
8489 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
8490 flush(win);
8491 delay(num1);
8492 line_marker;
8493 writeln(log, "DELAY " <& num1);
8494 end if;
8495 when {"DIM"}:
8496 exec_dim(symbol, line);
8497 when {"DISPLAY"}:
8498 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8499 if symbol = "=" or symbol = "(" or symbol = "[" then
8500 exec_let("DISPLAY", symbol, line);
8501 elsif symbol = ":" and "DISPLAY" in usedLabel then
8502 line_marker;
8503 writeln(log, "SKIP LABEL: DISPLAY");
8504 else
8505 exec_display(symbol, line);
8506 end if;
8507 when {"DO"}:
8508 exec_do(symbol, line);
8509 when {"DRAW"}:
8510 exec_draw(symbol, line);
8511 when {"ELSE"}:
8512 exec_else(symbol, line);
8513 when {"ELSEIF"}:
8514 line_marker;
8515 writeln(log, "ELSEIF - THE \"THEN\" BLOCK BEFORE WAS EXECUTED");
8516 symbol := find_end_if(line);
8517 if symbol = "IF" then
8518 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8519 line_marker;
8520 writeln(log, "END IF");
8521 else
8522 error_marker;
8523 writeln(err, "ELSEIF - MISSING \"END IF\".");
8524 end if;
8525 when {"ENDIF"}:
8526 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8527 line_marker;
8528 writeln(log, "END IF - THE \"THEN\" OR \"ELSE\" BLOCK BEFORE WAS EXECUTED");
8529 when {"END"}:
8530 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8531 if symbol = "IF" then
8532 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8533 line_marker;
8534 writeln(log, "END IF - THE \"THEN\" OR \"ELSE\" BLOCK BEFORE WAS EXECUTED");
8535 elsif symbol = "SELECT" then
8536 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8537 line_marker;
8538 writeln(log, "END SELECT");
8539 elsif symbol = "SUB" then
8540 if length(gosubReturn) >= 1 then
8541 check_loop_stacks_before_return("END SUB " & gosubReturn[1].subName);
8542 line_marker;
8543 write(log, "END SUB " <& gosubReturn[1].subName <& " - RETURN TO ");
8544 do_return(symbol, line);
8545 line_marker;
8546 writeln(log);
8547 else
8548 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8549 error_marker;
8550 writeln(err, "END SUB - RETURN WITHOUT CALL.");
8551 end if;
8552 elsif symbol = "FUNCTION" then
8553 if length(gosubReturn) >= 1 then
8554 check_loop_stacks_before_return("END FUNCTION " & gosubReturn[1].subName);
8555 line_marker;
8556 writeln(log, "END FUNCTION " <& gosubReturn[1].subName);
8557 symbol := "";
8558 running := FALSE;
8559 else
8560 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8561 error_marker;
8562 writeln(err, "END FUNCTION - RETURN WITHOUT CALL.");
8563 end if;
8564 elsif endOfStatement(symbol) then
8565 line_marker;
8566 writeln(log, "END");
8567 symbol := "";
8568 running := FALSE;
8569 else
8570 error_marker;
8571 writeln(err, "UNEXPECTED SYMBOL AFTER END " <& literal(symbol));
8572 end if;
8573 when {"ERASE"}:
8574 line_marker;
8575 writeln(log, "**ERASE " <& line);
8576 repeat
8577 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8578 until endOfStatement(symbol);
8579 when {"ERROR"}:
8580 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8581 error_code := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
8582 if on_error_label <> "" then
8583 line_marker;
8584 writeln(log, "ERROR " <& error_code <&
8585 " - ON ERROR GOTO " <& on_error_label);
8586 goto_on_error(on_error_label, line);
8587 symbol := "";
8588 line := "";
8589 else
8590 error_marker;
8591 writeln(err, "ERROR " <& error_code <& " WITHOUT ON ERROR HANDLER.");
8592 end if;
8593 when {"EXIT"}:
8594 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8595 if symbol = "FOR" then
8596 if length(forLoop) = 0 then
8597 error_marker;
8598 write(err, "EXIT FOR - NOT INSIDE \"FOR\" LOOP");
8599 else
8600 line_marker;
8601 writeln(log, "EXIT FOR " <& forLoop[1].varName);
8602 param1 := statement_label;
8603 symbol := "";
8604 if find_next(symbol, line, forLoop[1].varName) then
8605 forLoop := forLoop[2 .. ];
8606 else
8607 error_marker(param1);
8608 writeln(err, "NO CORRESPONDING \"NEXT\" OR \"NEXT " <&
8609 forLoop[1].varName <& "\" FOUND FOR \"EXIT FOR\"");
8610 end if;
8611 end if;
8612 elsif symbol = "DO" or symbol = "LOOP" then
8613 param1 := statement_label;
8614 symbol := find_loop(line);
8615 if symbol = "LOOP" then
8616 doLoop := doLoop[2 .. ];
8617 line_marker;
8618 repeat
8619 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8620 until endOfStatement(symbol);
8621 writeln(log, "EXIT DO");
8622 else
8623 error_marker(param1);
8624 writeln(err, "NO CORRESPONDING \"LOOP\" FOUND FOR \"EXIT DO\"");
8625 end if;
8626 elsif symbol = "SELECT" then
8627 param1 := statement_label;
8628 symbol := find_end_select(line);
8629 if symbol = "SELECT" then
8630 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8631 line_marker;
8632 writeln(log, "EXIT SELECT");
8633 else
8634 error_marker(param1);
8635 writeln(err, "NO \"END SELECT\" FOUND");
8636 end if;
8637 elsif symbol = "SUB" then
8638 if length(gosubReturn) >= 1 then
8639 check_loop_stacks_before_return("EXIT SUB " & gosubReturn[1].subName);
8640 line_marker;
8641 write(log, "EXIT SUB " <& gosubReturn[1].subName <& " - RETURN TO ");
8642 do_return(symbol, line);
8643 line_marker;
8644 writeln(log);
8645 else
8646 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8647 error_marker;
8648 writeln(err, "EXIT SUB - RETURN WITHOUT CALL.");
8649 end if;
8650 elsif symbol = "FUNCTION" then
8651 if length(gosubReturn) >= 1 then
8652 check_loop_stacks_before_return("EXIT FUNCTION " & gosubReturn[1].subName);
8653 line_marker;
8654 write(log, "EXIT FUNCTION " <& gosubReturn[1].subName <& " - RETURN TO ");
8655 do_return(symbol, line);
8656 line_marker;
8657 writeln(log);
8658 else
8659 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8660 error_marker;
8661 writeln(err, "EXIT FUNCTION - RETURN WITHOUT CALL.");
8662 end if;
8663 else
8664 error_marker;
8665 writeln(err, "ILLEGAL STATEMENT \"EXIT " <& symbol <& "\"");
8666 end if;
8667 when {"FIELD", "FIELD#"}:
8668 if symbol = "FIELD#" then
8669 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8670 else
8671 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8672 if symbol = "#" then
8673 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8674 end if;
8675 end if;
8676 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
8677 field_value[index1] := 0 times "";
8678 while symbol = "," do
8679 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8680 index2 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
8681 if symbol = "AS" then
8682 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8683 elsif startsWith(symbol, "AS") then
8684 symbol := symbol[3 ..];
8685 else
8686 error_expect("AS", symbol);
8687 end if;
8688 if isStringVar(symbol) then
8689 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
8690 setStringVar(variable_name, "" lpad index2);
8691 field_value[index1] &:= [] (variable_name);
8692 line_marker;
8693 writeln(log, "FIELD #" <& index1 <& ", " <& index2 <&
8694 " AS " <& variable_name);
8695 else
8696 error_marker;
8697 writeln(err, "STRING VARIABLE EXPECTED AS FIELD - FOUND " <&
8698 literal(symbol) <& ".");
8699 end if;
8700 end while;
8701 when {"FILES"}:
8702 exec_files(symbol, line);
8703 when {"FLASH"}:
8704 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8705 if symbol = "=" or symbol = "(" or symbol = "[" then
8706 exec_let("FLASH", symbol, line);
8707 elsif symbol = ":" and "FLASH" in usedLabel then
8708 line_marker;
8709 writeln(log, "SKIP LABEL: FLASH");
8710 else
8711 line_marker;
8712 writeln(log, "**FLASH");
8713 end if;
8714 when {"FOR"}:
8715 exec_for(symbol, line);
8716 when {"FUNCTION"}:
8717 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8718 line_marker;
8719 writeln(log, "SKIP FUNCTION " <& symbol);
8720 symbol := find_end_function(line);
8721 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8722 line_marker;
8723 writeln(log, "END SKIP FUNCTION " <& symbol <& " " <& line);
8724 when {"GET", "GET#"}:
8725 if symbol = "GET#" then
8726 symbol := "#";
8727 else
8728 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8729 end if;

8734 line_marker;

8742 end if;

8746 end if;
8747 when {"GO"}:

8754 line_marker;

8761 until endOfStatement(symbol);
8762 end if;

8772 line_marker;

8774 else

8776 screen(320, 200);
8777 win := open(curr_win, 8);
8778 if curr_win <> PRIMITIVE_WINDOW.value then
8779 clear(curr_win, black);
8780 color(white, black);
8781 scr := open(curr_win);
8782 KEYBOARD := GRAPH_KEYBOARD;

8784 IN := openEcho(KEYBOARD, OUT);
8785 IN := openLine(IN);
8786 end if;
8787 line_marker;
8788 writeln(log, "GR");
8789 end if;

8939 when {"LIST"}:

8942 index1 := integer(symbol);
8943 symbol := get_symbol(line);

8945 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8946 if symbol <> "" and symbol[1] in digit_char then
8947 index2 := integer(symbol);
8948 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8949 else
8950 index2 := MAX_LINENUM;
8951 end if;
8952 else
8953 index2 := index1;
8954 end if;
8955 else

8958 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8959 if symbol <> "" and symbol[1] in digit_char then
8960 index2 := integer(symbol);
8961 symbol := get_symbol(line);
8962 else
8963 index2 := MAX_LINENUM;
8964 end if;
8965 else
8966 index2 := MAX_LINENUM;

8970 listProg(win, index1, index2);
8971 when {"LOAD"}:

8978 line_marker;

8980 length(prg) <& " LINES");
8981 file_line_number := 0;
8982 symbol := "";
8983 line := "";
8984 elsif on_error_label <> "" then
8985 symbol := get_symbol(line);

8990 goto_on_error(on_error_label, line);
8991 symbol := "";
8992 line := "";
8993 else
8994 error_marker;
8995 writeln(err, "LOAD " <& literal(param1) <& " - FILE NOT FOUND.");
8996 end if;
8997 else
8998 error_marker;

9000 end if;
9001 when {"LOCATE"}:
9002 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9003 if symbol = "," or endOfStatement(symbol) then
9004 index1 := line(win);
9005 else
9006 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
9007 end if;
9008 if symbol = "," then
9009 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9010 end if;
9011 if symbol = "," or endOfStatement(symbol) then
9012 index2 := column(win);
9013 else
9014 index2 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
9015 end if;
9016 if symbol = "," then
9017 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9018 end if;
9019 if symbol = "," or endOfStatement(symbol) then
9020 okay := FALSE;
9021 else
9022 okay := TRUE;
9023 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
9024 end if;
9025 if symbol = "," then
9026 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9027 end if;
9028 if symbol <> "," and not endOfStatement(symbol) then
9029 ignore(exec_expr(symbol, line));
9030 end if;
9031 if symbol = "," then
9032 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9033 end if;
9034 if not endOfStatement(symbol) then
9035 ignore(exec_expr(symbol, line));
9036 end if;
9037 setPos(win, index1, index2);
9038 if okay then
9039 if round(num1) = 0 then
9040 cursor(scr, FALSE);
9041 else
9042 cursor(scr, TRUE);
9043 end if;
9044 end if;
9045 line_marker;
9046 write(log, "LOCATE " <& index1 <& ", " <& index2);
9047 if okay then
9048 write(log, ", " <& num1);
9049 end if;
9050 writeln(log);
9051 when {"LOOP"}:
9052 exec_loop(symbol, line);
9053 when {"LPRINT"}:

9063 index1 := length(getStringVar(variable_name));
9064 if length(param3) <= index1 then
9065 param3 := param3 rpad index1;

9075 "\" - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
9076 end if;

9080 literal(symbol) <& ".");
9081 end if;

9268 when {"RESUME"}:

9277 end if;
9278 elsif on_error_label <> "" then

9280 error_code := 20; # RESUME without error

9283 " - ON ERROR GOTO " <& on_error_label);
9284 goto_on_error(on_error_label, line);

9286 line := "";
9287 else

9291 elsif label_or_linenum(symbol) then

9293 line_marker;

9295 goto_label_or_linenum(symbol);
9296 in_error_handler := FALSE;
9297 symbol := "";
9298 line := "";
9299 elsif on_error_label <> "" then
9300 param1 := symbol;
9301 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9302 error_code := 20; # RESUME without error
9303 line_marker;
9304 writeln(log, error_code <& " RESUME " <& param1 <& " WITHOUT ERROR" <&
9305 " - ON ERROR GOTO " <& on_error_label);
9306 goto_on_error(on_error_label, line);
9307 symbol := "";
9308 line := "";
9309 else
9310 error_marker;
9311 writeln(err, "RESUME " <& symbol <& " - NOT IN ERROR HANDLER.");
9312 end if;
9313 elsif symbol = "0" or endOfStatement(symbol) then
9314 if in_error_handler then
9315 do_resume_same(symbol, line);
9316 elsif on_error_label <> "" then
9317 if symbol = "0" then
9318 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9319 end if;
9320 error_code := 20; # RESUME without error
9321 line_marker;
9322 writeln(log, error_code <& " RESUME 0 WITHOUT ERROR" <&
9323 " - ON ERROR GOTO " <& on_error_label);
9324 goto_on_error(on_error_label, line);
9325 symbol := "";
9326 line := "";
9327 else
9328 error_marker;
9329 writeln(err, "RESUME 0 - NOT IN ERROR HANDLER.");
9330 end if;
9331 else
9332 error_marker;
9333 writeln(err, "RESUME " <& symbol <& " - UNDEFINED RESUME.");
9334 end if;
9335 when {"RETURN"}:
9336 if length(gosubReturn) >= 1 then
9337 check_loop_stacks_before_return("RETURN");
9338 line_marker;
9339 write(log, "RETURN FROM \"GOSUB ");
9340 line_marker(gosubReturn[1].subEntryLine);
9341 write(log, "\"");
9342 do_return(symbol, line);
9343 write(log, " AT LINE ");
9344 line_marker;
9345 writeln(log);
9346 elsif on_error_label <> "" then
9347 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9348 error_code := 3; # RETURN without GOSUB
9349 line_marker;
9350 writeln(log, error_code <& " RETURN WITHOUT GOSUB" <&
9351 " - ON ERROR GOTO " <& on_error_label);
9352 goto_on_error(on_error_label, line);
9353 symbol := "";
9354 line := "";
9355 else
9356 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9357 error_marker;
9358 writeln(err, "RETURN WITHOUT GOSUB.");
9359 end if;
9360 when {"RSET"}:
9361 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9362 if isStringVar(symbol) then
9363 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
9364 if symbol = "=" then
9365 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9366 param3 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, unused_name);
9367 index1 := length(getStringVar(variable_name));
9368 if length(param3) <= index1 then
9369 param3 := param3 lpad index1;
9370 else
9371 param3 := param3[.. index1];
9372 end if;
9373 setStringVar(variable_name, param3);
9374 line_marker;
9375 writeln(log, "RSET " <& variable_name <& "=" <& literal(param3));
9376 else
9377 error_marker;
9378 writeln(err, "\"=\" EXPECTED AFTER \"RSET " <& variable_name <&
9379 "\" - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
9380 end if;
9381 else
9382 error_marker;
9383 writeln(err, "STRING VARIABLE EXPECTED AFTER RSET - FOUND " <&
9384 literal(symbol) <& ".");
9385 end if;
9386 when {"RUN"}:
9387 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9388 if isStringExpr(symbol) then
9389 param1 := exec_str_expr(symbol, line, variable_name);
9390 clearProgram;
9391 if runOrChain("RUN", param1) then
9392 writeln(log, "load program finished");
9393 line_marker;
9394 writeln(log, "RUN " <& literal(param1) <& " - " <&
9395 length(prg) <& " LINES");
9396 file_line_number := 0;
9397 symbol := "";
9398 line := "";
9399 elsif on_error_label <> "" then
9400 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9401 error_code := 53; # File not found
9402 line_marker;
9403 writeln(log, error_code <& " RUN " <& literal(param1) <&
9404 " - FILE NOT FOUND - ON ERROR GOTO " <& on_error_label);
9405 goto_on_error(on_error_label, line);
9406 symbol := "";
9407 line := "";
9408 else
9409 error_marker;
9410 writeln(err, "RUN " <& literal(param1) <& " - FILE NOT FOUND.");
9411 end if;
9412 elsif label_or_linenum(symbol) then
9413 clearProgram;
9414 line_marker;
9415 writeln(log, "RUN " <& symbol);
9416 goto_label_or_linenum(symbol);
9417 symbol := "";
9418 line := "";
9419 else
9420 clearProgram;
9421 line_marker;
9422 writeln(log, "RUN");
9423 file_line_number := 0;
9424 symbol := "";
9425 line := "";
9426 end if;
9427 when {"SCREEN"}:
9428 exec_screen(symbol, line);
9429 when {"SEEK", "SEEK#"}:
9430 exec_seek(symbol, line);
9431 when {"SELECT"}:
9432 exec_select(symbol, line);
9433 when {"SHARED"}:
9434 line_marker;
9435 writeln(log, "SHARED " <& line);
9436 repeat
9437 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9438 until endOfStatement(symbol);
9439 when {"SLEEP"}:
9440 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9441 if endOfStatement(symbol) then
9442 index1 := 1;
9443 else
9444 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
9445 end if;
9446 flush(win);
9447 sleep(index1);
9448 line_marker;
9449 writeln(log, "SLEEP " <& index1);
9450 when {"SOUND"}:
9451 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9452 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
9453 expect(",", symbol, line);
9454 num2 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
9455 line_marker;
9456 writeln(log, "**SOUND " <& symbol);
9457 when {"STOP", "SYSTEM"}:
9458 line_marker;
9459 writeln(log, symbol);
9460 symbol := "";
9461 running := FALSE;
9462 when {"SWAP"}:
9463 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9464 if isStringVar(symbol) then
9465 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
9466 expect(",", symbol, line);
9467 if isStringVar(symbol) then
9468 variable2_name := get_name(symbol, line);
9469 param1 := getStringVar(variable_name);
9470 param2 := getStringVar(variable2_name);
9471 setStringVar(variable_name, param2);
9472 setStringVar(variable2_name, param1);
9473 else
9474 error_marker;
9475 writeln(err, "STRING VARIABLE EXPECTED - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
9476 end if;
9477 elsif isNumericVar(symbol) then
9478 variable_name := get_name(symbol, line);
9479 expect(",", symbol, line);
9480 if isNumericVar(symbol) then
9481 variable2_name := get_name(symbol, line);
9482 num1 := getNumericVar(variable_name);
9483 num2 := getNumericVar(variable2_name);
9484 setNumericVar(variable_name, num2);
9485 setNumericVar(variable2_name, num1);
9486 else
9487 error_marker;
9488 writeln(err, "NUMERIC VARIABLE EXPECTED - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
9489 end if;
9490 else
9491 error_marker;
9492 writeln(err, "VARIABLE EXPECTED - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
9493 end if;
9494 when {"SUB"}:
9495 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9496 line_marker;
9497 writeln(log, "SKIP SUB " <& symbol);
9498 symbol := find_end_sub(line);
9499 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9500 line_marker;
9501 writeln(log, "END SKIP SUB " <& symbol <& " " <& line);
9502 when {"TEXT"}:
9503 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9504 if symbol = "=" or symbol = "(" or symbol = "[" then
9505 exec_let("TEXT", symbol, line);
9506 elsif symbol = ":" and "TEXT" in usedLabel then
9507 line_marker;
9508 writeln(log, "SKIP LABEL: TEXT");
9509 else
9510 scr := open(CONSOLE);
9511 win := openWindow(scr, 1, 1, TEXT_LINES, TEXT_COLUMNS);
9512 KEYBOARD := CONSOLE_KEYBOARD;
9513 OUT := win;
9514 IN := openEcho(KEYBOARD, OUT);
9515 IN := openLine(IN);
9516 line_marker;
9517 writeln(log, "TEXT");
9518 end if;
9519 when {"TYPE"}:
9520 exec_type(symbol, line);
9521 when {"VTAB"}:
9522 if is_let_statement(line) then
9523 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9524 exec_let("VTAB", symbol, line);
9525 else
9526 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9527 if symbol = ":" and "VTAB" in usedLabel then
9528 line_marker;
9529 writeln(log, "SKIP LABEL: VTAB");
9530 else
9531 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
9532 index2 := column(win);
9533 setPos(win, index1, index2);
9534 line_marker;
9535 writeln(log, "VTAB " <& index1);
9536 end if;
9537 end if;
9538 when {"WAIT"}:
9539 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9540 index1 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
9541 expect(",", symbol, line);
9542 index2 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
9543 if symbol = "," then
9544 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9545 index3 := round(exec_expr(symbol, line));
9546 else
9547 index3 := 0;
9548 end if;
9549 line_marker;
9550 case index1 of
9551 when {16#3DA}: # &H3DA/986 Wait for vertical retrace
9552 writeln(log, "WAIT " <& index1 <& ", " <& index2 <& ", " <& index3 <&
9553 " - Wait for vertical retrace");
9554 otherwise:
9555 writeln(log, "**WAIT " <& index1 <& ", " <& index2 <& ", " <& index3);
9556 end case;
9557 when {"WEND"}:
9558 if length(whileLoop) >= 1 then
9559 index1 := whileLoop[1].condLine;
9560 param2 := prg[index1].line[whileLoop[1].condColumn .. ];
9561 param1 := get_symbol(param2);
9562 num1 := exec_expr(param1, param2);
9563 if num1 <> 0.0 then
9564 line_marker;
9565 file_line_number := index1;
9566 statement_label := prg[file_line_number].linenum;
9567 symbol := param1;
9568 line := param2;
9569 writeln(log, "WEND - CONTINUE WHILE");
9570 else
9571 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9572 whileLoop := whileLoop[2 .. ];
9573 line_marker;
9574 writeln(log, "WEND - END WHILE");
9575 end if;
9576 else
9577 error_marker;
9578 writeln(err, "UNEXPECTED \"WEND\"");
9579 end if;
9580 when {"WHILE"}:
9581 index1 := file_line_number;
9582 index2 := length(prg[file_line_number].line) - length(line) + 1;
9583 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9584 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
9585 line_marker;
9586 writeln(log, "WHILE " <& num1);
9587 if num1 <> 0.0 then
9588 whileLoop := [] (whileLoopDescrType.value) & whileLoop;
9589 whileLoop[1].condLine := index1;
9590 whileLoop[1].condColumn := index2;
9591 else
9592 line_marker;
9593 writeln(log, "EMPTY WHILE");
9594 if symbol <> "WEND" then
9595 param1 := statement_label;
9596 symbol := find_wend(line);
9597 end if;
9598 if symbol = "WEND" then
9599 repeat
9600 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9601 until endOfStatement(symbol);
9602 line_marker;
9603 writeln(log, "CONTINUE AFTER WEND");
9604 else
9605 error_marker(param1);
9606 writeln(err, "NO CORRESPONDING \"WEND\" FOUND FOR \"WHILE\"");
9607 end if;
9608 end if;
9609 when {"WIDTH"}:
9610 line_marker;
9611 writeln(log, "**WIDTH " <& line);
9612 repeat
9613 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9614 until endOfStatement(symbol);
9615 when {"WRITE", "WRITE#"}:
9616 if symbol = "WRITE#" then
9617 symbol := "#";
9618 else
9619 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9620 end if;
9621 if symbol = "#" then
9622 exec_write_to_file(symbol, line);
9623 else
9624 exec_write(symbol, line);
9625 end if;
9626 when {"'"}:
9627 symbol := "";
9628 line_marker;
9629 writeln(log, "'" <& line);
9630 when {"%"}:
9631 variable_name := "";
9632 repeat
9633 variable_name &:= symbol;
9634 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9635 if symbol <> "" and symbol[1] in alphanum_char then
9636 variable_name &:= symbol;
9637 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9638 end if;
9639 until symbol <> "_";
9640 append_index(variable_name, symbol, line);
9641 if symbol = "=" then
9642 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9643 num1 := exec_expr(symbol, line);
9644 setNumericVar(variable_name, num1);
9645 line_marker;
9646 writeln(log, variable_name <& "=" <& num1);
9647 else
9648 error_marker;
9649 writeln(err, "\"=\" EXPECTED AFTER " <& literal(variable_name) <&
9650 " - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
9651 end if;
9652 when {":"}:
9653 error_marker;
9654 writeln(err, "UNEXPECTED \":\" - IGNORED.");
9655 otherwise:
9656 if symbol in subprogram then
9657 line_marker;
9658 writeln(log, "CALL " <& symbol);
9659 advance_after_statement(line);
9660 set_return_position(line);
9661 gosubReturn[1].subName := symbol;
9662 file_line_number := subprogram[symbol];
9663 statement_label := prg[file_line_number].label;
9664 line := prg[file_line_number].line;
9665 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9666 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9667 set_sub_entry_position;
9668 line_marker;
9669 writeln(log, "EXECUTE SUB " <& symbol);
9670 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
9671 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9672 end while;
9673 elsif symbol in sub_declared then
9674 error_marker;
9675 writeln(err, "CALL DECLARED BUT UNDEFINED SUB " <& symbol);
9676 while not endOfStatement(symbol) do
9677 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9678 end while;
9679 elsif symbol in usedLabel then
9680 param1 := symbol;
9681 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9682 if symbol = "=" or symbol = "(" or symbol = "[" then
9683 exec_let(param1, symbol, line);
9684 elsif symbol = ":" then
9685 line_marker;
9686 writeln(log, "SKIP LABEL: " <& param1);
9687 else
9688 error_marker;
9689 writeln(err, "COLON EXPECTED AFTER LABEL " <& param1 <&
9690 " - FOUND " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
9691 end if;
9692 else
9693 exec_let(symbol, line, process_next);
9694 end if;
9695 end case;
9696 if symbol = ":" then
9697 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9698 if symbol = ":" then
9699 # Allow :: as statement separator.
9700 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9701 end if;
9702 process_next := TRUE;
9703 end if;
9704 until not process_next;
9705 if symbol = "REM" then
9706 line_marker;
9707 writeln(log, "REM " <& line);
9708 elsif symbol = "'" then
9709 line_marker;
9710 writeln(log, "'" <& line);
9711 elsif symbol = "ELSE" then
9712 line_marker;
9713 writeln(log, "SKIP ELSE PART - CONTINUE AT NEXT LINE");
9714 elsif symbol <> "" then
9715 error_marker;
9716 writeln(err, "UNEXPECTED SYMBOL " <& literal(symbol) <& ".");
9717 repeat
9718 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9719 until endOfStatement(symbol);
9720 if symbol = ":" then
9721 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9722 running := execCmd(symbol, line);
9723 end if;
9724 end if;
9725 end func;
9726
9727
9728const proc: execLines is func
9729 local
9730 var boolean: running is TRUE;
9731 var string: symbol is "";
9732 var string: line is "";
9733 begin
9734 while running do
9735 if file_line_number > length(prg) then
9736 writeln(log, "END OF PROGRAM REACHED");
9737 running := FALSE;
9738 elsif prg[file_line_number].line <> "" then
9739 statement_label := prg[file_line_number].linenum;
9740 line := prg[file_line_number].line;
9741 (* writeln(file_line_number lpad 5 <& " " <&
9742 prg[file_line_number].line); *)
9743 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9744 running := execCmd(symbol, line);
9745 end if;
9746 incr(file_line_number);
9747 end while;
9748 end func;
9749
9750
9751const proc: runProg is func
9752 begin
9753 file_line_number := 1;
9754 execLines;
9755 end func;
9756
9757
9758const proc: logLine (in lineType: aLine) is func
9759 begin
9760 if aLine.linenum <> "" then
9761 write(log, aLine.linenum lpad 5 <& " ");
9762 else
9763 write(log, "" lpad 5 <& " ");
9764 end if;
9765 writeln(log, aLine.line);
9766 end func;
9767
9768
9769const proc: prepareLoops is func
9770 local
9771 var boolean: processing is TRUE;
9772 var string: symbol is "";
9773 var string: line is "";
9774 var string: headLabel is "";
9775 var integer: headLine is 0;
9776 var integer: headColumn is 0;
9777 var integer: tailLine is 0;
9778 var integer: tailColumn is 0;
9779 var string: variable_name is "";
9780 begin
9781 file_line_number := 1;
9782 while processing do
9783 if file_line_number > length(prg) then
9784 processing := FALSE;
9785 elsif prg[file_line_number].line <> "" then
9786 statement_label := prg[file_line_number].linenum;
9787 line := prg[file_line_number].line;
9788 repeat
9789 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9790 # line_marker;
9791 # writeln(log, literal(symbol));
9792 if symbol = "DO" then
9793 headLabel := statement_label;
9794 headLine := file_line_number;
9795 headColumn := length(prg[file_line_number].line) - length(line) + 1;
9796 symbol := find_loop(line);
9797 if symbol = "LOOP" then
9798 tailLine := file_line_number;
9799 tailColumn := length(prg[file_line_number].line) - length(line) + 1;
9800 # writeln(log, "LOOP[" <& tailLine <& "," <& tailColumn <&
9801 # "]->DO[" <& headLine <& "," <& headColumn <& "]");
9802 addDoLoopHeader(tailLine, tailColumn, headLine, headColumn);
9803 file_line_number := headLine;
9804 line := prg[file_line_number].line[headColumn .. ];
9805 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9806 else
9807 file_line_number := headLine;
9808 line := prg[file_line_number].line[headColumn .. ];
9809 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9810 if symbol <> "=" then
9811 error_marker(headLabel);
9812 writeln(err, "DO - NO STATICALLY CORRESPONDING \"LOOP\" STATEMENT FOUND ");
9813 end if;
9814 end if;
9815 elsif symbol = "LOOP" then
9816 tailLine := file_line_number;
9817 tailColumn := length(prg[file_line_number].line) - length(line) + 1;
9818 if not doLoopHeaderPresent(tailLine, tailColumn, headLine, headColumn) then
9819 error_marker;
9820 writeln(err, "LOOP - NO STATICALLY CORRESPONDING \"DO\" STATEMENT FOUND");
9821 end if;
9822 elsif ignoreRestOfLine(symbol) then
9823 line := "";
9824 symbol := "";
9825 end if;
9826 while symbol <> "THEN" and not endOfStatement(symbol) do
9827 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9828 end while;
9829 if ignoreRestOfLine(symbol) then
9830 line := "";
9831 symbol := "";
9832 end if;
9833 until symbol = "";
9834 end if;
9835 incr(file_line_number);
9836 end while;
9837 file_line_number := 1;
9838 end func;
9839
9840
9841const proc: preprocessLine (in var string: line) is func
9842 local
9843 var string: symbol is "";
9844 var string: label is "";
9845 begin
9846 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9847 while symbol <> "" do
9848 if symbol = "GOTO" or symbol = "GOSUB" or
9849 symbol = "THEN" or symbol = "ELSE" or
9850 symbol = "RESTORE" or symbol = "RUN" then
9851 label := get_symbol(line);
9852 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9853 if endOfStatement(symbol) and
9854 label not in not_allowed_as_label and
9855 label <> "" and label[1] in letter_char then
9856 incl(usedLabel, label);
9857 end if;
9858 elsif symbol = "REM" or symbol = "'" then
9859 symbol := "";
9860 else
9861 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9862 end if;
9863 if symbol = ":" then
9864 symbol := get_symbol(line);
9865 incl(usedAsStatement, symbol);
9866 end if;
9867 end while;
9868 end func;
9869
9870
9871const proc: checkLabels is func
9872 local
9873 var string: aLabel is "";
9874 var integer: number is 0;
9875 var boolean: first is TRUE;
9876 begin
9877 for key aLabel range multipleDefinedLabel do
9878 if aLabel in usedLabel then
9879 write(err, " ***** LABEL " <& aLabel <&
9880 " DEFINED IN MULTIPLE LINES: ");
9881 for number range multipleDefinedLabel[aLabel] do
9882 if first then
9883 first := FALSE;
9884 else
9885 write(log, ", ");
9886 end if;
9887 if number <= length(prg) and prg[number].linenum <> "" then
9888 write(err, prg[number].linenum);
9889 else
9890 write(err, "(" <& number <& ")");
9891 end if;
9892 end for;
9893 writeln(err);
9894 end if;
9895 end for;
9896 for key aLabel range subprogram do
9897 excl(usedLabel, aLabel);
9898 end for;
9899 usedLabel := usedLabel - usedAsStatement;
9900 for aLabel range usedAsStatement do
9901 excl(label, aLabel);
9902 end for;
9903 for aLabel range usedLabel do
9904 if aLabel not in label then
9905 if aLabel in multipleDefinedLabel then
9906 writeln(err, " ***** LABEL " <& aLabel <&
9907 " USED BUT DEFINED MULTIPLE TIMES.");
9908 else
9909 writeln(err, " ***** LABEL " <& aLabel <&
9910 " USED BUT NOT DEFINED.");
9911 end if;
9912 end if;
9913 end for;
9914 end func;
9915
9916
9917const func boolean: loadProg (in string: name) is forward;
9918
9919
9920const proc: loadProg (in string: name, inout file: infile) is func
9921 local
9922 var integer: file_line_number is 0;
9923 var string: symbol is "";
9924 var string: line_number is "";
9925 var string: line_label is "";
9926 var string: line is "";
9927 var string: help_line is "";
9928 var string: variable_name is "";
9929 var boolean: control_z is FALSE;
9930 var boolean: continuation_line is FALSE;
9931 var integer: number is 1;
9932 var integer: line_number_incr is 1;
9933 begin
9934 repeat
9935 line := getln(infile);
9936 for number range 1 to pred(line_number_incr) do
9937 prg &:= [] (lineType.value);
9938 writeln(log);
9939 end for;
9940 file_line_number +:= line_number_incr;
9941 line_number_incr := 1;
9942 repeat
9943 if pos(line, "\Z") <> 0 then
9944 # Control-Z is used sometimes as end of file marker.
9945 line := line[.. pred(pos(line, "\Z"))];
9946 control_z := TRUE;
9947 end if;
9948 line := trim(line);
9949 if length(line) >= 2 and line[pred(length(line)) ..] = " _" then
9950 continuation_line := TRUE;
9951 line := line[.. pred(length(line))] & getln(infile);
9952 incr(line_number_incr);
9953 else
9954 continuation_line := FALSE;
9955 end if;
9956 until not continuation_line;
9957 if line <> "" then
9958 if line[1] in digit_char then
9959 line_number := getDigits(line);
9960 if line <> "" and line[1] = '.' then
9961 # Accept line numbers with decimal point
9962 line_number &:= ".";
9963 line := line[2 .. ];
9964 line_number &:= getDigits(line);
9965 end if;
9966 while line <> "" and line[1] = ' ' do
9967 line := line[2 .. ];
9968 end while;
9969 if line_number in label then
9970 writeln(err, " ***** LINE NUMBER " <& line_number <&
9971 " ALREADY DEFINED AS " <& name <&
9972 "(" <& label[line_number] <& ")");
9973 else
9974 label @:= [line_number] succ(length(prg));
9975 end if;
9976 else
9977 line_number := "";
9978 end if;
9979 help_line := line;
9980 symbol := get_symbol(help_line);
9981 if symbol = "'" or symbol = "REM" then
9982 repeat
9983 symbol := get_symbol(help_line);
9984 until symbol = "" or symbol = "$";
9985 symbol := get_symbol(help_line);
9986 if symbol = "INCLUDE" then
9987 symbol := get_symbol(help_line);
9988 if symbol = ":" then
9989 symbol := get_symbol(help_line);
9990 if symbol = "'" then
9991 symbol := help_line[.. pred(pos(help_line, '\''))];
9992 if symbol <> "" then
9993 prg &:= [] (lineType.value);
9994 prg[length(prg)].fileName := name;
9995 prg[length(prg)].fileLine := file_line_number;
9996 prg[length(prg)].linenum := line_number;
9997 prg[length(prg)].label := line_label;
9998 prg[length(prg)].line := line;
9999 logLine(prg[length(prg)]);
10000 if not loadProg(symbol) then
10001 writeln(err, " ***** INCLUDE FILE " <& literal(symbol) <&
10002 " NOT FOUND.");
10003 end if;
10004 writeln(log, "---------- END INCLUDE ----------");
10005 end if;
10006 end if;
10007 end if;
10008 end if;
10009 elsif symbol = "#" or symbol = "$" then
10010 symbol := get_symbol(help_line);
10011 if symbol = "INCLUDE" then
10012 symbol := get_symbol(help_line);
10013 if symbol <> "" and symbol[1] = '"' then
10014 symbol := symbol[2 ..];
10015 prg &:= [] (lineType.value);
10016 prg[length(prg)].fileName := name;
10017 prg[length(prg)].fileLine := file_line_number;
10018 prg[length(prg)].linenum := line_number;
10019 prg[length(prg)].label := line_label;
10020 prg[length(prg)].line := line;
10021 logLine(prg[length(prg)]);
10022 if not loadProg(symbol) then
10023 writeln(err, " ***** INCLUDE FILE " <& literal(symbol) <&
10024 " NOT FOUND.");
10025 end if;
10026 writeln(log, "---------- END INCLUDE ----------");
10027 end if;
10028 end if;
10029 elsif symbol = "SUB" then
10030 symbol := get_symbol(help_line);
10031 if symbol in subprogram then
10032 writeln(err, " ***** SUB " <& symbol <&
10033 " ALREADY DEFINED AS " <& name <&
10034 "(" <& subprogram[symbol] <& ")");
10035 else
10036 subprogram @:= [symbol] succ(length(prg));
10037 end if;
10038 line_label := "";
10039 elsif symbol = "FUNCTION" then
10040 symbol := get_symbol(help_line);
10041 if symbol in subfunction then
10042 writeln(err, " ***** FUNCTION " <& symbol <&
10043 " ALREADY DEFINED AS " <& name <&
10044 "(" <& subfunction[symbol] <& ")");
10045 else
10046 subfunction @:= [symbol] succ(length(prg));
10047 end if;
10048 line_label := "";
10049(*
10050 elsif symbol = "DEF" then
10051 symbol := get_symbol(help_line);
10052 if symbol = "SEG" then
10053 noop;
10054 else
10055 variable_name := symbol;
10056 if variable_name[1] >= 'A' and variable_name[1] <= 'Z' then
10057 define_function(variable_name, symbol, help_line, FALSE);
10058 end if;
10059 end if;
10060*)
10061 elsif symbol = "" or symbol in not_allowed_as_label or
10062 symbol in sub_declared then
10063 line_label := "";
10064 elsif startsWith(symbol, "NEXT") and length(symbol) = 5 and
10065 symbol[5] in letter_char then
10066 line_label := "";
10067 elsif startsWith(symbol, "READ") and length(symbol) = 5 and
10068 symbol[5] in letter_char then
10069 line_label := "";
10070 elsif startsWith(symbol, "GOTO") and isDigitString(symbol[5 ..]) or
10071 startsWith(symbol, "GOSUB") and isDigitString(symbol[6 ..]) then
10072 line_label := "";
10073 else
10074 line_label := symbol;
10075 symbol := get_symbol(help_line);
10076 if line_label[1] in letter_char and symbol = ":" then
10077 if line_label in multipleDefinedLabel then
10078 multipleDefinedLabel[line_label] &:= succ(length(prg));
10079 line_label := "";
10080 elsif line_label in label then
10081 multipleDefinedLabel @:= [line_label] [] (label[line_label], succ(length(prg)));
10082 excl(label, line_label);
10083 line_label := "";
10084 else
10085 label @:= [line_label] succ(length(prg));
10086 end if;
10087 else
10088 line_label := "";
10089 end if;
10090 end if;
10091 preprocessLine(line);
10092 prg &:= [] (lineType.value);
10093 prg[length(prg)].fileName := name;
10094 prg[length(prg)].fileLine := file_line_number;
10095 prg[length(prg)].linenum := line_number;
10096 prg[length(prg)].label := line_label;
10097 prg[length(prg)].line := line;
10098 logLine(prg[length(prg)]);
10099 else
10100 prg &:= [] (lineType.value);
10101 writeln(log);
10102 end if;
10103 until eof(infile) or control_z;
10104 checkLabels;
10105 if length(label) <> 0 then
10106 writeln(log, "Labels:");
10107 for number key line_label range label do
10108 if line_label[1] not in digit_char then
10109 write(log, line_label <& ": ");
10110 if number <= length(prg) then
10111 if prg[number].linenum <> "" then
10112 write(log, prg[number].linenum);
10113 else
10114 if prg[number].fileName <> prg[1].fileName then
10115 write(log, prg[number].fileName);
10116 end if;
10117 write(log, "(" <& prg[number].fileLine <& ")");
10118 end if;
10119 end if;
10120 writeln(log);
10121 end if;
10122 end for;
10123 end if;
10124 writeln(log, "usedLabels: " <& usedLabel);
10125 end func;
10126
10127
10128const func boolean: runOrChain (in string: cmd, in string: name) is func
10129 result
10130 var boolean: successful is FALSE;
10131 local
10132 var file: infile is STD_NULL;
10133 begin
10134 if lower(name[length(name) - 3 ..]) <> ".bas" then
10135 infile := basicOpen(name & ".bas", "r");
10136 end if;
10137 if infile = STD_NULL then
10138 infile := basicOpen(name, "r");
10139 end if;
10140 if infile <> STD_NULL then
10141 line_marker;
10142 writeln(log, cmd <& " " <& literal(name));
10143 prg := 0 times lineType.value;
10144 label := label_hash.EMPTY_HASH;
10145 subprogram := label_hash.EMPTY_HASH;
10146 subfunction := label_hash.EMPTY_HASH;
10147 sub_declared := label_hash.EMPTY_HASH;
10148 usedLabel := stringSet.value;
10149 usedAsStatement := stringSet.value;
10150 multipleDefinedLabel := multipleDefinedType.value;
10151 loadProg(name, infile);
10152 prepareLoops;
10153 close(infile);
10154 successful := TRUE;
10155 end if;
10156 end func;
10157
10158
10159const func boolean: loadProg (in string: name) is func
10160 result
10161 var boolean: successful is FALSE;
10162 local
10163 var file: infile is STD_NULL;
10164 begin
10165 if lower(name[length(name) - 3 ..]) <> ".bas" then
10166 infile := basicOpen(name & ".bas", "r");
10167 end if;
10168 if infile = STD_NULL then
10169 infile := basicOpen(name, "r");
10170 end if;
10171 if infile <> STD_NULL then
10172 loadProg(name, infile);
10173 close(infile);
10174 successful := TRUE;
10175 end if;
10176 end func;
10177
10178
10179const proc: interactiveMode is func
10180 local
10181 var file: commandFile is STD_NULL;
10182 var string: symbol is "";
10183 var string: line is "";
10184 var boolean: running is TRUE;
10185 begin
10186 scr := open(CONSOLE);
10187 cursor(scr, TRUE);
10188 win := openWindow(scr, 1, 1, TEXT_LINES, TEXT_COLUMNS);
10189 OUT := win;
10190 IN := openEcho(KEYBOARD, OUT);
10191 IN := openLine(IN);
10192 err := OUT;
10193 commandFile := openEditLine(KEYBOARD, OUT);
10194 writeln("Type END to exit direct mode.");
10195 repeat
10196 write("] ");
10197 readln(commandFile, line);
10198 symbol := get_symbol(line);
10199 running := execCmd(symbol, line);
10200 until not running;
10201 end func;
10202
10203
10204const proc: main is func
10205 local
10206 var array string: arg_v is 0 times "";
10207 var integer: argumentIndex is 1;
10208 var boolean: doPauseAtEnd is FALSE;
10209 var boolean: doLog is FALSE;
10210 var boolean: interactive is FALSE;
10211 begin
10212 arg_v := argv(PROGRAM);
10213 if length(arg_v) >= 1 then
10214 while argumentIndex <= length(arg_v) and
10215 startsWith(arg_v[argumentIndex], "-") do
10216 if arg_v[argumentIndex] = "-p" then
10217 doPauseAtEnd := TRUE;
10218 elsif arg_v[argumentIndex] = "-l" then
10219 doLog := TRUE;
10220 elsif arg_v[argumentIndex] = "-i" then
10221 interactive := TRUE;
10222 else
10223 writeln(" ***** Unknown option " <& arg_v[argumentIndex]);
10224 end if;
10225 incr(argumentIndex);
10226 end while;
10227 if argumentIndex <= length(arg_v) then
10228 if succ(argumentIndex) <= length(arg_v) then
10229 command_line := join(arg_v[succ(argumentIndex) ..], " ");
10230 end if;
10231 err := open("bas7.log", "w");
10232 if err = STD_NULL then
10233 writeln(" ***** Could not open log file.");
10234 else
10235 err := openLine(err);
10236 end if;
10237 if doLog then
10238 log := err;
10239 end if;
10240 if loadProg(arg_v[argumentIndex]) then
10241 writeln(log, "load program finished");
10242 prepareLoops;
10243 # listProg(log, 0, MAX_LINENUM);
10244 scr := open(CONSOLE);
10245 cursor(scr, TRUE);
10246 win := openWindow(scr, 1, 1, TEXT_LINES, TEXT_COLUMNS);
10247 OUT := win;
10248 IN := openEcho(KEYBOARD, OUT);
10249 IN := openLine(IN);
10250 runProg;
10251 if doPauseAtEnd then
10252 writeln("=== Program finished ===");
10253 write("Press return to continue ");
10254 readln(KEYBOARD);
10255 end if;
10256 else
10257 writeln(" ***** File " <& literal(arg_v[argumentIndex]) <&
10258 " not found.");
10259 end if;
10260 elsif interactive then
10261 interactiveMode;
10262 else
10263 writeln(" ***** File name missing");
10264 end if;
10265 else
10266 writeln("Bas7 Version 1.0 - Basic interpreter");
10267 writeln("Copyright (C) 1994, 2001, 2004 - 2010, 2013, 2016 - 2020 Thomas Mertes");
10268 writeln("This is free software; see the source for copying conditions. There is NO");
10269 writeln("warranty; not even for MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.");
10270 writeln("Bas7 is written in the Seed7 programming language");
10271 writeln("Homepage: http://seed7.sourceforge.net");
10272 writeln;
10273 writeln("usage: bas7 [options] basic_program");
10274 writeln;
10275 writeln("options: -p Ask for a prompt at the end of the program");
10276 writeln(" -l List program and write log of executed statements");
10277 end if;
10278 end func;
